{"commentID": 379, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As a mortgage lender for an FDIC-insured bank, I'm astounded at the number of customers who sit across from me and are wholly dumbfounded when I tell them their loan request is denied because of outstanding collections.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For certain there are some people who knew full well they would have collections items and are playing dumb (and not doing so very well).", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But many of them had no clue,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and 90% of those collections are medical in nature.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "If the CFPB truly is about protecting the interests of the consumer, then the debt collection process needs to be simplified drastically in regard to collection items (medical, utilities, etc.).", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "after 60 days of non-payment, the account can be closed.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The creditor sends a certified letter to the last known address of the debtor, informing them they have 30 days to bring the account current or make other payment arrangements, ", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "or the account will be turned over to a collection agency.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "Said letter also needs to contain the contact information for that collection agency,", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so they know in advance who to contact if they don't respond within 30 days.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, a lot of those letters will be returned undeliverable or will end up in someone else's hands.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But that would demonstrate a good faith effort by the creditors to work with the debtors before passing the buck to a collection agency.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The added benefit for the government is the increase in certified letters passing through the USPS!", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 380, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "When mortgage holders transfer servicing of a mortgage loan to another creditor, they have rules in place as to informing the consumer that their loan has been sold.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Apply the same standards to any debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 381, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The agency needs to be careful of new rules that will, though unintended, be harmful to the free market.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, it is important that litigation is monitored to ensure that the system does not allow reward with no risk.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A plaintiff in a lawsuit cannot be placed in a situation where it is rewarding to sue with insufficient cause and minimal risk.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Creditors and those following in the process of recovery do not need additional regulation in this area", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since their efforts are monitored by the CFPB.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The CFPB does not need to set standards for the industry,", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but make it clear that only those documents provided to the court in the original filing will be considered in a CFPB review.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8", "9"], "text": "If in the course of a CFPB review, it is found that litigation was filed without a successful verification of the facts, the CFPB could award the amount sought by the filing to the defendant of the case and a fine to the CFPB of no less than $2,000 but no more than the amount sought.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This position would motivate the litigant to ensure their facts were correct before any filing took place.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This position would allow CFPB to review cases filed no matter how they were adjudicated by the involved court.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "This review could be conducted at CFPB offices", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since it only requires the original filings.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This review could be initiated simply based on a complaint to the agency's offices.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The penalty could be adjustable based on a variety of agency standards.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would have to take more time to consider when the plaintiff was not the original creditor or a member of the recovery industry,", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but, again, there must be a risk associated with the reward to stop nuisance suits.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 382, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "There needs to be something in place to stop the frivilous law suits that agencies have to spend thousands of dollars to defend even though they have tried to explain to the consumers / attorneys that there was no wrong doing and no case", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "a lot of these consumers file the suits Pro Se and continue pushing for a settlement or trial", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "in these cases the agencies spend monies to prove there was no cause for action to begin with and to have a judge agree with the agency.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Please look at putting some kind of penalty on consumers or their attorneys when they send settlement demands or file law suits when they have been shown that there is / was no case", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 383, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_2"], "text": "Debt collectors should not be allowed to alter their caller ID information.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They call misrepresenting themselves as \"Process Servers\" inquiring information about another person's debt.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "This prevents the consumer from reporting the debt collector for violating consumer protection laws", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because a false identify was used.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 385, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_3"], "text": "First, a third party collecting on behalf of a lender isn't, nor should be, defined as a furnisher of information.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "While the FDCPA requires notice specific to the validity of the debt, ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "the FCRA has requirements for users of consumer reports.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Combining two statue requirements in the initial notice of a debt serves no purpose.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sending during the 30 day notice would create confusion in the event the consumer responds, for example, to the validity of the debt and does not include a request about a credit report accuracy.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "I believe the issue is whether a third party debt collector or debt buyer should report an account to a credit reporting agency which would overlap the original lender's last report on the consumer account.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7", "8"], "text": "In my opinion they should not.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have seen confusion due to lack of rule clarity.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For example, if a consumer files a bankruptcy petition who should report that event?", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "If a third party opts to report then the third party would be required to report events that take place during or after the bankruptcy filing.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To date, Title 11 offers no direction to reporting and neither does the FCRA other than a credit reporting agency removing after 10 years.", "type": "fact", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 386, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As a Director for Collections now for Kennedy Space Center Federal Credit Union, which is over 500 Million in asset size I try as I have for prior union to file suit closest to the Consumers current address.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One method is to assign over to an attorney within the current residence-venue of the Consumer.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In legal terms we attempt to get service when filing a suit out of state,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "its method is called obtaining if possible a Alien Juddgement outside from the County and or State the contract/note was originally signed.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are states in the Union that do note accept foreighn judgments.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "So recording a judgement obtained for example in Floirda and rerecorded in another State may not be possible.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 387, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Telephonic pretrial-hearings can be scheduled in support of a consumer having to work;", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "times set and or scheduled with a court representative could passify this issue.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 388, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Very confusing if I can pay my student loans directly to DOE or to one of the many private companies who have owned my loan over the years.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They continue to try to entice me to restructure the student loan debt - very misleading - without disclosure of their fees", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "at this point I cannot even trace a $30000 fee that was double billed to my total.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "It is a web of confusion that I cannot escape.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "I intend to take my student loans to my death", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as I have no other way of making the monthly payments.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 389, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Having gone through a Chapter 7 bankruptcy I can tell you that debt collector phone calls were the worst part of the bankruptcy experience.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "3", "4"], "text": "Massachusetts has it right limiting the number of calls debt collectors can make.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That would remove one of the favorite illegal tactics debt collectors use to harass debtors.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some debt collectors would threaten to put us on robocalls so that our phone rang hourly until we agreed to a repayment loan schedule.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Or they would threaten to call my spouse at work to see if he would be \"more cooperative\" and agree to a loan repayment schedule even after being informed that his workplace did not allow debt collection calls.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Nothing phased these people ", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they appeared to enjoy verbally abusing me.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Informing them that we wanted all debt collection to be written was also ignored.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10", "11", "9"], "text": "I could accurately predict who was calling by the day and time of the calls.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Chase Bank called every Tuesday morning at 9AM.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Bank of America called every Monday morning at 10:30AM.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These calls were always professional and appreciated.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I followed specific instructions given by our bankruptcy attorney who did not want the debt collectors to know that we were planning on filing bankruptcy in a few months.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "So I faithfully answered every single debt collector call for almost six months.", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I politely confirmed my identity.", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I confirmed I owed the debt ", "type": "testimony", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and then I politely told each call that I could not start to repay the debt at this time.", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The banks/credit cards accepted this without a problem and remained professional.", "type": "testimony", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Others like GE Capital and the vacation time share debt collectors would then start with the abusive comments.", "type": "testimony", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Calling me a \"deadbeat\" and swearing at me was popular.", "type": "testimony", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Another popular threat was how they would harass us nonstop until they got their money.", "type": "testimony", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What finally put a stop to the unethical tactics was when they would call and inform me that I was being taped I then informed them that I too was now taping their phone calls.", "type": "testimony", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most immediately hung up.", "type": "testimony", "id": 22, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A few would clean up their act and then act in a professional manner.", "type": "testimony", "id": 23, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The ability to tape debt collection calls is a powerful tool for the debtor to have", "type": "value", "id": 24, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["24", "26"], "text": "and I would encourage this agency to grant debtors this right.", "type": "value", "id": 25, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Nothing cleaned up the bad behavior like knowing they were being taped.", "type": "value", "id": 26, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 390, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Most of the consumer debt I see if coming from debt buyers and the consumer doesn't recognize the name or the amount.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many of these are beyond the statute of limitations to file suit ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but suit is filed anyway.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many consumers don't know to file an answer is court ", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "and a default judgment is entered.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The information you suggest would help a lot in letting consumers know what this debt is.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "I would include the trail of ownership of the debt", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "as there could be intermediary owners between the original creditor and final collector.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debts are sold and resold.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10", "11_12"], "text": "It would also help to have some documentation of the specific debt having been sold", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so the consumer can verify the current ownership of the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Currently, all they get in response to a validation request is \"we checked and you owe it\".", "type": "fact", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Our firm asks for specific documents related to the claimed debt and the response we get is \"the courts say we don't have to provide any documents...go fish\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 391, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The price of paper (bad debt) varies depending on the collectability of the debt based on info known about the debtor and also varies based on the amount of documentation purchased from the original creditor.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most debt buyers only pay for a couple of recent credit card statements.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They may provide a \"bill of sale\"", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but these never identify a specific account being sold and reference a master purchase contract which is never provided.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 392, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The majority of the collection disputes I help my clients with are never validated with documentation.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The CRA simply sends a letter stating that the debt was verified ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "although the dispute letter specifically asked for documentation.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 393, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "That's not true in my experience.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Unethical debt collectors just ignore requests now.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most consumers also don't know ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "that debt collectors can call you to collect a debt on any phone number you have used to contact the company or provided the company.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "So calling your credit card company from your best friend's home phone, your neighbor's phone, or your relative's house puts their phone numbers on your contact list.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This practice needs to be changed to protect the confidentiality of the debt collection process.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 394, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The majority of the clients I work with try to settle their accounts.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The main issue is that most of the collection companies will not provide the client with a letter of agreement until after the payment is made.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They also will often wait weeks for a receipt.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": ["3"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have even had clients tell me that the company required a $10.00 payment for the receipt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 395, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Unscrupulous debt collectors use this tactic trying to force people into agreeing to repay a debt.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The threat of debt collection calls at work is a powerful incentive to repay a debt.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
