{"commentID": 397, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "As a creditor, I can agree with this notification on medical services", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since most people receive bills from companies they never heard of.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When it comes to auto loans, and other monthly installment loans, I am sure the consumers are aware of the debt and who it is payable to, unless sold.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "This could be a huge regulatory burden on creditors that don't sell loans and follow current collection laws.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After all, do very many people pay monthly payment to the same people for several months and them forget they owe the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All laws should not apply to all creditors.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 398, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "\"Verify\" needs to be thoroughly defined.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It should be no less than documented court admissible evidence that the consumer is responsible for the debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the debt collector cannot produce this evidence, he should be barred from reselling the debt or reporting it to the CRAs.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 400, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I did the same thing ", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the response was immediate to stop the abusive behaviors.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": ["2", "3"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Like you most debt collectors just hang up.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Those who stayed on immediately changed their tone of voice and behavior.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1"], "text": "I would advise anyone receiving verbally abusive, harassing, or threatening phone calls from debt collection calls buy a cheap telephone recording device and to use it when they call.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "When they inform you at the mini-Miranda point interrupt them and tell them that you too are now recording all debt collection calls.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1"], "text": "It's the most powerful tool any debtor can use.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 402, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I was never informed by Bank of America that they sold my credit card and closed the card.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I realized it, I paid it off immediately.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "During that quarter, after long illnesses, my Father and Mother both passed (within 31 days of each other) ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and frankly, credit card payments were not in the forefront of my thinking.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "ALSO, just because a bank or credit card company has been exempted from Usury laws does not mean they do not commit the violation!", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "THAT needs to be stopped!", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 403, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Depends on the type of Bankruptcy.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "If it is a CH 13 many times the creditors receive more money than if they choose to forgive a portion of the debt and settle direct with the consumer.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is because of the strict \"means test\" for CH 7.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 404, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I am concerned about the perception consumers have concerning older debts.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "With the knowledge that this legislation is both to improve debt collection practices (helping the credit industry) and to educate and protect consumers (to increase confidence and enforce their rights), this is especially relevent.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many consumers appear to be under the impression, if they haven't managed to pay off the debt within the first initial years, they should *ignore* it until it falls off their credit report.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Reviving the debt is the issue.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yet these consumers are not concerned about paying the debt off in full", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they might be in much better financial standing now.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They're concerned about how paying a debt affects their credit score.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8", "9"], "text": "I believe this should be concerning.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a debt is outstanding, and repying part (or all) of this debt actually would *worsen* a consumer's credit, it seems counter-intuitive.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It works both against the interests of creditors and debt collectors - and the interest of consumers who owe money on a debt.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't know of a viable solution,", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I'm certain this is a concern which should be addressed.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 405, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Hardships are not all the same", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and some hardships can last for a year or longer.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As a consumer advocate I see very few creditors that are willing to do anything more than refer to CCC or reduce rates for a short period of time.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 406, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2"], "text": "If a consumer is notified that their debt has been sold, there should be a way to contact the original creditor to verify.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "4"], "text": "e. there should be a paper trail", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I see an opportunity for scam artists to claim that (as they are now) the consumer owes money to them and to pay off their debt immediately to the scam artist.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "With a clear paper/electronic trail, the path a debt takes from creditor to collector to collector can be verified and authenticated for the consumer's peace of mind,", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "and so the right party gets paid.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 407, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If a consumer sends a post dated check(s) and it bounces then it may not fall under the bad check enforcement.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also, consumers use ACH capability to repay a debt,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "so if the amount is not available, then this may also not fall under bad check enforcement.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My experience is more consumers use ACH rather than personal check distribution.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "there are numerous reasons why checks bounce", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "so I suggest a look see as to determining the reason or cause why the check bounced.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 409, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "while this isn't the best forum for me to go into my company's entire collection process, we work a debt for at least 120 days with letters, live agent calls, robo calls, emails, mailed invoices, and by suspending subscription service (where allowed) as part of our collection campaign.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Even then, we only go to litigation after the debtor has been unresponsive to our attempts to contact them.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've found that if a debtor talks to their creditors, many times creditors will take their situation into account.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've offered lengthy repayment plans, reduced or waived interest or late fees, or partial settlement for those explain their hardship.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But if a debtor is uncooperative or doesn't respond to our attempts to work out a balance, what other alternatives do creditors have?", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 410, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["3"], "text": "The CFPB should require debt sellers to contact the debtor and inform them the debt has been sold.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Additionally, ALL pertinent information must be given to the debtor to eliminate any confusion.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Furthermore, the seller of the debt must be required and enforced to annotate the debtors credit report with the sale to help eliminate confusion and in a way to not increase the bad debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Essentially, debts that are sold sometimes appear as two seperate debts on a consumers report which increases the penalty of having bad debt.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A consumer should not be penalized twice for 1 debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 411, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The CFPB should require debt sellers to contact the debtor and inform them the debt has been sold.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Additionally, ALL pertinent information must be given to the debtor to eliminate any confusion.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Furthermore, the seller of the debt must be required and enforced to annotate the debtors credit report with the sale to help eliminate confusion and in a way to not increase the bad debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Essentially, debts that are sold sometimes appear as two seperate debts on a consumers report which increases the penalty of having bad debt.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A consumer should not be penalized twice for 1 debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 412, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "If surviving spouses signed or agreed to a contract or extension of credit then they are obligated to repay in my opinion.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also, certain states that have community property laws may require a spouse to repay a debt even though they did not sign the contract.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I believe the executor or administrator should investigate whether any debt was disputed or possibly fraud.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To start they should obtain a credit report for starters regardless whether collectors disclose either way.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "If a collector knows a service member passed away, then the spouse, executor, administrator should not be contacted and the account closed law or no law", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as I have seen this type of issue arise over the years and have seen and approved accounts closed in the event a service member passed away.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 413, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The idea is sound in principle,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but as any technology geared towards convienance, there are risks against privacy encouraging identity theft.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Having creditors, collectors, and consumers come together \"on the same page\" regarding debt would be fantastic for everyone involved.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4_5"], "text": "But any technology which accomplishes this needs to be very secure with very strict authentication requirements to ensure *only* the relevant parties can view information concerning the debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Otherwise, not only thieves would have access to this information", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but also non-criminal third parties, who may never have learned of such information due to the protection of consumer privacy laws.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Knowledge of the debt and money owed would need to have the same level of security afforded to consumer reports and information within a consumer report (as defined in the FCRA).", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 414, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "security would be paramound.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Since the weaknesses in current authentication practices financial institutions/others covered by FACTA and the FCRA are not within the scope of this legislation,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "it shouldn't be difficult to impose those same security standards on any centralized debt collection database.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 416, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_3", "4"], "text": "I strongly endore drose977's response.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Currently, debt collection agencies can sell debt without proper validation.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Or they can sell the debt if a consumer disputes the debt and the agency can't product the proper validation.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These things should not be allowed and are very detrimental to the consumer.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5", "6"], "text": "Consumers should be protected above collectors and other agencies", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as they, typically, have far less resources to fight inaccurate information.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Additionally, the inaccurate information adversely effects consumers more than any other group in these situations.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Collectors should not be allowed to report a debt as 30 days late if the debt isn't 30 days late.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The law should include stiff enforcable penalities to deter collectors from pre-dating debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These rules should apply for any debt reported late at any time, not just the first 30 days.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 417, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The most common consumer contact my firm receives as a dispute is the comment by the consumer on a call with the agency that \"it's not my debt\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "While that may be a true statement in some cases, some proof from the consumer should be required as to why the debt isn't theirs.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For our customers, proof of residence at a different address from where our service was provided is usually sufficient for us to remove that customer from the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The consumers must understand that they have to work with the creditor or agency to correct whatever info lead to an \"incorrect link\" (common name, bad SSN, fraud...).", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The 3 items listed in CFPB summary is usually adequate.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 419, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Consumers should not be allowed to dispute a debt using identity theft as a reason without proof as well.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Otherwise some consumers will \"game\" the system and make false disputes.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 420, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I currently have an alias on my Credit report that I have NEVER gone by.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've disputed this serveral times ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I can't get this alias and the related debt off my report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_2"], "text": "As such I want federal laws that REQUIRE an agency to produce some paperwork ,legal document that proves a consumer used that alias on a credit application/paperwork.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "When disputed with a CRA they should be requesting this information from the agencies as well.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "CRA's should be the neutral parties and be the enforcing agencies on both sides.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5", "7"], "text": "CRA's should be mandated to report accurate information and be responsible to gather the accurate information.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "currently they are warehouses of bad information that err on the side of collectors.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Consumers do not have a reliable agency fighting for their rights.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "without enforcement Federal laws equate to a bunch of useless words on a paper.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 422, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_2"], "text": "The CFPB should ban workplace calls completely.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Consumers provided a home phone number when they take on the debt", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and that should be the number they call to collect it.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Communicating by registered/certified letter should also be the alternate method not workplace calls.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6", "7"], "text": "Second Massachusetts limiting the total number of calls is a fabulous idea.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We don't throw debtors in prison today", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "yet the ridiculous amount of abuse and scorn they must endure is totally unacceptable.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "CFPB desperately needs to clean up the debt collection industry.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 423, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "More information to the consumer with the initial notification would be more confusing and intimidating than it already is for them.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0", "2", "3"], "text": "Simplifying the initial notification while including information about how to contact someone if you do not recognized this obligation is the way to go.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Then the CFPB can design and require everyone to send a separate Summary of Consumer Rights to a consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It could also be available in the exact same form on the CFPB website and on informed professionals websites within the industry.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would maintain the consumer's right to ask for a cease communication,", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "but I would suggest that the CFPB would serve everyone better by including that the CFPB would suggest that the consumer may be better served by keeping this communication available except as a last resort.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This solution also bears the added advantage of making sure the public is aware of the assistance available through the CFPB.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 424, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "my in-laws had the same issue with BoA.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They paid their mortgate EARLY every month and still were reported as late every month.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "This is tragic", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and ruined their credit.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When these things happen it takes years for the credit to br repaired even though a collector reported the information falsely, incurracately, and repeatedly.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "BoA should be penalized HEAVILY for these infractions", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "otherwise they just ignore consumers.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 426, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As someone who regularly reviews credit reports,", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I am appalled by a practice I see regularly.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debt Collectors frequently resubmit the report of a debt as delinquent every month .", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This will have a highly adverse impact on the consumer's credit scores.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 427, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If federal rules can be ignored by local/municipal/state laws then the federal laws are irrelevant.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Consumer credit is recognized in all 50 states and internationally.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As such these laws should be enforced by each state and lower courts and states and such should not be able to make laws that ignore of superseed federal law.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 428, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Calling someone's work is clearly and without dispute intended to embarrass and annoy.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "It is never acceptable.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 429, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I don't know what constitutes as \"repeatedly or continuously,\"", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but more than once a day seems to qualify.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The system is designed to give collectors complete control, leaving the consumer with none.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Letters through the mail is a much more effective approach,", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but collectors refuse to honor that request.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 430, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "Unless the consumer chooses to communicate by phone, all correspondences from collectors should go through mail.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This allows the consumer to take time in considering what the collector is requesting.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It also avoids confusion for both parties.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The only reason this isn't the standard approach is because it limits how annoying and embarrassing collectors can be--plain and simple.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 433, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Once a debt has reached the end of its statue of limitations is should be removed from the consumer credit report.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, collectors use the law to refresh old debts so they effectively never leave a report.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a collector can't sue to retrieve the debt it has no business on a consumer report.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 434, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I had one debt collector in particular who called me a liar when I told him I wasn't the person he was looking for.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This was after he violated the FDCPA by calling me at 7:00 on a Saturday morning.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I called them back immediately and spoke with a supervisor who said she'd take me off their hit list.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I asked her if she got my number out of the phone book.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "She claimed that they had not.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A few months later, they started in on me again.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Obviously they still considered me a liar.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I sent them a cease-communication letter with a copy to my state's Attorney General, who has been wonderful in all this.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "At that point, I started sending out letters every time I received a collection call, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and, other than the one, none ever called me again.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "At one point I was receiving daily calls from one collector or another.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I can name names, and I have a thick file folder full of copies of my letters and responses to my Attorney General.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It has been a wild ride, and I sure hope it's over.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'm approaching the one-year anniversary of my most recent collection call.", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I just wish they wouldn't use the phone book as their primary research tool.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 435, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Legally, I don't believe that CFPB authority should stretch into this area ", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since the federal laws do not include such a limitation.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Notification to a consumer that a debt is beyond statute is problematic", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since that date is not permanent.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Partial payment on an account restarts the statute of limitations.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't believe that a rule issued by the CFPB can help here.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Education of consumers is the only pro-active method that I see as available here.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, this education should include notification to the legal profession that the CFPB will bring violations in this area to the attention of the Attorney General in their state.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 436, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Current debt substantiation requirements all suffer from the same significant shortcoming in that they fail to address the often symbiotic relationship between first-line creditors, collectors, reporting agencies, consumer data clearinghouses, buyers of bad debt, and others industry players.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Each has a vested profit motive in the \"validation\" of debt.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Without appropriate disincentive--i.e., enforcement of rules and stiff penalties for non-compliance--corners are cut and quid pro quo-type behaviors begin to surface.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Consumers hold few cards and have to play against a stacked deck.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The validation process should involve more than merely inquiring with the creditor about the validity of the debt or the identity of the debtor, and failure to observe all the necessary steps--in the sunshine, no less--should have severe consequences.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The best deterrent would be putting the power back in the hands of the (truly-wronged) consumer through the inclusion of \"private attorney general\" style enforcement mechanism.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Awarding attorneys' fees and damages, with the ability to elect either actual or meaningful statutory damages (similar to the scheme introduced by Congress into the copyright statutes), would create serious disincentives for anyone involved in unscrupulous validation practices.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 439, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "This is a problem that needs to be corrected.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In this case, the line of credit is negatively affecting your credit a multiple of times even though it is one line.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 442, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "We live in the Information Age.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All the information this individual is requesting is readily available with a few keystrokes.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
