{"commentID": 448, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I don't believe in abusive behavior ", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "(i.e. the behavior spelled out in the FDCPA),", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but what this individual is saying that she owes a debt that she is not paying.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Instead, she wants to be the offensive party and paint the collector into a corner using a recording device.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 450, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Can there be a national repository to report abusive phone calls from debt collectors that masked (fake and \"spoof\") their caller ID?", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I got a brand new phone number a few years ago ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "and it obviously previously belonged to someone who is delinquent on their bills ", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I get calls everyday from debt collectors looking for the person who had my phone number before me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "No matter how many times I tell them they have the wrong number, they don't care and they just keep calling and they call from spoofed phone numbers.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And this is my cell phone, which is against the law for debt collectors to call.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The same debt collectors call with faked caller IDs.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Here are just some of the phone numbers these debt collectors use: 808-792-8186 462643 858-568-7632 805-322-4584 706-913-1192 808-348-0083 858-345-4076 858-312-7724 908-505-9008 800-633-2677 252-808-7969 571-522-0386 407-712-3093 213-816-2972 804-721-3193 678-781-4530 427307 858-240-4079", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 451, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Compliance 2013 demonstrates the type of arrogance that I have been addressing in my prior comments.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The belief that a default is a default by courts along with the practice of REWARDING Strategic Defaulters while sentencing INVOLUNTARY DEFAULTERS to never ending escalating debt because of the ongoing interest rate charges needs to be addressed.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have been researching consumer debt for the past few years ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": ["5"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and Consumer Debt is ON THE RISE GLOBALLY,", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and that is not a good thing.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/business/too-much-debt-in-the-developed-world-chilton-230947131.html\">Canadian finance expert warns about rising consumer debt.</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I can replace Canada in the title with England, Australia, South Africa, China, Russia, Ireland and on and on and on.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The consumer debt escalation is being caused by a ridiculously low 2% monthly minimum payment, the gateway drug to higher and higher debt, and because consumers who have legitimate life Changing events that cause them to default cannot plead INVOLUNTARY DEFAULT in court.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We let criminals plead involuntary to many crimes, but not law abiding citizens when it comes to their credit cards and student loans!", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 452, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have worked in collections for 13 years with mostly first parties.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All of these institutions have complied with the FDCPA and seek to service their lost members to the best of their abilities.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 456, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, one of the biggest scams that consumers get put through is the collection agency saying discussions about the debt have to be made with the parent company,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the parent company saying they cannot talk about the debt because it has been assigned to a debt collection agency,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Please FIX THIS.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
