{"commentID": 476, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Consumers need to be pro-active in everything they do.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "If an individual had the capability to take on a debt then they should have the capability to resolve the debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Every credit union I know goes the extra mile to help their members achieve financial success.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 477, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If a consumer states that he disputes the debt, the debt collector should immediately cease ALL collection activity until the debt is validated.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And, by validation, it needs to be more than \"the name and social security information matches the creditor's records.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The validation process should include a clear and complete copy of ALL DOCUMENTS that create the alleged obligation.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If none is available, then the debt should be cancelled.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 479, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As a bankruptcy lawyer, I frequently deal with clients or are harassed by debt collectors calling family or neighbors.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "the collectors will claim they are acquiring location information, but this is frequently the case where the consumer has been at the same location for years.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "I hope the rules will narrow the \"location information\" exception ", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so that it can only be used where there is really doubt about the consumer's location.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 480, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Paying a debt in full will always improve a credit score unless the debt is over 7 years old.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If that is the case, I'm sure you can make a request to the financial institution to not report the payment.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 481, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "It seems that just about anyone can create a debt collection company", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and if the owners and/or employees have unscrupulous desires, then it seems that privacy is a big concern.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Plus, if anyone can create/own debt collection companies, then it doesn't seem to surprise me why so many debt collecting companies break the laws.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There should be tighter laws on the formation of debt collection companies and the employees that they can hire.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
