{"commentID": 485, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_2"], "text": "The problem is that cell phone customers have to pay for the minutes that are used.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have pre paid cell service ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and debt collectors are calling me all the time looking for someone else who I do not know.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "This is the problem.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Harassment to the cell phone owner and harassment that the cell phone owner must pay for.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "this is why it will always remain illegal for debt collectors to call cell phones.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 486, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2", "3_4"], "text": "No phone calls at work.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I agree!", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Work is for work, not personal debt business.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I personally don't get calls at work,", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I can see how embarrassing it would be and how quickly the company would probably fire.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "3_4"], "text": "No work phone calls period, should be the law.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 487, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If a collector is calling from a different number than the one they are displaying on Called ID, that should be not allowed.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Does not allow the consumer to block those calls since the number displayed is not the one actually calling.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 488, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Many states have a judgement law where a consumer with over a certain amount of judgements may be terminated from employment.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Having a collector call at work just seems to be another way to break down a consumer and put them at a disadvantage.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A friend has mentioned to me receiving collection calls at work for one of his employees where the collector identified himself as \"Officer\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My friend told the collector never to call again and that it's illegal to impersonate law enforcement.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Too many other stories that went to court for FDCPA violations of collector harassment at work even when the employer has told the collector not to call there again.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 489, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Creditors generally do not send accounts to collection until after they have sent multiple notices.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Requiring a specific notice will expose small creditors to liability beyond any benefit to consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 491, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "A standard first letter would be an excellent idea - especially if states would agree on the content.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Consumers could recognize the format and know where to look for the information they need.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4"], "text": "Consumer testing would be a very good idea.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I believe that industry members would favor this to reduce litigation over technical violations.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Taxpayers would benefit by reduced federal court expenses.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 492, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I was following the advice of our bankruptcy attorney.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was allowed to tell creditors only a limited amount of information.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I could confirm- my identify, that yes I owed the debt, and third that I was not able to start repaying my debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "No I was not allowed to tell the debt collectors that we would be filing bankruptcy.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It took almost six months to complete tasks prior to notifying creditors about the bankruptcy.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "During that time I was subjected to verbal abuse, threats, illegal intimidation tactics, and outright lies.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The tape recorder completely stopped the bad behavior.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's amazing what debt collectors will say and do when they call debtors.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's a totally different story what they want recorded.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The best money you will ever spend is a cheap $20-25 telephone tape recorder.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 493, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I knew a man who was sued by a debt collector and he was not served.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "\"Someone\" was served, but not at his address and he was denied due process.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He learned of the suit when it was a judgment on his credit report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He attempted to have the judgment overturned for lack of due process and the judge would not grant it.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Unfortunate, but yes they are allowed to deny due process and get away with it.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
