{"commentID": 502, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I don't think that we are discussing how to block a collector from calling you.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "You shouldn't have to feel that you have to \" block \" a call .", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You should just answer and ask them not to call you.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 503, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Creditors should be entitled to require consumers to provide them with a contact address and phone number and to provide updates while debts are outstanding.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If consumers do not do so, it should be fair for creditors (and collectors) to skip-trace or to reach them at other numbers.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Collectors should not be allowed to make calls to work until they have made multiple attempts to contact a consumer at home.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 505, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I don't think limiting the time to call a person at work is an option.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Everyone works at different times.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some people moves, change cell phone numbers , ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "so call them at work is sometimes the only option.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's hard to know what place \"prefers\" no personal calls , ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and a list could be an option, ", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but most people work for smaller company's ", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "and the lists will cater to the large company's.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most people have information about where they work somewhere on the web.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't see a problem if a debt collector calls a customer at work if they don't know prior of any inconvenience.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 506, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Let's start by assuming the creditor provided something for which a consumer agreed to pay.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Creditors should be entitled to get a phone number and address at which the creditor can reach the consumer and to get updates as long as a debt is outstanding.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a consumer chooses to use only a cell phone, the creditor and collector should be able to contact him at that number.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 512, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "To start e-oscar should take internet complaints the same a shad written letters.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They do not do that.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They take internet disputes differently then they do hand written letter.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is in regards to disputed debts and it is important that the credit bureaus be consistent about the dispute process and the statues of limitations based on state laws.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They should also have limits on how many collection agencies they sell the account of too including their shady practice of selling accounts of to collection agencies in different states.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Their should be a cap on debts owed and the power that the agencies have on consumers.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think ultimatel it is about the collection agencies not abusing the consumer and helping consumers find ways to keep their accounts out default.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A good start to offer consumers to get their accounts out of default would be based on charging consumers a small percentage of % coupled with a promissory note with a date to begin making payments to the debt collector.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They abuse the consumers ", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they should stop it.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Overall, the communication process between consumers and debt collectors is flawed with mis communications and a lack of options to pay back what they owe.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 513, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have no personal experiences with debt to speak of, only my experiences working with victims of identity theft who have fraudulent debts; which is a horse of a different color.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Consumers are not educated about how debt collection and revival works.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The issue in the end isn't the mechanics, or if they can request the debt not be reported.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "The issue is that, the way things stand now, it is not clear how repaying a debt will improve their score.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is not clear that they can ask for the collector not to report the debt payment if the debt is older than seven years.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Consumers are confused and have these inaccurate perceptions because things are not clear.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Again, it is the perception which concerns me - it would benefit both creditors and consumers if it was plain and clear, in language the average consumer could understand, that paying off a debt is a good thing.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 514, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Please go hard after the service industry.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They have done a lot to foul up the debt collection process by having their service people FALSE SERVE and FALSE SUBSERVE prospective debt collection alleged defaulters.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": ["2_6"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's happened to me twice, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "the first time the process server simply guessed by using the most generic age size, weight and assign a made up name!", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The second time the servicer simply called the sub server \"Jane Doe\" and once again made up the most generic cut across as many age, height and race descriptions they could come up with, which meant they could not be more far off.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Then when I went to court I just happened to hear another defendant make the claim to the judge that they were never served, that the paper work was left outside the door.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Besides the service company lying in court documents about serving someone that was not actually served, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "which in and of itself should be enough to give the judge some type of latitude to do something to protect the defendants, ", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "when a debt collector knows they can get a false service, they have MUCH LESS MOTIVATION to negotiate with the defendant. ", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Judges don't seem to get this aspect of false service.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I know what I know ", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I will state unequivocally anywhere that I have twice been false served/subserved.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
