{"commentID": 520, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "After having a perfect payment history for 15 years, I had to across the board default on six accounts ", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I became an unpaid caregiver for my parents.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, before I ever defaulted, I contacted each account and explained what was going on.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would also like to note that five of the six accounts were still being paid down until I ran out of savings.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I discovered the credit card companies HAVE NO INTAKE for potential defaulters.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "I consider a potential default division a cost of doing business that credit card companies have eschewed ", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they have co-opted the courts to do all the work for them for a very nominal fee.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My goal was simple, keep making monthly miniscule autopay payments on all six accounts in exchange for no harrassing phone calls so that I could concentrate on CareGiving AND modifying my self employment so that I could make something every month.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Everyone refused, and the harrassing and MORE IMPORTANTLY REPETITIVE phone calls started.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I ended up having to convert my land lines to 6 dollar a month cell phones, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "and then I rarely used them ", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I could not afford the 20 cents a minute cost.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In essence the credit card companies and debt collectors destroyed the best way I had to regenerate earnings while still being an unpaid CareGiver.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And as Marlene so eloquently pointed out, an additional roadblock is the debt collectors ABSOLUTE REFUSAL to put any verbal agreement reached in writing!", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 521, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "That's business.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debt collectors--small, medium, and large--know the cost of doing business.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And if they don't know, then they need to find a new \"career.\"", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 522, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "I don't think that the partial SSN should be included.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "That raises too many privacy concerns.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "And I'm sure that one day a debt collection company will have a \"system malfunction\" and will \"accidentally\" send the full SSN.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Too many consumers have similar names in the same city.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Lastly, many different companies classify a partial SSN as the first 5 digits whereas other stick to the traditional last 4 digits.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a mail thief is lurking, then he might have access to a consumers full SSN.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 523, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Once I tell a debt collector I am a unpaid CareGiver", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "and that is why I had to stop making payments,", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In essence they were telling me to let my parents die if necessary and go get a job.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was repeatedly baited with the comment, \"So you are a \"refuse to pay\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I found this type of conduct outside the lines of common decency.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had a business,", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had to give up the business to become an unpaid CareGiver.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I had been shown at the time I apparently agreed to the credit card agreement that there truly were no ifs ands or buts in regards to monthly payments forgiveness on an \"unsecured\" debt, I would have come up with a different business model that did not require credit card debt.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Credit card companies get to present themselves as pro family in their advertising when the exact opposite is true in times of crisis.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Ask people who had a dramatic life changing incident occur how the credit card companies treated them.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Ask the Colorado flood victims, or the Hurricane Sandy Victims, or the person who was the victim of a hit and run how the credit card companies treated them.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These are the same credit card companies that lobbied the comptroller of the currency in 2002 to keep their monopoly on credit card debt suspension insurance and the outrageous overpriced premiums they were charging their customers.", "type": "fact", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One of the best ways consumers had to be responsible regarding their credit card debts was having AFFORDABLE credit card debt suspension insurance.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This option was stolen from consumers in 2002 when the comptroller of the currency allowed credit card companies to over charge by 1000% to 2000% on monthly credit card debt suspension insurance premiums.", "type": "fact", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I created a time line document that shows how the financial elite stole fairness from the people in regards to credit card products.", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": ["15"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://debtsuspensionrights.blogspot.com/2013/05/my-consumer-financial-protection-bureau.html\">My appearance in front of the CFPB in May of 2013 and the research I shared with them.</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 15, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 524, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I think that both an English and Spanish letter should be sent.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This already happens with most legal and other important things (like voting and letters from school) in my State.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But this should be a fed requirement to always include Spanish.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 525, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "AT & T is notorious for setting up new accounts that don't have an official phone number attached.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": ["1_7"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was put in the situation of having an 800 number that AT & T customer service reps could not find in their system.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had no way to cancel it!", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Eventually the false 100 dollar debt went to a debt collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I respectfully explained that the debt was not valid, in a letter.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A few months later I got a letter from a different debt collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Again I wrote a letter.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A few months later another letter over the same faux debt from a third debt collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 526, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I dont understand why bill collectors are so stuck in ancient times.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I get so many calls and its annoying.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4"], "text": "I would much rather get a text or email.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The phone ringing can be annoying and a text is more subtle.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It also doesnt require me to hear a long dragging voicemail.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4"], "text": "I would rather get a text saying who they are and what they want.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I dont respond soon then call me.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
