{"commentID": 572, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The first entity I will probably take to small claims court and possibly file a complaint with Kamala Harris.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The second incident I started sending faxes messages in big bold letters to the same fax where my prior faxes had been lost, asking other workers to look to see if they had taken the papers by accident.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also faxed overnight warning those who might have access to that room that taking fax documents could lead to their arrest.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I did this for several days in a row.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It was the only way I could think of to apply a much needed enema to those who have established a routine and can't shake free from it.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Of course this assumes that they care.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 573, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "That is not going to work.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The burden of proof in the American Justice System is bore by the one who is making the accusations.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some debtors are going to lie and say that a debt is not theirs when it actually is,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but that is the nature of the beast with debt collections.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Innocent until proven guilty is the rules of the game.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Otherwise I, as a debt collector, can accuse anyone of anything owning any amount and extort money from innocent people.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debt collection is about collecting debt, not about making accusations and extortions.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 574, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I like the Summary of Rights idea.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "3", "4"], "text": "I think that a validation letter and even an initial communication letter should included of Summary of Rights for State Laws and Fed Laws.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4"], "text": "This would help two fold: both the debtors/consumers and the debt collecting companies.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debtor/consumers would know their rights ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the collectors would then also know the particular rights for the states that they are collecting in.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "This shouldn't be burdensome at all ", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since the CRA already include Summary of Rights as do employers who check credit.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 575, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "There should never be a fee for payment.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In fact, in about 1/3 of the states have state laws that prohibit any fees/surcharges for payment by credit/debit cards (unless it is a government agency).", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "if a debt collector accepts credit/debit cards for payment, there should not be any fees for payment processing.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Nor should there be any fees for payment processing for any other payment method for that matter.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "debt collection companies should also be able to accept prepaid debit cards for payment as a means of privacy and security for the debtors, rather than access to a bank account.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 576, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "When two parties engage in a lawsuit, each side presents the evidence they have supporting their assertions.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As a collector, I provide proof of the debt", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debtor is also expected to present some proof that the debt is not theirs.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, the assumption is innocent until proven guilty but you have to provide evidence to support your claim of innocence.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I offer a signed document that says you agreed to the purchase and documentation that supports that you did not pay, I have fulfilled my side of the burden of proof.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debtor also bears a burden of proof in our system.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That's what the judge is for - to hear both sides, weigh the evidence, and make a fair decision based on the evidence and arguments presented.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 577, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Being in a court of law and talking to a debt collector on the phone that requires proof that the debt in question is not a valid debt, are two different things.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If your intent is to sue, then sue.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But requiring proof from anyone you call up and demand that they prove to you (and not a judge) that the debt is not theirs is extortion.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 578, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "If there already isn't a law or rule at the fed level for when what happens to time barred debts when a debtor leaves the purview of one states SOL and now resides in another states SOL, there needs to be.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It should be clear that if a debtor changes states, which SOL should come into play.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 579, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I think there should be a fed law that should clearly state that any partial payment might revive the SOL for suit.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "How consumers get a phone call/letter telling them they have a debt and they just blindly pay it or make partial payments in order to just stop getting the phone calls? Lots.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And the debt might not even be theirs, ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they pay it anyways thinking that they might have a old debt that they forgot to take care of.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The problem with that is, that the debt then is revived, the debt collector sues, and the judge tells the debtor \"well, if this wasn't your debt then why did you agree to make partial payments?\"", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Then the judge will make favor in the debt collector for a revived debt that the debtor was not even responsible for in the first place.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This scenario happens every day of the week.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And the consumer had thought they were doing the right thing, but the debt collector is actually taking advantage.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 581, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Old debt that is beyond the statue of limitation should indicate the original creditor in the initial contact letter.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think the collector does not know this information or they deliberately refuse to disclose it because they know that the debt has run it course through the CRA's for seven years.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So why is it that a collector can rename themselves as the merchant because they bought an old debt and proceed to collect and to report it to the CRA's.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once your credit has taken a hit the debt collector should not be able to continually harass you for the rest of your existence.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Portfolio Recovery is the culprit ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they should not be able to look at your credit report and send letters to collect as if you entered into a legal and binding contract with them.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Why should you reactivate an old debt that is over 16 years old.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Everyone know and remember the hard patches in their lives, such as medical issues, divorces, death etc.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once the fear of being sued is removed, the chances of a collector to collect is very minute.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "So it becomes time consuming and it cost money to send a certified letter to ask them to validate an alleged debt.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the collector can not validate a debt then they should not continually sell and resell such debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "And there is a problem with the CRA's ", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because it seems to me they are in cahoots with each other.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If there si not any active business with a particular account on a credit report, then the CRA's should make the collector prove that a debt is valid.", "type": "policy", "id": 13, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 582, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Actually there should always be more communication about specific things, rather than less.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "More communication from the Original Creditors that an account will be turned over to a collector and when.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "And when a debt collector then turns it over or sells to someone else there should be more communication about who.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Just like when mortgages are sold to other servicers, the borrowers get letters informing them of who now owns their mortgage and who now to send payment to.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This should be standard practice for debt collectors.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "Explaining to the debtor that they have turned the account to someone else and that all payment and communication should now be directed to the new guy (even if no payments were sent to the first debt collector.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Because there are debtors who can't make payment now but can later, and if they start sending payment to an old debt collector via an old letter they got in the mail, then debtors attempts to actually resolve the debt go by the wayside.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "More communication about who/what/where/how is necessary.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 584, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I was sent to collection.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Collector informed me that it was for and overdue insurance payment.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Having everything on Auto-Pay, I overlooked the notice they mailed to me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One call to my agent and the problem was resolved.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'm glad they called and gave me the opportunity to get to root of problem before it jeopardized my good credit rating!", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I \"know\" the majority of CFPB complaints come from people who simply don't want to pay their bill.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "I know this ", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I have worked for a collection agency for the last twenty years, privy to all complaints we receive and very, very few have any merit.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'm by no means stating that some people don't have legitimate complaints.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What I am saying is if we compare the number of complaints to the number of accounts being pursued by all collection agencies the percentage of complaints would be a mere fraction of one percent.", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So, how much more regulation is necessary to address such a tiny percentage?", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 586, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I once had a debt collector send collection letters to my work address.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They had my home address.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "I think this should also be prohibited.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Who gets personal mail sent to them at work?", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 587, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I keep getting collection calls for some unkown person on my cell phone at least 4 times a day.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have repeatedly told them that this is not that person's number.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I recently got a new number ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it is so aggravating to monitor your calls because of someone else", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 588, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The name of the agency is the CONSUMER Financial Protection Bureau not the Collector Financial Protection Bureau.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The industry have their lobbyists ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "and consumers have the CFPB.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "The goal is to protect consumers from illegal practices by certain industries ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and that sometimes means more regulations.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 591, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "The enforcement mechanism of the FDCPA is laughable from the point of view of the debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For example, a debt collector said that since they are out of the country they are not required to adhere to the FDCPA.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Luckily, I knew better, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but most folk don't.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The CFPB's voluntary reporting combined with proxy enforcement power may curb the industry's activities, and may be cheaper and faster than class action lawsuits.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 592, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "A neighbor who has since moved away has had her debts turned over to collection agencies.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We receive repeated calls trying to get contact information, even though we request to be taken off their list.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "An unfortunate situation but we don't know the whereabouts of the individual and shouldn't be subjected to this sort of harassment.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 594, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I am a clerk at a local city court.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I am the civil clerk ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I feel that debtors are treated extremely unfairly by debt collection laws.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The Court cannot give legal advice", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "so it is saddening to have to try and explain and console upset litigants who have no idea what they are in for.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think there should be more avenues for pro se litigants who cannot afford to retain a private attorney ", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "(which is 95 % of the litigants in my city).", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I can say that most people do not answer summonses because they either were not properly served or they just straight up do not care, or most often, do not understand the legalese.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "BUT, I do have to say that I get many litigants who call and ask what they do now that they are served.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "On the occasions that people do file answers, most of them are in letter form, not a \"legal\" verified answer.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most debt collection attorneys jump right on that and request a summary judgment.", "type": "fact", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Our Court does not turn away letters, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and we send a copy to the attorney and set the matter up for a pre trial conference with a judge or court attorney to help try to get both parties together to come to some sort of resolution.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The Court does have to adhere to a scheduling policy for these conferences, ", "type": "fact", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but we are very flexible ", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "if a defendant has a scheduling conflict we try to accommodate them as best we can.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When summonses are filed with the court, half of them have tons of information about the debt, others only have the amount due!", "type": "fact", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I find that sometimes it's hard for litigants to obtain further proving documents from attorneys, even with the court telling them they have to.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When entering default judgments, I take my time and examine the whole file, like comparing the contents of the summons/complaint and the default judgment submitted, re-checking the affidavit of service of the summons (to make sure the defendant had the legal time to answer the summons), and ensuring that attached to the default judgment is the proper documentation as to purchasing the debt, a non-military affidavit, etc.", "type": "testimony", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also make sure that they are being charged the proper interest rate and court costs.", "type": "testimony", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The bottom line is that the debtors still do not have enough and/or sufficient laws to protect them, and the Court's hands are tied based on these laws,", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["20"], "text": "even if they wanted to help, they couldn't.", "type": "value", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I know the Court is to remain impartial, but in a small city, everybody knows everybody and sometimes it's hard to see these practices occurring.", "type": "value", "id": 22, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 595, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "To the first question, due diligence is a must.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Even if collectors are allowed to continue litigation (which I do not see going away,) there must be a penalty for the collector if false claim is made.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "If a collector starts litigation and it is found to be against the wrong person, compensation and additional penalty should be paid by the entity initiating the litigation in the form of a reasonable fee to the victim and an additional (and substantial) fee to the governing authority to help cover oversight expenses.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To the second question, I believe an overwhelmingly large portion of consumer debt can be repaid.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, there are always going to be exceptions to this.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In cases where debt can not be collected for whatever reason, it should be written off as truly not collectable and no not be allow to be sold again as debt to be collected.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Fine tuning and definitions of \"Not Collectable\" will have to be worked out by the appropriate oversight bureau or agency.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To the third question, both party's must be measured.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are currently established credit reporting agencies to monitor the consumer side of this issue and an additional, numerical evaluation score can be added to the consumer's already established credit report.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "That would be a starting point that can be expanded on as the system is fine tuned.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The collector, on the other hand, would require a new measuring system that would not only score the company as a whole, but the individuals taking part in any debt resolution activities.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For successful examples of such a system I would direct you to the Department of Transportation, Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration and their Compliance-Safety-Accountability system.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Admittedly, their system is much more complex and dives much deeper than would be required for the debt industry.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, their point system is valid and flexible for future change.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It would also allow for measurement of the initial creditor.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Such measurement would give the government and investors a better idea of a given business' risk level.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Add to this mix, the recommendations from Mr. Bartmann and you have a system whereby collectors and financial institutions will better regulate themselves to achieve an ethical and responsible outcome and not hide behind the \"what I did was legal\" defense.", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It would be a Win-Win for both sides and bring many consumers out of the debt death spiral.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["19"], "text": "Lastly, the federal government could implement this system with a minimal impact on state autonomy.", "type": "value", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It would reduce the number of litigation in state and local courts, thereby motivating the states to take part.", "type": "value", "id": 19, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 596, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I contacted the debt collection company and tried to make arrangements for payment of debt,", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "the reason I could not pay my bills is my husband was laid off work and he had started a new job.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I wanted to make payments of $100. a month, debt collectors said NO, so I said the most I could afford was $200 a month the said NO they wanted $1,000. a month.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Now we have 4 children, a mortgage and utility payment, debt collection said $500 a month my husband brought home after taxes $1,100 twice a month.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My mortgage is $1,300 per month not including utilizes so I told debt company that I couldn't pay.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I always thought something was better than nothing and that a debt company would try to work with you.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I learned that they won't work with you.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 597, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have received calls from debt collectors at 9:30 pm,", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I consider this rude.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have also had robocalls early in the morning that woke me up.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I am 69 yrs old, and retired, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I sleep late.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My health is not good at the moment, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "so sometimes I have had a bad night", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "5"], "text": "please, please don't wake me up with a robocall.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 598, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I do NOT answer any calls that have \"unknown caller\" or \"unknown\" in the ID.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If you can't show your name in the ID line, then something is not right with your company, or you have something to hide.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Remember, YOU are calling ME, ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "so in that sense, phone calls are an invasion of my privacy.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't have any obligation to answer any calls that I don't want to.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "There should be a regulation that requires debt collection agencies to identify themselves when making phone calls.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 599, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I absolutely hate robocalls, especially those that repeat constantly and relentlessly.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are some people who shirk their responsibilities,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "but there are also those who simply do not have money to pay out a debt.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "People lose their jobs, get laid off, get sick and can't work, retire and try to make it from one month to the next on miniscule retirement benefits.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "There should be a regulation against robocalls, period.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "They should not be allowed.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They are not necessary and only serve to harass people.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "It's a bullying tactic, in my opinion.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 600, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I am on a Senior plan for my mobile phone ", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "and I get charged for each text that comes in or goes out.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I am able to make/receive texts, but have to pay for each one ...", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "so it is not fair to make me pay extra on top of what I already owe.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "I am against using cell phones for business advertisements or debt collecting texts or calls.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 601, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I agree with Bonzarel.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "The obvious solution is to ban debt collection calls to cell phones, period.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Not everybody has the same options on their mobile plans, ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and some have strict time/call/texting limits and/or restrictions.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 602, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "They could set transparent, limited rate increases which debt collectors could charge for each mode of communication that is eliminated.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A rule setting that kind of rate increase would add some necessary transparency to the question of whether these kinds of communications are even worthwhile for the agency.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 604, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I would like to see the time frame for validation change.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I, as a consumer, have 30 days from the date of the letter to dispute the debt,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "however, the collection agency can take as long as they want, even years, to get back to the consumer.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This practice is not only bad ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but some charge interest on the debt, even though they don't call it that (fee's\"), all the time they are 'looking into it\".", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4"], "text": "If I have 30 day's they should have the same time frame to get back to me, period.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 605, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Collection Agency's' should be REQUIRED by law to show their phone number when calling a debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most if not all come up \"unknown\".", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they are a legitimate company then they should have no problem showing their number.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I call them, and my number is blocked, I can't get thru until I unblock my number.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "3"], "text": "If they truly are legitimate, they should want to do things fair and above board.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 608, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Agreed.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "And it should be their real phone number.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So that when you miss their phone call and try to call them back, it should go to the real company.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And not say something like \"the call can not be completed as dialed.\"", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I mean, what is the point in that.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some debtors can't get to their phone before it goes to the answering machine ", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and if the collectors don't leave a message, the debtor will try to call back.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But then the call can't be completed when you try to call back.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "So, really what was the point of the call.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many debtors would just assume it was a scam call.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Increasing Right Party Contacts should be the goal.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And that goal can only be reached if the real phone number is showing up on calller id.", "type": "fact", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 609, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "There's no need to be rude about it.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are some debt collection practices that should obviously be illegal.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Other things that people are discussing here are obviously matters of convenience.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To the extent that preferences are widely shared and outright prohibition wouldn't increase lending costs across the board beyond a marginal amount, outright prohibition makes sense.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But if someone wants the ability to stop someone from conducting any and all robocalls from all phones, and robocalls help creditors recoup their loans, then the creditor should be able to charge a regulated fee for that convenience.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'm not saying that the debt collection agency itself would charge the fee", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Just that a consent-based approach is another option.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 610, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Any collector who uses a robocall, without first having a live person call to verify that the phone number is correct, is lazy and irresponsible.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "Aside from being a major nuisance, robocalls to a third party are always an improper disclosure ", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because prerecorded calls are required to include the name of the company at the start of the message (per the TCPA).", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've received dozens and dozens of calls like this, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and now I know which of my neighbors are alleged to owe money.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "I say \"alleged\", ", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because the companies making these calls are usually the same scofflaws who have been sued repeatedly for trying to collect nonexistent debts.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Outlawing robocalls, particularly robocalls to third parties, would hurt the bad actors without having much impact on legitimate collectors.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I wouldn't have a problem with live callers using autodialers, except that the technology used by some collection agencies is so far behind the times.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Telemarketers are able to stay within the required 3% abandonment rate,", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "yet my experience is that the drop rate on live calls from collectors ranges from 50% to 100%.", "type": "fact", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, I had one company hang up immediately every single time one of their agents called me. ", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'm not sure how this is profitable.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "Extending the FTC's 3% rule to debt collection calls would address this issue.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 611, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If I am paying for the minutes on my phone, which I do, then I should be able to chose who's call I do and do not want to answer.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When it comes up 'unknown\", how do I know it's a Collection Agency, a telemarketer trying to sell me vacation homes, cruse lines trying to sell me a cruse, someone wanting to offer me a better mortgage rate, ect...", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Every call I answer deducts time from my minutes ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and that is NOT fair to me.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I now block ALL \"unknown, withheld & private\" calls.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they truly are legidimate and want to talk to me, press 1 to unblock, just like I have to.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 612, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "A collector's toll-free number is the ideal number to display on Caller ID,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since it allows the call to be returned from anywhere without incurring long-distance charges.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It also lets the recipient know right away that it is not a personal call and is probably not from a local company.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'd much rather see an 800 number than a spoofed local number for a company that is really 1000 miles away (or in India).", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This spoofing is clearly a false and deceptive practice that is barred by the FDCPA, ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but still it occasionally happens.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 614, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I don't like #2", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because if they were to start telling consumers to a to a certain website, that opens the door for spammers/hackers to increase virus infections by simply doing the same thing.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Just calling every phone number in the phone book and telling the consumer navigate to a certain website and then infect their computer.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 615, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Require debt collectors to send validation notices via certified mail.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There must be some way to prove the debt validation notice was at least sent, if not received.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have had the experience of a debt collector not sending me a validation notice.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I made a complaint to the Illinois Department of Professional Regulations, the debt collector did not have to prove that they sent the validation notice.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All the debt collector had to do was claim that they had records of sending the validation notice in their computer system.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Since I did not receive the validation notice, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "I did not know what my rights were.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 621, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "They could at least start with address and area code of debtor\"s phone number.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And I would say that the reach would be at least as far as the local commuting area.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So for a city like Boston, there's Boston, Chelsea, and the other surrounding areas.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Now, if a debtor from NY traveled to Boston for the marathon, for example, that would be much harder for a collector to have a reasonable expectation of a debtor\"s whereabouts.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But once a debtor has identified his/herself within the reach of the commuting area of the place of emergency, then perhaps the exemption period should kick in.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In a place like Newtown, or Colorado, if a collector has a reasonable belief that a debtor may have been an employee of the school or movie theater (if they can't identify the debtor being in the local commuting area by address/phone number), then they should also stop collection for the exemption period.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So, place of employment, address, phone number, and debtors self-identifying their whereabouts, could be ways that debt collectors could/should have reason to believe the location of a debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 622, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2", "4"], "text": "It would be a good idea to create a national database of collectors and assign them an ID number just like the IRS.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0", "2", "4"], "text": "Require them to state their name and ID number just like IRS employees do.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This would allow debtors to easily identify an abusive collector or just call a debt collection agency and ask to speak to a specific employee.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they call and leave a voicemail they are required to state their ID number somewhere in the recording.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It would be good for both debtors and collectors.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 623, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "This is a collectors favorite.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They call over and over to harass debtors ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "and they should be limited to one call per day with a required voicemail stating their purpose.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 626, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Creditors should only be allowed to call between the hours of 9am until 7pm local time unless they have written consent (maybe even a web form) that gives them a minimum 3 hour window in which to call.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Additionally, they are limited to 3 phone calls a day maximum.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 627, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["3", "8_9"], "text": "I think limitation is good as not to harass.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think it has been generally defined as 3-4 days per day, ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "though I think that is still excessive, ", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "and any collector who follows that is clearly trying to harass.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Who else would someone call 3-4 times in a day?", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "But, with the example of 1 call per day, I would think that there would also need to be another limitation such as 1 call per day or no more than 4 calls in a week.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Otherwise, a collector could call 1 time a day, 7 times a week, 30 times in a month, etc.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And personally, in my personal phone calls and in my business phone calls, it can take me more than a day or two to return a message.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Customarily, in personal phone calls and business phone calls, if a message is left, the caller will leave a message and wait a couple of days before calling back if the person has yet to return the phone call.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is the way normal phone etiquette works--both in personal phone calls and in business calls.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So, why should debt collections be different,", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "why should they break the norms.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 628, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Creditors should only be allowed to call between the hours of 9am until 7pm local time unless they have written consent (maybe even a web form) that gives them a minimum 3 hour window in which to call.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Additionally, they are limited to 3 phone calls a day maximum.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they leave a message they should be required to leave the name of the company, the name of the representative, the number to call, and a reference number.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5_12"], "text": "In regards to debt sales, the entity selling the debt should give 90 days notice of the intent to sell giving the consumer notification of the intent to sell and maybe even offer a settlement amount.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5_12"], "text": "The entity purchasing the debt must honor any and all terms of the debt they are purchasing (i.e. payment plans, deferment/forbearance, etc.).", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My brother has several private student loans.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "About a year ago we started getting phone calls from Discover in regards to student loans and we all assumed that it was a sales call because no one living at my address had student loans with them.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Eventually we managed to be home when they called ", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and we discovered that two of my brother's loans were sold to Discover ", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and he was never notified.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So all this time thinking it was a sales call, because Discover only gave a 1-800 number to call about student loans and not even the name of the person they were trying to reach, his loans were actually in default ", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because Discover cancelled the forbearance he had upon purchase.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When he attempted to put them back into forbearance, Discover told him they \"didn't have a system for that yet\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 631, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The courts should also mandate that if a debtor has reached out to the creditor in an attempt to negotiate the creditor must continue to try to reach a settlement rather than seeking judgment against the debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "Also, the collection agency should not be able to add interest on top of debt that seek judgment for if the debtor agrees to pay ", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since they will make a profit over what they paid the original creditor.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Basically these so called \"attorneys\" (just another form of ambulance chaser in my book) are just forcing bankruptcies upon people who would be willing to work a deal ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and then they and the courts and the government are whining about what the bankruptcies do to the economy and the bottom line.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Last time I checked even in a court of law you can't play both sides.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 633, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "A lot of excellent points made by MLegz13.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My elderly parents needed help with day to day activities even if they were too proud to say anything.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I stopped my award winning video business to be their CareGiver.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once the savings ran out, I had to default after 15 years of having a perfect credit card payment history.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debt collectors were constantly accusing me of being a \"refuse to pay\" even though I said I acknowledge the debt but had no income at the moment.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "It is this type of scenario that requires debts be frozen where they were at the time of default and in exchange the debtor agrees to pay off the debt, even if the initial monthly payments are just for a couple of dollars.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What this does is free the debtor's phone lines so they can completely focus on moving forward rather than engage in pointless rat a tat with repetitive debt collection callers.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "It's why I started the Debt Neutrality Petition as well.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If you click on the link PLEASE read the comments left by some of the 500 plus people who have signed the petition.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Even a debt collector signed the petition, their comment speaks volumes of truth, as did all the others as well.", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.change.org/petitions/congress-create-debt-neutrality-rights-for-paying-down-credit-cards-student-loans\">Debt Neutrality Petition.</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 635, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "How about allowing arbitrators to not be bound entirely by the law, but also by common sense when it comes credit card defaults?", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Common sense tells us that if a Colorado flood washes away a community, those in the community are possibly not going to be able to pay their credit card bills for a few months.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Common sense tells us that a medical emergency, being the victim of a hit and run accident, destruction of a home, or becoming an unpaid CareGiver for a family member should take precedence over the monthly payment requirement. ", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is not about debt forgiveness, ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "its about declaring a debt neutral, no more penalties, fees or interest rate charges are applied to the debt, and the debtor agrees to pay off the debt in a reasonable manner, even if it takes 10 years to do so.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "http://www.change.org/petitions/congress-create-debt-neutrality-rights-for-paying-down-credit-cards-student-loans", "type": "reference", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 637, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I can state from personal experience that when our savings ran out I became eligible for in home support services ", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "in which I as an unpaid caregiver could be paid a very modest amount (at minimum wage payment) ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I was a caregiver.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "By being an in home CareGiver, I was saving the state a lot more money than it would cost to pay me a small amount every month via in home support services.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I told this to all of my creditors, none of them cared.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Then reality hit, my state agency that was supposed to help me obtain in home support services instead cast fear into both me and my parent by stating to me on the phone that whatever they paid me, they would file a lien on the home to get back if I outlived my parent.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It turns out this application of the law did not apply to me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However the damage was done.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": ["8"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I lost 1.75 years of eligibility and probably enough money to pay all of my vendors, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and, I would have never had to prolong the default for more than a couple of months if any of my vendors had cared enough to just help me get through the process of applying for in home support services.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But because judges have become so vindictive in their approach to credit card defaulters, ", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "judges have allowed the credit card companies to become LAZY at solving their own problems internally.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Nobody helps, ", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "everybody simply self protects their own interests first and foremost.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 638, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Like most regulatory programs additional cost would be inevitable,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "it could be paid for by a yearly fee that collectors pay to be a licensed collector.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 639, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "With a fully communicative voicemail identifying the purpose of the call I think one call is quite diligent.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they choose to call and leave no message then they might as well have done nothing.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "At least this way their message is being delivered.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 644, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "The national database and licensing would be a good idea if it were used effectively to weed out the bad collectors and put them (and their corporate officers) out of business permanently. Not those who get caught up in technical violations over mini-Mirandas, but the ones who knowingly commit serious violations of the FDCPA, FCRA, and TCPA.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As Tfleeman noted in his very insightful comment above, the \"private policing\" we have now has not been effective in stopping the worst abuses.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As for the main topic of this page, I think it's far better for a collector to leave a voicemail (with clear identification of the caller and callee) than to call the same number 50 times without leaving a message.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "The rules should encourage this rather than frustrate it.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "So, I would favor option #1, with the mini-Miranda deferred until the collector is sure he is talking to the right person.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 645, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I would have to point out that there is many complaints in regards to how abusive or harassing debt collectors are according to consumers.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As a third-party debt collector, I receive dozens harassment complaints daily.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would just like to note that 80% of the time, these consumers that my fellow co-workers and I come across, are complaining of harassment and abuse;", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "and 100% of them are truly just unwilling to face the facts.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That's what they are complaining about.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When we tell them that they owe a debt, they consider it harassment and abuse.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "They just don't want to hear their problems.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, grant it, there are some debt collectors that are harassing and abusive, but the other 98% are just pointing out the truth.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When consumers realize that it is them and not us, debt collectors would receive a better reputation.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But until then, we are the enemy in the consumer's eyes.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 649, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The majority of the time, when a debt has been paid off, it has been paid to the client, not the collection agency.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most of that time when that debt has been paid to the client, the client neglects to report it to the agency.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1"], "text": "So the collectors continue to call on a paid debt that they have no knowledge of.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1"], "text": "It's really not the collectors fault, it is generally the client's.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 655, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If a debt is to be sold, the owner of the debt should be required to send an itemized statement to the debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "3"], "text": "The statement should have a large-type header, something like, \"[NAME OF CREDITOR] IS SELLING THIS DEBT TO [NAME OF DEBT BUYER].\"", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This would give the debtor another chance to pay in the simplest way, before getting tangled up in idiot phone calls, ", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it would help the debtor identify the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 656, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2", "3", "5"], "text": "If a debt is to be turned over to a collection agency, the owner of the debt should be required to send a fully itemized statement to the debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The statement should have a large-type header, something like, \"[NAME OF CREDITOR] IS TURNING THIS DEBT OVER TO [NAME], A DEBT COLLECTION AGENCY.\"", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This would give the debtor another chance to pay in the simplest way, before getting tangled up in idiot phone calls,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it would help the debtor identify the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debt owner already has the itemized bill;", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "it would be just a matter of copying it again and sending it.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "there should be a requirement that the original creditor make a true, good-faith effort to contact the debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've dealt with those who do this, and those who don't.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some will send you a bill, and then when they get no answer, call you and check the address, which is often wrong.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some, it seems, hardly wait for the ink to dry on their first bill before they turn it over to collection.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 657, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "My experience is only with medical bills.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debt collectors seem only to know (a) what hospital and (b) how much.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When you've been doing the hokey-pokey from emergency room to nursing home and back again over a period of months, that information is not much help.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1_2"], "text": "What's really needed is an itemized bill that's a lot clearer than the \"statement of benefits\" we get now. Something as clear as: \"You were in X hospital on this date. You had this test and that test. They cost a gazillion dollars, but we bargained them down to $17.48. Please pay this amount.\"", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 658, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Wow, I didn't even know we had those rights", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "except for the one about the workplace, they're all news to me.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0", "1"], "text": "So I've no experience,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but my guess would be that the debt collectors would rather not receive this information.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 659, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["5"], "text": "I think probably the benefits of giving debt collectors and buyers access to these documents would NOT worth the costs unless the documents have to be included with the validation notice.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the debt collectors were anxious to be sure they had the right debtor, sure, great.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "But I don't think they are.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The actual guy on the phone is only anxious to get the money;", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "he doesn't really care where it comes from or whether the debt is legal.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Giving him the information, without giving it to the debtor, probably wouldn't be much good.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And maybe I'm being unfair.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Maybe these companies are strict about making sure the debt is collected from the right person.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Naaah....", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 660, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["4"], "text": "The main problem with privacy is that we use the SS# for everything, so everything can be connected.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "That's been a bad idea since they started using it as a taxpayer i.d.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It probably prevents a little fraud,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "but it's not worth it.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We have, in effect, made it illegal to be untraceable--not a good thing for victims of domestic abuse, among others.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 661, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2", "3"], "text": "No robo-calls or automated dialing systems should be allowed for any profit-making or solicitation purpose. Period.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You can call me if a tornado is coming,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but if you want money, you have to use a person.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And I don't see why I should pay for the call.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 662, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I generally prefer e-mail to telephone communication,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but you can't be sure the e-mail has reached the person.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1"], "text": "I would suggest a notice that says, \"If you don't acknowledge receipt of this e-mail, we'll start phoning you.\"", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 663, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Payment processor Visa has general information and the corresponding state statutes about the 10 states that prohibit companies from charging credit/debit card fees located on their website.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": ["3", "4"]}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "Texas, which most people would think would be business friendly, is actually really consumer friendly when it comes to these fees, for example.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Texas has had a long-standing state law against credit card fees, and just recently this year created a new state law to cover against debit card fees and other stored value cards (like prepaid debit cards).", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": ["5", "6"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "http://usa.visa.com/personal/using_visa/checkout_fees/", "type": "reference", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "http://usa.visa.com/download/merchants/surcharging-faq-by-merchants.pdf", "type": "reference", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "http://www.statutes.legis.state.tx.us/Docs/FI/htm/FI.339.htm", "type": "reference", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "http://www.capitol.state.tx.us/tlodocs/83R/billtext/html/HB03068F.htm", "type": "reference", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And, no, I do not have any knowledge of if debt collectors are charging debtors payment processing fees or not,", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but if they are--especially in the states that forbid this practice--they should not be allowed to do so.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And I further believe that in the remaining states that do not have any laws forbidding credit/debit cards surcharges, that a fed reg/law should forbid debt collectors in all states from doing so.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 665, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, I am also concerned with whether or not collectors should identify themselves in a message, or if they should be more general in identifying who they are in a voice message as to not invade the privacy of the debtor for whomever else may share the same answering machine or otherwise may over hear the message.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "So far, I have purposely remained neutral on this matter", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "because I have yet to form an opinion.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I can see both sides of the arguments.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think I lean more to wanting the collectors to be more discrete and general about who is calling,", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I still am not sure.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "The big concern that is more concrete is definitely the phone number caller id,", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "in that it should be the true number of the business and (if a message is left) should also be the call back number.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 668, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have found, on numerous occasions, that the debt collection process allowing firms purchasing debt - for pennies on the dollar - often use intimidating tactics that can easily be considered extortion.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Every time a deb t collector purchases an old, out-of-date debt, they re-file the debt with the credit bureau(s).", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This continues the credit report damage for years - sometimes decades.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As a mortgage banker, those persons often find it impossible to secure a mortgage and realize the American dream of home ownership.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 669, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I think I do kind of like this idea.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This designated database/website could also list Summary of Rights for state laws and Fed laws.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Then this same website might also be able to be used as a way to report abusive behaviors (or link to the appropriate websites to do so), and other relevant information for consumers regarding consumer debt, credit, and credit reports, and other various useful information that is currently available but is spread across many agency websites.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The website could be paid for and maintained by the debt collectors (sort of like how annualcreditreport.com is paid for and maintained by the credit reporting agencies).", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It could be a way to help bring legitimacy to the debt collection industry by having a way to identify them to separate the legit companies from the bad ones while allowing collectors to operate effectively.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 672, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_3"], "text": "I would like something that addresses the amount of times a debt collector can contact someone other than the debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My husband's exwife has several debts", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and we are sometimes contacted several times a day and often at night to find out if we are in contact with her", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they have been divorced 36 years", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 673, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Please include calls to family and friends of debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We are called frequently to pass on messages for people that have our last name, some of them we don't know.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 674, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I often get robo calls about family members debt, sometimes 3 or 4 a day, usually for family members that I haven't spoken to for decades.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "I am not sure how they get my phone no.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as it is unlisted and I am sure the family members don't have it.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 675, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Mslade, you have some valid points about the confusing Foti rulings,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "but I think you are wrong about the TCPA.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This law has always applied to debt collectors, politicians, and even charities with respect to cellular phones.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And it's not just one judge who has ruled in this way.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The FCC and the courts have repeatedly affirmed it.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 676, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_3"], "text": "Tiffany, I think part of the problem is that the 2% of collectors who harass and abuse are responsible for a disproportionate share of the contacts that consumers have with your industry.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Everyone (whether they owe a debt or not) has had an encounter with one of these bad apples,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and then they want to take out their anger on you.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And when you make an honest mistake and get sued for a technical violation, you pay the same penalty as a company that has deliberately harassed someone with 100 phone calls.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 677, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["4"], "text": "I do not believe that use of social media should be allowed to initiate or to conduct any legal or other sensitive arrangements or communications to and from debt collectors.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are a couple of things that I've noticed about social media:", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4"], "text": "social media is a fad, and an outlet.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "People use social media as an outlet for the narcissistic/public/storybook/memorable moments side of their lives.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And recent evidence shows that fewer teens and young adults are using facebook and twitter.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "And I am most certain that no social media user would like for their private life to become public life by dealing with a debt collector on facebook.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Nobody likes to be in debt and have bill collectors chasing them,", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In writing\" to me, means a letter delivered in the mail.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would also accept an interpretation to mean delivered by email but only on official company letterhead documents. And only if first requested by the debtor and not first initiated by the collector.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But I can not accept \"in writing\" to mean messages and communication sent via social media.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12_13"], "text": "I think that E-Sign consent should only be valid for the original creditor.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "And any and every collector who then gets involved must get the debtor to consent E-Sign with them.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The reason is because there are some things that I, as a consumer, am comfortable with dealing online or through email with my original creditors,", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but there are things that I know I would not feel comfortable dealing with online/email with a debt collector.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12_13"], "text": "So E-Sign should not be blanket consent for anyone and everyone.", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 679, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "My daughter has both private and federal loans through Sallie Mae.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They call her cell phone and my cell phone daily, at least 10 times a day.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They called me,", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "by the way, they do not have her permission to speak with me, and tell me to stop paying her federal loans because they can be deferred and pay the private loans.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My daughter owes 176000.00 in private loans and can't afford to make the payments that they are asking for.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They called her employer requesting information on her.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "She sent a letter and requested that they only contact her through email and US mail.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When they called me I asked them if they received this", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they said yes but they need to be able to talk to someone.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Well, they don't have my number as a contact number.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I told them and they still call my cell phone daily.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My daughter can barely pay the bills she has now.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I help her pay her private loans.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I am not on any of her loans.", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This harassment needs to stop!", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 680, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "You know, my only experience is with medical debts,", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but with those, we have NOT been notified several times, or sometimes, even one time.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "No one seems to care if the address is right", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and when you're dealing with an old person, the billing address is often not the same as the physical address);", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "sometimes the bill seems to go to what they claim is a collection agency even before the insurance company finishes with it.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We are perfectly happy to pay our bills,", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but our contract is with the provider,", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and that's who we pay, not a collection agency.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 681, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "All? It's just not so.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Maybe retailers do;", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have no experience with them.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But medical billers are consistently mistaken, careless, and just plain wrong.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One medical facility called my daughter-in-law's cell phone about a bill for my mother!", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They had her number as, I think, the fourth emergency number.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And this was a GOOD place, that actually tried and finally managed to get in touch with me.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was very pleased with their billing department, compared to others we had dealt with.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 682, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I see what you mean,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but that tiny percentage suffers incredible annoyance and harassment.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Should they pay what they don't owe, merely to get out from under?", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All we've ever asked for is an itemized bill from the original creditor,", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but the collectors act as if that's too much.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And they say--and probably believe--that we've received other bills, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but we haven't.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We've lived in the same place for 30 years", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5_7"], "text": "how awful it must be for people who move a lot.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
