{"commentID": 684, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The state in which I practice does not allow jurisdiction based solely on where the contract was signed.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "As such, we limit our filings to the venues where we reasonably believe the consumer resides.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The states typically define what is the proper court thereafter, whether its based on amount, location, etc.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "so even if there is a large judicial districts we do not have the choice to file elsewhere by local rules.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 685, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I am sorry to hear about this situation.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This kind of abusive behavior is upsetting to hear as a consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "They don't need to \"speak\" with anyone.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You/your daughter are perfectly within your legal rights to ask the phone calls to stop and to communicate by other means.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And the collectors who are refusing to honor this request is in violation.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Moreover, they should not be contacting you", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "nor they should be contacting you/your daughter 10 times a day.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is clearly excessive and abusive.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would like to also mention, that although they do have a point about the federal loans can usually be placed into deferment,", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "debt collectors are not fiduciaries", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and are not acting with nor are capable of providing financial advice that is in the best interest of the consumer/debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The collectors will say anything and do anything just to get paid.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11", "13"], "text": "They should not be allowed to offer advice on what bills to pay and how to pay them.", "type": "policy", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This sort of \"advice\" can be detrimental to consumers/debtors.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Perhaps the CFPB should allow collectors to offer referrals on financial advice,", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they should not allow collectors to outright give financial advice.", "type": "policy", "id": 15, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 686, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Debt collectors file a large number of default judgments ", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because quite simply consumers do not take action, not because they are unaware of the issue.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Usually at the time a lawsuit is filed, a debt collector has attempted to resolve the issue via telephone calls and/or letters.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This doesn't even include the efforts the original creditor may have made.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "A lawsuit is never a first response.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is usually done after numerous and repeated failed efforts to work with a consumer to resolve an outstanding debt.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A default judgment is just a further extension of that.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Even after we file suit, we may attempt to reach the consumer to resolve the lawsuit prior to judgment being taken.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have seen numerous files where we have spoken to the consumer and told them they can file an answer, and they still don't.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In my opinion, default judgments are largely the result of consumer's deliberate uninvolvement with the process, rather than a collector taking deceptive steps.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I will state that many states have local rules that if there is no response to a summons and the consumer has defaulted, they do not need to be noticed on a motion for a default judgment.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "Therefore, the actual entry of the judgment may in fact come as a surprise, despite the summons stating if you don't answer a judgment may be taken.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, an attorney who follows the local rules is not acting deceptively.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In order to curb this shock for the consumer who doesn't answer, it wouldn't be bad to require all motions for judgment be served upon the consumer, despite local rules which may require otherwise.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["15"], "text": "I would point out, many default judgment motions are not noticed for motion hour.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They may simply be submitted for a ruling without a court hearing.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As to the inquiry as to what is required to support a default judgment, this varies court to court and judge to judge.", "type": "fact", "id": 16, "evidence": ["17"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The courts that I have seen require more documentation are largely looking for affidavits of debt, charge off statements and statement showing payments or charges, and the assignment (if the plaintiff is a debt buyer).", "type": "testimony", "id": 17, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 688, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I would like to see requirements that the consumers are required to provide written notice of any new addresses for the creditor to reach them", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so in the event the account does go into default, the creditor has current information to attempt to contact the consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many consumers move frequently, yet fail to update the creditors", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 689, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2", "3"], "text": "I believe that this practice in already in place in three major ways.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The creditor usually already requires all of their customers to provided updated contact information,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once a consumer moves the address change and other contact information changes are updated on the consumers credit report,", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and finally, The USPS has records of mail forwarding procedures once a consumer moves.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 691, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "From a creditor's standpoint, I generally agree with this comment.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think a good validation notice could answer a lot of the consumer's question.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think the author of the above note had some very well reasoned thoughts.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "I wouldn't go so far as to add that an itemized statement must be provided, particularly if one might not be available (perhaps because of record retention rules or because one simply may not exist),", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but providing information as to the type of account, brand name of the original creditor issuing the account, the account number, the date of last pay, and the name of the party from whom the debt may have been purchased would help.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Providing documentation at the get go seems rather unneccessary and costly, particularly if the wording of the letter allows the consumer to readily identify the account, and the disclosures allow the consumer to request documentation for validation.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 692, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Alternative one is the easiest to communicate and probably the easiest to understand.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Accouting systems will vary from creditor to creditor", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "and requirements beyond this would only become more cumbersome and costly for a creditor and more confusing for a consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "I would not have the breakdown be different for different types of credit extended.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Computers and brains all across America will start smoking.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 694, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "You raise an issue that has two distinct definitions: \"sent\" and \"received\"", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't think that any consumer wishes that they \"receive\" a notice that wasn't \"sent\" in the first place.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In addition, letters and parcels get lost in the mail all the time.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If there is a requirement for a credit/collector to \"send\" the notices you are referring to, the first place to send them are going to be an address that is on file.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the letters then get returned, then you would know that they are not at the address that is on file.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But the letters have to be \"sent\" in the first place.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 695, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "You are correct.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There is quite a difference between send and receive.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All I am suggesting is that a creditor only be required to send any notice to the last known address - not that the consumer receive it.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and you presume too much if you think that all mail is returned if not delivered to the proper recipeint),", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "then the creditor must send the notice to that new address.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the point of this dialogue is to ensure the consumer is protected, then require the consumer to protect themselves and provide this information to the creditor.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they don't then a creditor can't be hanged in a lawsuit for a letter failing to reach a consumer, when the creditor actions used the best information on hand.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 698, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_2"], "text": "I am an experienced recipient of collection calls.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As I have explained in another post here, I live in a fairly large metro area,", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and whenever anyone with my very common last name and first initial skips town without paying his/her bills, I'm the one who gets the calls from the debt collectors.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "I know that a call about \"an important business matter,\" is a call about a debt.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have received many of these kinds of calls.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Whenever a debt collector calls me and leaves a message without a name, it doesn't take me very long to figure out that the call is from a debt collector.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the debt collector calls and leaves a name, that debt collector is revealing to me, an unrelated third party, that the individual has a debt in collection.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "I consider this to be a violation of the spirit of the FDCPA if not the letter.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Whenever a debt collector calls me, I am burdened with the knowledge that I now know the name of someone else who has a debt in collection.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've gotten any number of the calls described in #4 telling me not to listen if I'm not the named individual.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The big problem with that is that, one again, the name of a debtor is being revealed to me,", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "and then there's the added dilemma of the fact that now my phone number has been programmed into a debt collector's robo dialer.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When that happens, the calls continue to come.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I always disobey the instructions and listen to the message.", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["15"], "text": "I then call the debt collector to report a case of mistaken identity.", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's the only way to stop the calls.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In all the collection calls I have gotten over the years, I have received only one message with the \"mini-Miranda\" warning.", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I called the debt collector to report another case of mistaken identity I was connected with an individual in a call center in India.", "type": "testimony", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After I told the woman she had the wrong person, I thanked her for the \"mini-Miranda\" and she hung up on me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't have any answers, just lots of experience.", "type": "value", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I hope someone finds this information useful.", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 702, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "There was another debt collector that went after me a second time.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "First they placed me on their hit list trying to get me to pay the debt of a man with my last name and first initial.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I told them that they were contacting the wrong person.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Then, several months later, they went after me again, this time looking for a woman with my last name and first initial.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After the second round, I send them a cease-communication letter,", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they haven't called me again.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 703, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "Sorry, but you are mistaken about debt collectors not being able to change information in your credit file.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, they can,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and yes they do.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If my account has been sold (several) times to other people, and my original creditor no longer owns the account, then how would my account be (updated/reported) by that company (debt collector) that purchased it?", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "And, yes they (the person furnishing) the information to the credit bureau can and do supply credit bureaus with fraudulent information.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That's how Debt Collector's get sued in the first place.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 704, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2"], "text": "I agree.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most creditors already have this information in contracts and other correspondence to the debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "This additional notice is unnecessary would be cumbersome and costly.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
