{"commentID": 708, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2", "3", "4", "5"], "text": "The FDCPA needs to be brought into current times.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is more efficient and effective for collectors for sure.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "It is the preferred method of communication for consumers without a doubt.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Most would certainly rather get an email or text, rather than a phone call.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Regular mail is inefficient and becoming more expensive every year and often ignored.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It benefits everyone to update to allow using modern technology to communicate with each other.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "Social networking is can should be used for locating only.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't believe that communications through social networking is in the best interest for any of the parties involved.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 710, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I had a 19 year old debt come back to haunt me", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I went to three attorney's to attempt to pay them to \"talk\" to the company, as the information I was given, would not call me back after leaving several messages, along with an offer to settle it for slightly more than one-half of what they claimed I owed.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This debt went from around $1200 up to $9,300 in those 19 years.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "This type of behavior must be regulated", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "it is only out and out a scam.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 716, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "When the first collection agency can't collect they sell the debt to 2nd tier collectors.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They sometimes sell it to 3rd tier collectors.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My experience in helping resolve collection disputes is sometimes the first collector and always the third collectors do not provide debt validation letters.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 717, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Once companies have sold the debt to a collection agency they do not help resolve it in any way", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the collection agency is only interested in getting money not whether the debt is real or there were some mitigating circumstances.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 720, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The most important would be not to call at work.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "That's really the most important to the collectors, too,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because a person out of work isn't likely to pay.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 721, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_3"], "text": "I believe most default judgments occur for one reason: the consumers know they owe the debt and see no reason to prolong the situation.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many consumers will call us and make payment arrangements after being served.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "We advise them they have the opportunity to be heard in court but most decline.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They simply want to resolve the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 722, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Consumers who ask for validation should receive just that: a validation that the agency has verified the balance due has some basis as alleged.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Too often consumers categorize this process as requiring \"proof\" as taxguy does.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "This is not the function of the validation process.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "\"Proof\" is something that will occur in court (or not).", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "No document will be enough \"proof\" for many consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "That is why the court system exists.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 728, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "My experience is the collection agency will not correct the debt on the credit report!", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "we need a law requiring the collection company to report debt repayment or debt settlement to the credit bureau in a timely manner... Say 30 days after the debt has been settled, or payment arrangements have been made.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "It can be very hard to clean up your credit when working with collection companies...", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they want their money but they don't care if your credit report is accurate!", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 730, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "FDCPA 805(a)(1) is routinely violated by at least two large banks--Citicards and Wells Fargo.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": ["1", "2_3"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Both have called before 9 AM and after 8 PM.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I live in the Central Time Zone", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and no matter where these banks are based, they ignore that and call early and late.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The mailing address should take priority", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "and it should not matter whether the collector is based in Portland, Oregon or Ft. Lauderdale, Florida,", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "if it's 8 AM in Chicago, they should not be calling.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 732, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Massachusetts has this right.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "There need to be strict and enforceable limits on the number of times a collector can call during the week.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've received as many as 40 calls over a 5-day period from Citicards and calls every 50 minutes at work during the day by Wells Fargo.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "THIS IS SHAMEFUL", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "AND THIS FREQUENT REPEAT CALLING HAS TO BE STOPPED BY LAW!", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Those of us who are in debt know it and don't have to be reminded over and over again.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Calling numerous times per day or per week won't get the debt paid any faster.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If you explain that to the collector on the other end of the phone, they blame the repeat dialing on their computers.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "Now that's lame.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The computers can be programmed to call once a day or a hundred times a day.", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once is enough.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
