{"commentID": 748, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Patience is the number one option.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Agree to contact the credit card company and have the debt reduced to what it was at the time of default.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Agree to even a 5 dollar monthly autopay with the promise that eventually it will be increased.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Then report the account in good standing to the credit bureaus as long as those five dollar payments come in.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 750, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Bonzarel. while I think your idea is a good one,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "it could open the floodgates to interest rate padding the debt until it reaches one of the \"floors\" that you are suggesting.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "30% interest rate charges, penalties and fees (which in turn also get hit with a 30% interest rate charge), can accelerate even a 500 dollar debt into the thousands in less than 24 months time.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 751, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2_3"], "text": "Larry S, your quote...\"A plaintiff in a lawsuit cannot be placed in a situation where it is rewarding to sue with insufficient cause and minimal risk\" is a very powerful statement and one that I entirely agree with.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is this scenario that emboldens debt collectors to hire riff raff service companies who will lie about doing a legal service or sub service, and apparently get away with it.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": ["2"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have been victimized by two false subservices.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think both were done by the same service company.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 753, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have been falsely subserved twice.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Both times resulted in verdicts against me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Thank you for taking the time to express your viewpoint, which should carry a LOT OF WEIGHT", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since you are in it at the ground level.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I had not been falsely subserved, it is possible that the debt collector would have been more humbled and more amenable to my extremely generous offer of agreeing to the pay the debt in full based on what it was at the time of the default, as long as I could start with a very low monthly payment and build it up over time.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And as along as I was honoring my word, the debt would no longer be reported negatively on my credit report.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "But I never got that far", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because the debt collection companies simply hired someone who would deliver a service, no questions asked as to its legality.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 755, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Jeffreyjon, it sounds like you are identifying how a strategic defaulter acts.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, Involuntary Defaulters don't have the income available to pay down a debt if the interest rate charges are going to keep accruing.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 756, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "By the time a file reaches litigation, the debtor has already received at least one prior opportunity to resolve the debt with the collector (the initial demand letter, which by law must inform the debtor of his/her right to challenge the veracity of the debt being pursued).", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "By making default judgment more difficult, the CFPB would only be rewarding the debtors who choose to take no action to resolve their complaints.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Furthermore, the CFPB arguably has no authority to impose new, more burdensome requirements upon litigants in state court fora.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Doing so would constitute an admission that state court rules of civil procedure deny due process in other types of proceedings that are not granted the \"benefit\" of Federal oversight.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 757, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "It is unwise to require that the debt collector send sensitive personal information to the debtor (e.g., SSN, account number", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as such a requirement would expose the debtor to the danger of ID theft.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 758, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "For attorney debt collectors, being required to provide a list of all the rights the consumer may have comes perilously close to the provision of legal advice;", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "even if it doesn't cross that line, the unsophisticated debtor may believe that an attorney is acting as a neutral court officer rather than as an advocate for an adverse party.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've had debtors ask me \"Do I need to come to court for this?\" after I've sued them.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 759, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "There is now a class of \"consumer representatives\" which obtains from debtors a signed \"Power of Attorney\" and who then claim to be authorized to act as the consumer's attorney for purposes of debt resolution.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They routinely seek to avoid the debt, most commonly by not answering their phones.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My current practice is to advise the relevant state bar of the unauthorized practice of law by these jokers;", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "perhaps a clarification statement that such persons must be licensed to practice law in the state in which the debt is being collected would cut down on the confusion.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 760, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_2"], "text": "In fact, it is a gross distortion of the law for the CFPB to claim that suit on a debt outside of the statute of limitations period is per se unfair, deceptive or misleading.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Under the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure (and most state civil rules), the statute of limitations is an affirmative defense which must be pleaded by the defendant;", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "if it is not, the defense is considered to have been waived.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The purpose of the defense is to enable a party to avoid being disadvantaged by the long delay, loss of evidentiary documents, memory fading, etc.;", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "if the debtor doesn't claim that they are disadvantaged by the delay, then the delay clearly isn't so long as to preclude a vigorous defense.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 762, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Several courts have held\"and the [FTC] and the [CFPB] agree'that a collector who sues or threatens suit on a time-barred debt violates the FDCPA.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The FDCPA prohibits, among other things, the use of \"any false, deceptive, or misleading representation or means in connection with the collection of any debt.\" ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": ["3"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These include making a false representation of 'the character, amount, or legal status of any debt,\" threatening 'to take any action that cannot legally be taken or that is not intended to be taken,\" and \"using any false or deceptive means to collect or attempt to collect any debt.\"", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": ["3"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "http://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/201309_cfpb_agency-brief_12-cv-04057.pdf", "type": "reference", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "It is in fact your gross distortion of the law and misunderstanding to claim that SOL are a defensive mechanism to allow a plaintiff \"to avoid being disadvantaged\" for not filing a lawful suit within a lawful time frame.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 763, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I am sure many judges would disagree with you.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Courtrooms are not a playground.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "And judges do not like it when plaintiffs waste their time by filling frivolous lawsuits that do not have proof.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 764, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As I frequent many of the consumer credit forums,", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "I will tell you that most consumers do think that a debt can still be brought to court when the receive contact past the SOL.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And others I have run into also still get contacted even after the 7 year mark when the debt has finally dropped from their credit report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In fact, just the debt dropping off from the reports that has otherwise been dormant will get an automatic response from debt collectors.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It seems they purposely wait for it to drop off and then pounce to instill fear. As in a \"gentle\" reminder that they are still there.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They act like sharks in the water circling their prey.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And the consumers bring up questions like \"when will this end?\" and \"I thought the debt wipes out after 7 years, why are they still contacting me?\"", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Something needs to be done about this.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "SOL are SOL for a reason.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "Debt collectors should not be able to harass and harass and harass.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 765, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "A marital spouse is no longer a marital spouse when either martial partner dies.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The end is death.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A spouse doesn't remarry while still married,", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but unmarried people will remarry.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "A divorced spouse or a widowed spouse, may become the spouse of another once remarried.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The term spouse, in my opinion, relates to a marriage.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Once the marriage is over, the \"spouse\" is no longer a \"spouse.\"", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 766, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "After offering documentation that I didn't owe a debt, the collection company ignored what I offered as proof and continued to try to collect the debt", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "even stated they didn't care that I didn't owe it.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "They should be required to investigate and respond in writing to a consumer's defense,", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so a follow up can be made, or complaint filed with a governmental agency.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Documentation should also follow the claim ", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as collection companies sell their lists to new companies.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Better, no documented defense of a claim should be eligible for sale until resolved.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 768, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2_7"], "text": "Debt collectors should announce themselves and refrain from acting like: investigators, attorneys, or hitmen.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0", "2_7"], "text": "There needs to be an enforced code of behavior that represents a professional on the other end of the phone.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most recently, my husband has been receiving threatning phone calls from a collector pretending to be a law enforcement investigator.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The most humiliating part is that the calls have escalated to his ex-wife, cousin, and associates.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He has a common name and the \"investigator\" has not properly identified himself or clearly identified if my husband is the right person that the debt belongs too.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In addition, the so called debt is 8 yrs old,", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they call from unknown numbers", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "or if the number shows up and it's googled there are comments stating that the persons calling are harassing.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 771, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Well, I get at least one call per week from a litigant saying \"I was served with a summons today, and it says I must appear within 10 (or 30) days to answer this complaint, but there is no court date on the papers for me to appear\",", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I have to tell them the procedure (and point out to them the blurb about you not physically having to come to court to answer).", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "I'm not sure how much clearer the wording in the summons has to be,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I understand them fully, and not just because I'm familiar with the forms,", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'm just smarter than the average litigant I have to deal with I guess.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The complaints do state that they have the rights to the debt, under verification that is notarized, at first...", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they cannot enter the default judgment unless they provide the affidavit signed by both parties who owned and now owns the debt, which is generally attached to their judgments.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 772, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I was not the one with debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was a mediator trying to help.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The people with this situation sometimes ignore the first notice to them and don't ask for a validation letter.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Others, I believe, do not read it carefully and see they have a small window of time to dispute the claim.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "3"], "text": "I think the original notice letter to the debtor should HIGHLIGHT the part about a validation letter.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6_7"], "text": "I also, think the original creditor should be required to help resolve disputes instead of debtors or third parties like me only being able to talk with the collection agency.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Probably 50% of the agencies I have dealt with do not follow existing regulations.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Without penalties they never will.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The few that are reasonable and follow the rules are a pleasure to deal with, as a third party.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 774, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Disputes are not investigated.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is a joke.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sending out a letter to whoever these debt collectors think is responsible for the debt is just rote -- it is not done in good faith or follow the letter of the law.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They 1) use vague names, no signature, post office boxes, a million aliases for their debt collection business", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "THAT practice has to stop).", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The FTC says \"reasonable\" investigation but these companies do none,", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and that is the standard practice.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A good start is having a realistic and fair and honest laws requiring the companies to verify debt without already having assumptions or worse, not caring if they have the right person or not.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "Any rule change needs to carry some penalty", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "or it won't have any impact on an industry that has run roughshod over consumers now for two decades.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Abuses abound.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "There also should be special requirements for validating medical debt because of privacy rights.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There seems to be no concern of violating people's privacy when it comes to medical debt collection activities.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 776, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "what kind of consumer contacts do debt collectors... disputing the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That presumes they actually follow the law and do a validation investigation.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "That is wrong,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4_12"], "text": "they do not.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I sent a letter to a company claiming I owed a debt", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I was clear I was disputing the debt. A clear, declaratory sentence.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I mailed it to the address listed.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There was NO PERSON who signed this letter to me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had to send it to To Whom It Concerned.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But it was clear I was disputing the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I did so within two weeks, well within the 30 days.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yet they did nothing but wait 30 days and send me a letter saying \"here is the info you requested.\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It contained nothing I recognized.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You are presuming they are actually validating.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["15"], "text": "This is the biggest mistake.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They do none of that.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["17"], "text": "Any rule that defines what qualifies as a dispute would help. The clearer, the better.", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["18"], "text": "The vagueness now has led to abuses. Such as \"frivolous and irrelevant\" disputes.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is a license to abuse consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 18, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 779, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I had the same situation with another cellular carrier.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It seems it's a ploy to keep making the debt seem fresh.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It was another early termination fee,", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I wrote many letters before it was finally removed from my credit report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5_6"], "text": "I think that the tactic of selling the same debt to keep it on a credit report definitely should stop.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is one debt,", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and there is a time limit for how long it stays on one's credit report.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8", "9"], "text": "One way to keep track of this is to require people to be notified if a debt is sold.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is required when a mortgage is sold.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "It seems like a no-brainer.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The rules should also be written to discourage -- no, to bar -- collections companies from passing around debt for the purpose of keeping it on credit reports.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 783, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Well I do want to shout.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You've never been on the receiving end of a collections company that treats people like cattle with dollar signs on them, whether they owe money or not.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And it's been going on for years.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Shame that is the first comment to make to me.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 784, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I concur with previous comment.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If consumers are informed when our mortgages are sold that should be a rule across the board.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sending a letter by mail isn't very expensive, either.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4", "5"], "text": "It should contain the amount, info on original debt, the name and address of who owns the debt and I'd even add the amount the debt was sold for.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Consumers can keep track for one thing, and make sure these debts are not posted twice on our credit reports,", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "it will let people know who to contact about the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 785, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I think it should be kept uniform.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It seems to make sense for sellers to send notification.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 786, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Probably won't find any legislation", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "since people who have allegedly defaulted on a debt aren't necessarily going to tell the world, or create a lobby for their cause.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debt Defaults and Debt Collections are a one sided issue in which judges have been constrained to simply determine if a default has occurred, or not.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "The lawyers primarily work with strategic defaulters", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because S.D.'s have some source of money or income available to pay both the attorney and a partial portion of the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "Involuntary Defaulters are left to fend for themselves", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they don't have money to pay a lawyer.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debt Neutrality, in which an involuntary defaulter agrees they owe the debt and simply want's to be able to pay it down based on the amount the debt was at the time of the default, with no more penalties, interest rate charges, or fees, even if it takes 10 years to pay off the debt, would possibly alleviate a large amount of unnecessary court cases.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And of course, once the very modest initial payments were set up, the account would no longer register as a negative on a debtor's credit score or credit rating.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And to safeguard fraud, the debtor would not be able to keep borrowing larger and larger amounts of money until after their defaults were paid in full.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's a very logical solution in my opinion.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Judges should be able to use logic to solve the growing backlog of credit card default cases.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 788, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The letter I received just said this communication is for the purpose of collecting a debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "First, it was supposed to be a \"validation\" letter,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they don't bother to validate", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they jump the gun.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Communication is always the best way to avoid confusion,", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "so I don't think it would be a hardship on anyone to state clearly this is a debt collection agency/company", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "why use euphemisms.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And then to state unless such and such is paid by (whatever time frame is legal) this will be placed in collection.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I believe there is some rule now to that effect,", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "what I think the problem is, it is not handled consistently.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11_12"], "text": "Each of these many many debt collectors do their own thing.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some are better at communicating than others.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some deliberately do NOT communicate, for deliberate reasons.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Crafting consistent rules and regulations should be the start.", "type": "policy", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["15"], "text": "And then actually requiring these companies follow them.", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If you don't put teeth into it, none of these collection agencies will bother.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are already rules.", "type": "fact", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But we are here because of lack of obeying the law, lack of ethics, lack of clarity in the law, and in my opinion, laws that are slanted against the consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 790, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Clear communication helps everyone, not just consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think debt collectors when trying to collect just send bills,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and everyone knows what a bill is.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But when they devolve into harassment, they blur the lines between trying to collect debt within the law and behaving in misleading and abusive ways toward consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "TRuly, the robot calling, the letters, they have money enough for this.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they communicated clearly up front, they would save more money.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "The post office is still a good deal,", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "not an expensive way to communicate.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "You are missing the boat on the problem, though.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "It is not the costs or whether they should communicate.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most of these companies hire people who are barely literate, poorly trained and certainly uninformed -- wait, UNINFORMED -- about the laws that already exist regarding debt collection.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is a huge problem when trying to get information from an employee who doesn't know the law requires him/her to provide certain information.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This has come about from decades of lack of oversight, in my opinion.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Lack of oversight, lack of clear rules and lack of enforcement.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So, if they don't have to worry about following the law, they hire whoever they can cheap and don't bother to train them.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["14"], "text": "This is why there are so many of these companies", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and after some of them do get in trouble, they just change their name and keep on doing the same law-breaking habits.", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 793, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I found an unsealed envelope in my mail box that had court documents in them.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "I contacted the debt collection company and asked what was going on ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since I had not been served.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They claimed a subservice had already been done to someone at my residence.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "I explained that was probably not likely ", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I am a Caregiver and I would have been the only one to answer the door and I did not get any service.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had to pay to file a response and was late by one day, andthen had to challenge the default because of the non service.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "The judge agreed that there had been no valid subservice ", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "based on the fact that the service company used the most generic \"guess\" they could come up with, a women in her mid 30's to late 40's, around 5 foot 4 inches, weight around 130 pounds to 150 pounds.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is about as generic of a description as one could give, ", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "and it was completely wrong.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because that person did not exist.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They even made up a name of someone I had never heard of and when I googled the name, could not find it anywhere on the internet.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The second time a false subservice happened, a very similar description was given as the first time, ", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the alleged subservice recipient was identified as \"Jane Doe\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would like to point how dangerous these lies are on another level.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I exclusively have been providing CareGiving services for my parents, no one else has.", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "By lying and introducing these lies into a court document, anytime in the future I could be accused of exposing my parents to a person at our residence who never even existed.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["19"], "text": "I was also somewhat frozen by this level of dishonesty", "type": "value", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because on the rare occasion when I had to sue someone, I followed the law and had the service performed legally and properly.", "type": "testimony", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I just expected the same in return", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and by not getting it weakens one's ability to respond.", "type": "value", "id": 21, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 794, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The data is difficult to obtain", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "and likely not attainable", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "considering lawsuits can be filed in magistrate, county, state, and federal courts.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Also the data could be inaccurate", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since a case can be postponed and renewed later.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I do not know if there is any central data base for either court.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also, lawsuits are filed in bankruptcy proceedings as well", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "so these would need to be considered as well.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1", "3", "6_7"], "text": "This is why I am concerned when numbers just get tossed out without and substance verification.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Based on my experiences I would estimate about 1.5% of delinquent accounts were forwarded to filing a lawsuit.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
