honest, this is an outrage what these companies have done, ", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and nobody has minded the store on them.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Never should the onus be on the consumer to get this to stop.", "type": "policy", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["18"], "text": "You have to find a lawyer who thinks a whopping $1,000 is worth suing over.", "type": "policy", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You have rigged this system in favor of the sharks.,", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["20"], "text": "and that is why these sleazy companies have proliferated and have grown more and more egregious in their actions.", "type": "value", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "no more recorded calls.", "type": "policy", "id": 22, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "call from one number", "type": "policy", "id": 23, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as soon as someone says stop calling, STOP.", "type": "policy", "id": 24, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "if there is any call beyond that, they get fined.", "type": "policy", "id": 25, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["27"], "text": "Agreed, people will have to write a letter ", "type": "value", "id": 26, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because none of these companies will admit they were told to stop calling.", "type": "value", "id": 27, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But they do receive the letters,", "type": "value", "id": 28, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "which should go to a physical address and to a person, not just a vague company name.", "type": "policy", "id": 29, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["31"], "text": "Last, stop allowing these bad companies to change their names.", "type": "policy", "id": 30, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They get in trouble, they change their names, and go on doing terrible things under another name.", "type": "value", "id": 31, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Just look online at some of these companies and how many names they've gone through.", "type": "policy", "id": 32, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The reason this got so bad is nobody has been looking out for the consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 33, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 797, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["7"], "text": "This is unreal.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Reading your \"if there is a new federal rule regarding messages...\" It seems like this agency is trying very hard to make it easy to get around the court decision which is one of the few that protected consumers,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they also seem to try to protect the company that abuse the phone because what these people do is harassment.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They know it,", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they know how to do it.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "They've gotten away with it for so long", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "because they answer to no one,", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "you've put the onus on the consumer to have to sue a debt collector who violates the law.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "This is unreal.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 798, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Why are these questions putting the onus, once again, one the consumer?", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is the collectors who have harassed in the name of collecting a debt.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "It is pretty easy to distinguish landline from cellphone", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "google the number, that tells you.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But creditors use recorded calling,", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "that should be stopped.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they have a well-trained person, that person ought to be able to determine the time zone the consumer lives in.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "I agree with the previous comment.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Creditors should assume the current mailing address is the correct one.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "How difficult is it to go from there in assessing the times that are appropriate to make calls?", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 799, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Why should the consumer pay a filing fee at all if the collector is at fault?", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That could be a hardship on many people.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "The collection agencies need to follow the rules of doing their validation correctly,", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and this would not be an issue.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 802, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_2", "4"], "text": "I believe that most Defendants are properly served.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I review about 200-300 civil cases a month", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and very rarely is service done improperly.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This does vary a bit from state to state", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but in my experience the majority of defendants have been properly served.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 803, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["3"], "text": "What a great idea -- record them.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Reading these comments, there are so many examples of abuse, ", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "it seems like this Consumer Protection agency ought to have gotten the message thus far: the phones are used to harass.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The only way to get this to stop is to put some teeth into the laws through civil fines,", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "not put the onus on the consumer to have to sue.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 805, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "They have done so.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've gotten calls from the same collector who will use a toll free, then a number with an area code, then that number will be changed by a digit.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Google the number.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "That is so helpful.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It will tell you the company that is calling.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It was always the same on.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I agree this is wrong, misleading, a fraudulent way to deal with people.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But the totality of all I am reading here is that collectors are harassing and do it by phone.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11", "9_10"], "text": "The thing to do is put some teeth into the laws that prevent this.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Now, the only thing consumers can do is sue.", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And for $1000 -- and you'd be hard pressed to find a lawyer who will sue for such a small amount.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It has become a situation that slams the consumer,", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "it has evolved into that.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 806, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "This is a violation of the FCRA (Fair Credit Reporting Act) and can be corrected quickly by the credit reporting agency.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the credit reporting agency refuses, there are many Consumer Protection Attorneys that would happily take this case on contingency.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "This type of violation normally never sees the inside of a court room.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A letter from a well known CP Attorney will likely get awards and the prompt correction of the credit report.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 808, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The debt collector who harassed me did that number one on the \"three others\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I got calls saying \"hey we'll settle for\" such and such.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It was a medical debt ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "and I was tempted to say why? ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There is only going to be more medical debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When times are that difficult for people, making the mortgage and getting medicine takes precedence.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't think it should be legal for any of these things to happen,", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and certainly not robo-repeat calling", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but yet as you read these comments they are going on.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "I hope this has a good outcome and there will be laws and fines for those companies that do this,", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because what is available now, suing the debt collector, has not put a dent in their egregious behavior.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 810, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Email communication is a huge advantage for all involved parties.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12", "2", "3", "5", "8", "9"], "text": "Emails provide consumers with much better tools to control how they are being contacted.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "First, if treating emails as \"in writing\" (as they should), disputing a debt or demanding that collectors cease communication is much easier.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Second, setting rules to hide collection notices is a powerful tool not available in any other communication medium.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "3rd party disclosure is therefore a lesser concern.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Third, email delivery is fast, and facilitates an efficient process, where less communications can be made to reach a settlement.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Everything is in writing.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Fourth, email is significantly less confrontational than phone calls ", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "and causes much less stress to recipients.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Fifth, email is better than recording in keeping record of communication,", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "making it even harder for collectors to hide acts of non compliance.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Email should be allowed, while keeping the sensitive parts of the message (disclosures, personal details etc) hidden - as an attachment or as a link that is part of an email.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, email is more cost efficient to collectors", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "which is why using email should be conditional on collectors not charging the debtors any fees for their payments.", "type": "policy", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The added profitability should be shares with the consumer.", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 811, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Email rules allows hiding emails and routing them in ways that surpass any other communication method.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In addition, since email \"sender ID\" is easier to demand and maintain,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "debtors will have an easier time managing what communication they receive, and when.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "As a result, there is no necessity for forcing specific times of email delivery.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 812, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Email isn't easier to access or view off the debtor's screen than a call", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "a call's content is actually harder to hide if you receive it among other people),", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "text message or SMS.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4", "5"], "text": "The way regulation should handle sensitive information is by mandating that some information be an attachment, or in a link provided in the email, rather than the body of an email.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the attachment is encrypted or details are stored on a secured web page, no one will be able to access them.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In fact, they will be much better protected than any other information relayed to the debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Work emails should be handled differently, much like calls to a work place, which can also be accessed by the employer.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 813, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have a lot of concerns with emails.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Email clients have privacy/security settings that do not allow the sender to know if/when an email has been or was received.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The problem is that even with these privacy/security settings, senders are able to get around these settings.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is widely used by spammers and hackers.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "All of the spam experts all say not to open emails that are spam or potential spam, ", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because the spammers are so good at manipulating and getting around the privacy/security settings and force the recipients email client to inform the sender of when/if an email was opened.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "Also, I do not like the idea that collectors can insert links in emails.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The more unscrupulous collectors and unscrupulous employees can insert links that are harmful to the security of the user\"s computers and offensive to the recipients (like pornographic material).", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Just think about how many collectors still (even after all of the lawsuits) use offensive and abusive language over the telephone,", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "just think about what kind of harm these bad apples would be able to do with emails.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "I also I do not like the emails ", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because of the ease with which collection companies can sell the email lists to marketers.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many decades ago, one of my neighbors was a debt collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "She would tell me that if they couldn't get money out of the debtors then we make money off of them by selling your address and personal information to marketing companies.", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have huge concerns for allowing collectors from using emails.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Any rules that allow collectors to use email should come with deliberate care and attention to the privacy/security, materials and content, and the restriction of selling email lists.", "type": "policy", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["17"], "text": "I also worry about true and accurate identification of emails.", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Spammers/hackers are able to manipulate how emails are presented and the name of the email address that they send with.", "type": "fact", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "there should also be rules restricting collectors are manipulating and spoofing their email addresses.", "type": "policy", "id": 18, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 814, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If emails are allowed, they should not be allowed to be sent outside of what is the acceptable time for phone calls.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "I would like to restrict the time to inside normal business hours for the locale of the debtor,", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "because no business email should ever be sent from the office outside normal business hours.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is basic and normal business etiquette for emails.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But a compromise could be made for what is accepted for phone calls.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6_7"], "text": "However, I would like to see no emails sent on Sundays.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The USPS does not operate on Sundays", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and neither should emails of a business nature.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 815, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I agree that of course an ideal situation would be for consumers not to pay.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But let's not let the perfect be the enemy of the good.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3_4"], "text": "I was proposing some viable method that would result in an ability of a consumer to have a hearing.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Hearings cost money", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and ultimately the collector would be assessed.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 816, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Debtors often respond with \"I don't owe anything\",", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "which is vague and makes it harder to cater for their needs.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1"], "text": "If any rule making is needed, it is about the types of disputes a debtor may bring forth and the documentation needed for both the substantiation of that dispute", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "leaving the option for a dispute to be deemed frivolous", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and what constitutes satisfaction of the dispute or proper proof.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Otherwise, this is left for negotiation between individual collectors and debtors.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 817, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "If you want to instantly level the playing field, make any credit card debt above and beyond the moment of default, disputable.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2_4"], "text": "Disputability of any amount over the amount at the moment of default would instantly get both the credit card companies and the debt collectors working with the consumer on a reasonable plan going forward, no?", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As it stands now, credit card companies can and usually do jump the interest rate up to as high as 29.9%", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "and may even let the account stay in default ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as they rack up frequent default points on the debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I gave up my regional emmy award winning video business to become a caregiver for both of my parents, eventually savings ran out and I notified each of my credit card vendors ahead of any default.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "NONE could offer me anything other than, \"pay your bill on time\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If instead the credit card companies know that once the default occurs they cannot accrue any more penalties, fees or interest rate charges on the debt, they will bend over backwards to work with the alleged defaulter to get them to pay down the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Citibank rate jacked my never late payment 15 year old credit card account by 5,000 dollars.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I dispute that amount of excess in lieu of why I had to default, but Citibank does not care, nor does the debt collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The amount of the debt reverted to what it was at the time of the default, you can bet citibank would be working hard to work with me.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 819, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Why can't we bring back the olden days?", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have been a \"victim\" of debt collectors run amok for over 35 years.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Back in the day, a debt was assigned to one collector who would pursue me relentlessly for a debt that belonged to someone else.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Nowadays with the robo-dialers the collection call is assigned to the \"next available operator.\"", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Why not just go back to the days when only one collector was responsible for making the contact?", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 821, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have a creditor who begins calling withing a few days of becoming past due.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They are relentless calling up to 10+ times a day.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "I don't call them back ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because once on the phone with them, they hound you until you agree to make a payment or post-date a payment.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I don't call them within about 15 days of becoming past due, they start calling my relatives and neighbors and say \"we're trying to locate xxx - do you know them?\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When they answer yes, they ask them to deliver a message to me (phone number and name).", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've been told this is not illegal since they are using public information and not revealing who they are or what the call is in relation to, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but this tactic is shameful.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We are making an honest effort to get current and stay current, ", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but when my neighbor hands me a piece of paper with a note on it, I feel pretty powerless.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is both harassment and abuse in my opinion", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "and it should be addressed.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 822, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I was sued for an alleged debt from 1993 by NYC landlord.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Judge denied him the 1600.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and then his real estate/collections attorney put me into collections ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the landlord got to write off a debt that was not a debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Great for these big landlords in NYC ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as they play the corporate game and sue a tenant 10 times and write it off each and every time even though its not a valid debt.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Its a big deal in Manhattan.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 823, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "It's a good question,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but unfortunately the answer is (of course) complicated.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Manually dialing phones slows down businesses and raises costs;", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "Automated dialing has preventive measures built in that manually dialing does not.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To expand on the first point, debt collectors are cost centers, meaning their primary goal is to minimize costs (i.e., delinquent monies).", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "An automated dialing system allows for a much more efficient manner of calling delinquent account-holders.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Representatives are able to review the account history and status while the system connects the call,", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "so the rep can quickly engage the customer.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a customer has given their cell phone or home number to the lender knowing it may be used for future contact attempts, there is no difference to the customer if the call is executed through a computer or dialer on the keypad.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11", "13"], "text": "To expand on the second point, automated dialing systems have a lot of built in controls that actually protect the consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "People make mistakes, and so do collectors:", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Automated dialers can have filters in place that restrict calls to customers based on location, time of day, or even how many attempts have already been made.", "type": "fact", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In addition, calls made through the dialer can all be recorded", "type": "fact", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "so if there is a problem with the representative, the customer can refer back to the recording and the truth will come out.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 824, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Additionally the landlords real estate attorney also had a collections agency", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "so he continuously flipped the landlords debts into his agency", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and again the landlords get to keep writing it off with each and every lawsuit,", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "in this instance it was 8 lawsuits for the same amount.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 825, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "A dialer does none of the things to which you refer.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A human takes a lists of calls that are deemed restricted to any of the criteria that you listed,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and loads that list into the computer software that also holds a lists of all calls to be made.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Then the list of restricted calls are \"scrubbed\" out of the automated dialer.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This scrubbing process is akin to a human scratching out a phone number with a pen on a paper list.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are no measurable gains in consumer protection to which you refer.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Calls are not recorded through the dialer.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Dialers work in unison with the recording software.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This recording software records manual phone calls just the same.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
