{"commentID": 845, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Most consumers have a bad taste in their mouth from the way that a select few agencies used to operate.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And rightfully so.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But look at it from the other side.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If i owed you $1,000 debt do you really think sending me a letter would do the trick?", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Would you attempt to call me to find out my intentions?", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "My point is, agencies are operating under a pretty broad microscope.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Compliance with the laws is being monitored very closely now.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We view ourselves at my company as extensions of customer service.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If we call you, we specifically ask if we are calling a cell and if it is okay to reach you on that number.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If you say no, we remove the number.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 846, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "6"], "text": "Every validation notice should include, not only the name, but the address and phone number of the current owner of the debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is not always the case that the consumer knows who the owner of the debt is, or how to contact them.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4"], "text": "This would not be a burden on collection agencies,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because it would only require the collection agency to cut and paste the address and phone number of the debt owner onto the validation notice.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "The collection agency should already have this information in their company records,", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as the debt collector is forwarding consumer payments to said debt owner's address.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "This would allow the consumer to attempt to deal with the debt owner directly to try to resolve the dispute.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8_9"], "text": "For example, a case of mistaken identity can more easily be resolved by talking to a customer service representative of the debt owner, than by talking to a debt collector.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debt collector has no authority to correct the mistake,", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but a customer service representative of the debt owner does.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 851, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "With increased and onerous liability for making calls and sending letters to debtors, creditors and debt buyers have had little option but to file suit rather than repeatedly attempt to contact an uncooperative or uncommunicative debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most complaints provide adequate and identifying information about the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "In my experience, most debtors don't feel taken advantage of by lawsuits,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they simply understand they owe the debt", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "3"], "text": "so there is little point in filing an answer or taking time to appear in court.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "In fact, the vast majority never respond to a Federal Law letter inviting them to dispute the debt.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Filing suits and appearing in court is expensive and time consuming for creditors and debt buyer,", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but there is little alternative,", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "nor should there be", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as these matters have always been governed appropriately by State law and State judges.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11_12"], "text": "and the US is a credit ecomony", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "over 70% of our economy is based on consumer spending ", "type": "fact", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "which comes mainly from credit extensions and not consumers pay increases),", "type": "fact", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "there are simply more defaults,", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "particularly in a Great Recession.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Any heavy handed Federal regulation will hamper and restrict credit granting and debt buying,", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "both of which are needed by the economy and the credit industry.", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "While credit grantors should should make their documentation retention systems more accessible and share more documents upon a sale of accounts,", "type": "policy", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "a lack of documentation should not hamper State court lawsuits when a debtor offers no dispute so long as the account is adequately identified in a complaint.", "type": "policy", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In Michigan, efforts to \"make it more likely that consumers would defend themselves\" have fell very flat for the reasons mentioned above.", "type": "value", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As it has always been, the protections are in place and are used by those debtors that wish to avail themselves of them.", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Judges are there to listen.", "type": "value", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, most debtors (bless them) understand they simply owe the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 22, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 852, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Someone who lived at my address, more than 30 years ago had a debt with Household Finance.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We get letters that we return \"Addressee Unknown\" and phone calls.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Finally I called one number back and told them that the person they looked for wasn't there.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That law firm stopped robo-calling ", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but a few months later a new one started up.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_3", "6"], "text": "Records should convey when debts are sold from collection agency to collection agency.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Why should I have to go through all that a second time?", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "I also think debt collectors should be prohibited from using the address to get a phone number after 2 years.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This debt was more than 30 years old", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "why do they think anyone who knew here would still live there?", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I googled the woman's name.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I found out on the first search that she lives about 10 miles from here.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I can find her that easily why can't a debt collector, who stands to gain something, be bothered to do a little research?", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 854, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "When we did it, it was agreed that any 3rd party communication outside SOL at any point was a potential violation of the FDCPA.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Since 3rd party debt collectors are required to be truthful at all times,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "they cannot say 'we are attempting to collect a debt' if they are time-barred from collecting the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We were the meanest, nastiest, most aggressive in the multi-state area at that time,", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and this was the stance.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Suggestion is clarify that time-barred debts are time-barred for the 3rd party as well, and cannot be collected, attempted to be collected, or bought/sold.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 856, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I assume by \"free to end\" you meant the agency is on the hook for the charges incurred on that particular call.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "I think it would be well worth exploring.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We do have situations where the consumer doesnt have a landline and refuses access to their cell.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If we recieve a cease and desist order we note the account and return it to our client as such.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a consumer simply asks not to be contacted via cell we will remove the cell and send a collection letter if it is within FDCPA guidelines.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Other solutions may be to send a settlement letter allowing the consumer to save money in an effort to resolve the issue.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The industry certainly didn't set a very good standard ", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "and regulation is certainly needed.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think the vast majotiry of us get the message loud and clear and are making sure we comply impicitly.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The effort needs to be two fold.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "The consumers have to be willing to discuss the accounts and express willingness to pay.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After all, if everyone's debts were paid, there would be no need for a call.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And that's not meant to sound standoffish.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The simple fact remains at the end of the day, debts are owed and our clients want their money.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["13"], "text": "Consumers must share some of the responsibility.", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 860, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "A contractor who did work unlicensed was able to file bogus claims against both me and my wife amounting to double the original bid price.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "there was no court action.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I managed to get rid of the debt collector ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but there seems nothing I could do to stop another contractor doing the same thing.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "There should be a penalty for the people filing the false debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The amount in question was almost $10,000", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 861, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2"], "text": "I do not think that answering 97% of the calls from an automated dialer within two seconds is a solution to my problem.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would like for Mr. Dan to explain exactly what the safeguards of using a robo dialer are.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "From my perspective as a frequent recipient of robo calls from debt collectors, the problem is a lack of ownership and impersonality of the collection agency when the debt is not assigned to one collector to handle.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Years ago when a collector would call me, it would always be the same person.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Now it is not.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3_4"], "text": "Assign the debt to one collector who would then take full responsibility for making all contacts with the alleged debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This could even include acquisition of location information.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 862, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "What I had in mind when I made this comment was that some debtors are in debt because of a medical condition that has negatively impacted their ability to work.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They may be on Social Security disability for this reason.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sometimes, that medical condition is scientifically known to be aggravated by stress, such as any heart condition, or an anxiety disorder.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Currently, Section 806 of the FDCPA makes abuse or harassment of debtors illegal.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, what qualifies as abuse might be different for a debtor with a disabling medical condition that is sensitive to stress.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "My hope, and my suggestion, is that there could be some way for debtors to make collection agencies aware of the fact that the debtor has a documented medical disability, and that abusive or harassing phone calls have additional health consequences for the debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
