{"commentID": 1041, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I agree that this is about Financial Literacy,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, this is also about the court's enforcing completely one sided credit card adhesion agreements that don't give the debtor/defaulter, rights of any kind, even in the most humanitarian of situations, thereby calling into question the legality of these one sided credit card adhesion agreements.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Lets not forget that it was the comptroller of the currency back in 2002 that prevented the Insurance industry from competing in the credit card debt suspension insurance arena with the credit card companies.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This allowed the credit card companies to then have an obscene monopoly on overpriced credit card debt suspension insurance premiums they charged their own customers who otherwise could have carried insurance policies that would have frozen interest rate charges for a certain period of time when a life changing emergency occurred.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Financial literacy is in play when it comes to the 2% monthly minimum payment addiction scam perpetrated on first time credit card borrowers.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "2% monthly minimum payments are literally no different than a crack dealer giving out a few free hits of crack to get people hooked on their product.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A person can be buy a $1,000 top of the line television set and only have a 20 or 25 dollar payment due the next month.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That's credit card crack in my opinion.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Financial Literacy could be a warning printed in bold letters on every credit card agreement warning how credit cards purposely have low monthly minimum payments to lure one into more and more debt, how credit card companies have no compassion for life changing events, and that credit card companies are overcharging for credit card debt suspension insurance by a factor of up to 2,000%.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11", "12"], "text": "Put those three warnings on every agreement in bold letters, ", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and two things happen,", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "customers have a better chance of becoming financially literate, ", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it also is an admission of fraud by the credit card companies for all the prior agreements already in place.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So the irony is the credit card companies can't change even if they wanted to.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But where is the outside force to come from to make the obvious happen in regards to those three credit card wanrings?", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Apparently it can't come from the CFPB, ", "type": "fact", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["17"], "text": "which is unfortunate ", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because it turn this ties the courts hands that much more.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1044, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If consumers can receive phone calls on Sundays, there's no reason for them to not accept emails.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Controlling which messages you get and how they are routed and presented to you, including what alerts or sounds they make when received, is only possible with email.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Email is far superior to any other communication medium.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1049, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I believe the most significant problem is due to financial institutions having two systems that are not fully integrated.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One is the system of record that contains account level information ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the second is a charge off system that is used to track events that occur after the account is charged off.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Events that occur on the charge off system are normally not reported to the system of record.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also, charged off system does not or is not used for credit reporting.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The second problem is a result of mergers and/or acquisitions where the financial institution only converts the system of record and not the acquired charge off system.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This leaves a void as to the particular status after the account was charged off.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As accounts are outsourced or purchased ", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "the reliance of information resides on the system of record and NOT the charge off system.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The third problem involves a consumer who has more than one account with the original lender so the risk of one account going to a different agency or debt buyer is highly likely.", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Even if access by the debt buyer and collector is available, the events that took place on the account are normally not recorded in the system of record and the charge off system may have been decommissioned.", "type": "fact", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As to the issue of credit reporting of disputes depends upon whether an agency or debt buyer furnish data to a credit reporting agency.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The amount of consumer data currently and in the past reported to credit reporting agencies may not be accurate specific to charged off accounts", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and to require a chain of title would be expensive ", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the likely hood of accuracy would still not be achieved.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12_14"], "text": "Going forward I think the first focus must be on credit reporting accuracy.", "type": "policy", "id": 15, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1050, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Though I do not agree with \"someone to rack up tens of thousands of dollars of debt and never pay it back\".", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2_3"], "text": "My current standing is that the laws of each and every state allow for higher interest rates to be charged for non-secured debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is because the lenders take more losses ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "\"the risk should be in alignment with the award\".", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In many cases the principal has been paid back in full or the majority of the debt has been paid back.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To allow a \"third party\" to buy it at a significantly reduced price, after the debt has been charged off by the original \"lender/creditor\" AND allow the third party to collect the full alleged balance and interest is not just.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is the way I am leaning at this time.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Explain to me why you or I feel differently?", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
