{"commentID": 1066, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have a fairly common last name,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and my listing in the phone book uses two initials rather than a first name.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I get calls from credit collectors several times a week looking for various people with my last name and one or the other of my two initials.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They are just taking a stab in the dark.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I tell them that I don't live with any other family members and that I have an excellent credit rating, they take me off of their list to of numbers for today's person of interest.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I ask them not to call me at all because I have no other people living with me that they would be looking for, they say that they only had me listed for their person of the day.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Tomorrow my number might pop up as a possibility for tomorrow's person of the day, but they \"can't do anything about tomorrow.\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I actually had a credit collection rep (in India) say that to me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1067, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I'm in the same situation--get calls about numerous people with my last name and one or the other of my two initials.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "None of the people being sought are even related to me, as far as I know, much less living with me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would like to be able to make an official declaration that I have no delinquent debt and that I do not live with anyone who does.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'd be willing to renew the declaration once a year in order to stop receiving these calls that are nothing more than fishing expeditions.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1068, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I would like to see a rule prohibiting debt collectors, debt owners/debt buyers, and other related affiliates from being able to pull a debtor\"s credit report once the debt is officially time-barred and out of SOL.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would also like there to be a rule that specifically distinguishes between a \"hard pull\" and a \"soft pull\" credit inquiry.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have been opted out of promotional marketing via the www.optoutprescreen.com website for years.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I do not have debt and have never had debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What I do have is a common name, ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "and so from time to time I will have various debt collectors and debt buyers \"soft pulling\" my credit reports while they are trying to locate whomever they are trying to locate.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "This should not be allowed even if the debt is still collectable and within the SOL.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "No debt collector has a \"permissible purpose\" to just randomly \"soft pull\" my credit reports just because I have a common name.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10", "9"], "text": "As far as being outside the SOL and time-barred debts: no debt collector and debt owners/debt buyers should be allowed to pull someone\"s credit report ", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since they can't legally sue the debtor outside of the SOL.", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "So there is no need to continue pulling someone\"s credit report.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "As far as the \"hard pull\" \"soft pull\" is concerned: There needs to be specific language that prohibits any debt collectors, debt owners/debt buyers, and other related affiliates from performing \"hard pull\" credit report inquiries.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The FCRA makes it clear what \"permissible purposes\" are ", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but it does not specifically state or distinguish between a \"hard pull\" and a \"soft pull\" credit inquiry.", "type": "fact", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A \"hard pull\" is a consumer-initiated request for an extension of credit.", "type": "fact", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Anything other than a consumer-initiated request is a \"soft pull.\"", "type": "fact", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But time and time again, I have friends, family members, and online forum members, tell me and show me that a debt collector or a debt owner/debt buyer has \"hard pulled\" their credit report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And some of these times are when the debt is time-barred from being outside the SOL and also from the Credit Reporting Time Period.", "type": "testimony", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is unacceptable.", "type": "value", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A \"hard pull\" will decrease a consumers credit score and will be visible for up to 25 months to anyone who does have a legitimate permissible purpose to view that consumer\"s credit report", "type": "fact", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Making a \"hard pull\" on a debtor\"s credit report could be a violation of the FDCPA in the privacy of the debtor.", "type": "fact", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["19", "20"], "text": "Any debt collectors, debt owners/debt buyers, and other related affiliates should be prohibited from doing \"hard pulls\" ", "type": "policy", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the CFPB should make it absolutely clear.", "type": "policy", "id": 22, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.optoutprescreen.com\">www.optoutprescreen.com</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 23, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1069, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Filing suit in the state that the consumer lives in is the most practical.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a state has a large district there is nothing that can be done unless judges want to allow tele-conferencing,, or phone conferencing.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, if that is allowed it should be allowed for both sides provided the evidence of the debt is supplied to the court in advance.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1070, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Let's remember that most debtors have had the original creditor from 2 to 4 collection agencies and the creditors attorneys office before a suit is ever filed.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That process usually takes as much a 2 years or more.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "So it is difficult to think that the courts should make special accommodations for these individuals.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1"], "text": "Every person called into court has had many opportunities to have the debt validated or payment arrangements made prior to a default judgment.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I do believe basic evidence should be supplied.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This would be a statement or bill copy with a matching name of the consumer and proof of address at the time the debt was incurred.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This proof of address could be provided by other confirming data available through skip tracing companies.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There were significant problems with how debt buyers were allowed to file suit and receive default judgments with virtually no evidence.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "So improvements and consistency is needed in evidence but it should also not be expected to show every single bill copy.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1071, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "It is my companies practice to send a validation of debt notice to nearly all accounts placed.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is not required but a best practice.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also believe in most cases the original creditor provides notices to the consumer on their bill if they are going to be referred to collections.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also it is time to be realistic.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Is it possible that a consumer is not notified of a transfer to collections? ", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yes.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But that being said most if not all consumers know they have not paid their bill beyond 30 days and they could be sent to collections.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is time personal responsibility plaid a part in rule making and that the rules apply to the vast majority of circumstances instead of trying to account for the rare occurrences where the process does not work fully.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1072, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "A simple solution to all of the hype about calling cells which is by far the most common means of contacting a consumer these days.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Direct that all telecommunication companies offer a site that allows the agencies to register their phone numbers.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a call is placed to a consumer that does not have unlimited calling or testing then the charges are reversed to the registered phone agency.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1073, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I think the current limits are fine.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The MA rules are too restrictive and frankly could be a disservice to the consumer who wants to try to resolve the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "I do not believe in robo calling but do believe that preview dialing on an automated dialer system should not be prohibited ", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as the agent still has to review the information on the account and push a button to allow the dial.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1075, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Someone keeps calling for a person named Sean, who does not live here and I don't know anyone by that name.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I tell them they have the wrong number, but they continue to call.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They sometimes leave canned messages on my answering machine.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I realize some debtors pretend not to be at the number being called, ", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but these collectors need to verify the information ", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "so they don't keep calling the wrong number.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't know if the debtor gave the wrong number intentionally, or this number was used by someone else before I got it.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is extremely irritating.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And even though the callers do not say they are debt collectors, it is obvious.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1076, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Collectors are not calling me repeatedly ", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they don't believe me.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "They are calling me repeatedly ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because there are so many people with the same last name as me and one of my initials.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is just as annoying to get frequent calls about different individuals as it is to get frequent calls about the same individual.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1077, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I live in Georgia which seems to have laws that are very biased toward the debt owner.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "An example is the statutes of limitations for Mortgage debt.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For instance, if the 1st lienholder forecloses, and you have a 2nd mortgage also, the 2nd remains in effect", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The OCGA states that the statute of limitations for any \" debt instrument under seal\", is 20 years from the date of foreclosure.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The 2nd lien can be sold over and over ", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the last one holding it can come after you for up to 20 years.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In these times when houses are lost due to catastrophic illness, job loss and other situations that not due to the irresponsibility of the homeowner, legislation should be drafted to protect the consumer from financial ruin.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1078, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "State regulations should preempt them from collecting exorbitant returns on such minimal investment (usury!!!).", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Other items to consider pertaining to this issue are : The bad debt", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "buyer does not disclose what he/she purchased the bad debt for.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "This should be disclosed and transparent", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as they have the original debt information, including SSN, phone and financial information.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't begrudge them making a profit ,", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but their predatory practices need to be regulated.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A superior court judge should be able to examine the original transaction,", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "all the documents concerning the purchase of this debt by a third party and determine a fair and equitable payment to resolve the problem, avoiding bankruptcy .", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1079, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I would like to see the CFPB address the issue of their \"phishing\" expeditions , i.e., trolling the phone listings and calling anyone with a similar name.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was listed by my initials, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but with a common last name, I was getting daily calls from debt collectors until I switched my listing to a nickname.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are many comments on this site from people having the same problem,", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "so it's obviously a common practice.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For some strange reason, the folks in the phone centers, react badly when I ask them to explain how my phone number ended up being programmed into their robo dialer.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The usual response has been to hang up on me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "I would also like to see the CFPB address the issue of repeated calls to the wrong person.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I'm not the person of interest on the first call, then I won't be on any subsequent calls.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In my experience with debt collectors, I have reached the conclusion that their are two reasons for repeatedly calling me:", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The people in the call centers are trained not to take No for an answer.", "type": "fact", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "By calling me repeatedly the debt collector is trying to wear me down and get me to pay a debt that isn't mine just to get them to stop calling.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1083, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2"], "text": "I do think a \"free to end user\" would work ", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I don't see any problems with using such a practice or service.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It creates some fairness for the collection companies and will not charge the cell owner if they do not have unlimited calling.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1084, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "These so called free-to-end-user alternatives (if allowed to be used) also need to be regulated.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are huge privacy concerns at stake here.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My friend started texting me on a free texting app, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and then all of a sudden I was begging to be bombarded by SPAM text and SPAM phone calls.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I can't be certain that the Free Text App that my friend was using was selling my phone number to other people, ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but it was a massive coincidence.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Why else are these text apps free?", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "How do they make their money (besides a few embedded ads)?", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Of course these people are selling phone numbers.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My privacy is not for sell.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Nor is my phone number.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The CFPB needs to really think about these so called free-to-end user alternatives and what sort of privacy practices these companies are engaging in, if any.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1085, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Just to make my comment clear: I implied that the Free-to-end-user alternatives (if allowed to be used) need to be regulated ", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so that they are not selling phone numbers and compromising the privacy of the consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My comment made it appear as though I think that the free texting apps (which allow people to text for free) and the free-to-end-user alternatives are the same thing.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They are not.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't want the free-to-end-user alternatives to behave the same as free texting apps -- selling phone numbers to Spammers.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1086, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The Michigan program for handling NSF checks is outlined in Michigan statute (MCL 600.2952).", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The statute provides the exact language to be used in the demand notice to the debtor but does not include the FDCPA Miranda language- which we add to the notice.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We also send a copy of the dishonored check with the notice.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The statute allows the debtor to pay the value of the check plus $25 is paid within 30 days of the notice, or $35 if paid thereafter.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "IF the creditor brings suit (after the first 30 days) they can sue for the value of the check, PLUS damages of 2 times the amount of the dishonored check PLUS $250 in costs.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This may even be used in small claims court.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It seems that the idea is to penalize those who pass bad checks such that merchants will be willing to accept checks from customers.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1087, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Providing too much information in the first notice creates a risk of divulging sensitive personal information to the person who now lives where the actual debtor used to.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "I do think that providing the chain of ownership information (especially original creditor) should be provided for sold debts.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When it comes to medical debts, HIPPA becomes another concern.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "Therefore, specific info on medical debts should only be provided AFTER the collector has verified that they are communicating with the proper party.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1088, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The current validation notice is already too long--bordering on \"boilerplate\".", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To add more language to this would confuse or intimidate the least sophisticated debtor and/or lead them to immediately ask that the creditor cease communication.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The problem with that strategy is that it forces the creditor to file suit, thereby incurring court costs that will be added to the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Instead, debtors should be encouraged to communicate their questions & concerns to the collector who can then (after right-party verification) openly discuss the account & quite possibly answer the debtor's question(s).", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1089, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As for medical collections, I very, very rarely see a legitimate dispute.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": ["1", "2"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most often people are just trying to get the item removed from their credit or scare the collector with threats of FDCPA action.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many of the disputes we receive are copied directly from the internet and contain all kinds of demands for proof that are not required by any state or federal law OR even the rules of evidence during trial.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0", "1", "2"], "text": "CFPB really needs to address this issue and set a clear standard for what is (or is not) a legitimate dispute and how the collector should respond.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1090, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "We instruct our collectors to treat EVERY dispute the same--whether received in writing or over the phone and without regard to when it was received.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "Therefore, I agree that debtors should provide the information referenced in FCRA.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The problem with FCRA disputes is the E-Oscar system that only affords the collector a couple options like \"account information is accurate as of date reported\"\"", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "this doesn't even make sense as a response to the info provided by the debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If E-Oscar is going to be a valid \"dispute\" under FDCPA, that website needs some serious updating including making sure that disputes actually contain the information listed in CFR 1022.43(d) and allowing collectors to transmit the actual contract/itemized statements/etc back to the debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1091, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Any FTC rule regarding verification should absolutely include an exception for frivolous and irrelevant disputes", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because there are way too many websites out there providing sample dispute letters and the advice to keep using them that the process is abused by enough debtors that we now have a standard letter to address this issue.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1092, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I had a debt collector tell me they told me that if I'd make a payment right then they'd make a payment plan.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This was an Amercian Express collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once I made the payment they said they're supervisor would have to approve it and they weren't there. But that she would call back at 7pm MST to make the arrangement.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Needless to say no one called back", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "and American Express would not make arrangements with me ", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they said I was able to pay that amount so I shouldn't need arrangements.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_4"], "text": "I was so dumbfounded by the collection practices of American Express.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It was from their internal collections department.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1093, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The CFPB should clarify whether \"verify\" means verify that you are a legitimate collection agency (not a scam) OR does it mean to prove the legitimacy of the account relative to the debtor's objections.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If is the former, some basic information relative to the account--contract, itemized statements, or any other identifying information that only the creditor would have access to would suffice.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If CFPB wants \"verify\" to answer every single objection a debtor can cook up, a collector could never move forward without spending hundreds of hours normally reserved for litigation.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As to a time frame on answering, I think the current system of stopping collection action until verification is provided is appropriate.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Normally, sending the information to the debtor is not the hard part.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Getting the info from the creditor and then circling back around to this particular account is what takes the time.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't think disputes should be limited to the first 30 days, but should be prohibited once suit has been filed.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The Court rules and discovery process provide the debtor all the access to this information they could ever need or want", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the provide this access under pretty strict penalties from the Court if the creditor/plaintiff does not provide the info requested.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1094, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have a hard time believing that a debt collection company \"treat[s] EVERY dispute the same\"", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "when debt collectors seem to blatantly disregard a dispute that has the appearance of being \"copied directly from the internet.\"", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Consumer advocates are trying to educate consumers, debtors, and alleged debtors with information on how to handle debt collectors or how to handle their particular situation.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We are try to give them relevant links to FDCPA, FCRA, HIPPA, and various form letters that can help them communicate with debt collectors.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There is nothing wrong with form letters.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But there is everything wrong with debt collectors disregaring certain letters just because they don't like that it came from a consumer advocate source.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Debt collectors operating legally and with nothing to hide should never treat form letters as something to throw in the trash.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You seem to be saying that debt collectors will only want to communicate with consumers who are misinformed and don't know what their rights are, rather than communicate with a consumer who knows the laws and the appropriate ways to address a letter of dispute.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1095, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If our client(s) can't provide any verification of the debt, we close the account and send the debtor a letter that we are doing so.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Note: this has only happened once or twice in 20 years.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "an unresolved dispute account should NOT be sold.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If so, seller should be liable.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1097, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The problem is not with a form letter of dispute.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The problem is that these websites and unreasonable letters lead unsophisticated debtors to believe that a creditor has to provide extraordinary proof that simply is not required.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "'stopwithspoofedcallerID' (if that IS your real name) is correct that no legitimate dispute should be ignored, regardless of the form, but nor should debtors be allowed to abuse the system by repeatedly asking for proofs that are not required.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1098, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I think the \"unless\" part of the rule about contacting a person more than once should be scrapped.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They should not be allowed to contact anyone (other than the debtor him/herself) more than once.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the person (usually the innocent family member) they contact to try to locate the debtor is willing to give out contact info, fine.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If not, whether they have it or not is beside the point.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "They should not be forced in the middle.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is not their debt, or in any way their responsibility.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And when collectors claim they can't give their name or a return phone number to be passed on because of privacy reasons, how can they expect someone else to share personal contact info with a stranger?", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1099, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_2"], "text": "A collector contacting a consumer via email, voice mail, or text message should identify themselves and say what they are calling about (e.g. overdue ABC account) without details of amount, account #, etc.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So what if a third party might possibly conclude this person has debt?", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Without details they still don't know anything.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "I personally never return any calls about \"an important business matter\":", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "if you don't tell me who you are or what you are calling about, I consider it spam.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If you call in good faith to clear up an outstanding balance for ABC company, then you should say so.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's the ones that are trying to scam consumers that give as little detail as possible in hope that someone panics and fills in the blanks for them.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1101, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I'm not sure a registration system for debt collectors really addresses the issue.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'm not exactly sure how the registration system would operate.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In MA, consumers can check online to see whether a debt collector is licensed to practice in the state,", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "many just don't know about the website or on a more basic level don't know that the debt collector has no right to try to collect from them.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Is the registration system meant to displace state laws requiring licensing of debt collectors in the individual states?", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "I hope that's not the case", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since states have a strong interest in regulating debt collectors for the protection of its consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1108, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "it should be a fdcpa violation to spoof a debt collector's phone number on the caller ID.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Either no number on the caller ID or a number linked back to the collection agency.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1109, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "There are still too often abuses by debt collectors in regard to time-barred debts.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Zombie debt collectors who use partial payments, acknowledgement of the debt in writing, or other tactics are effectively hard-wiring around the laws having to do with the statute of limitations.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": ["2"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have witnessed situations where consumers were effectively tricked into setting up a series of payments on a long time-barred debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Collectors continue to take advantage of consumers for whom ESL and also those who are unsophisticated and possibly naive.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1110, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["7"], "text": "Given the highly coercive consequences of having negative information reported to or by CRAs on consumer credit reports, I think it is reasonable that a debt not be deemed \"verified\" or \"substantiated\" unless and until there's a final non-appealable order, but only in circumstances where the consumer has timely disputed the existence or the amount of the debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Currently, if you dispute a debt, the debt collector reports you to the CRAs ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and your credit standing is adversely impacted; i.e., the damage is already done at that point.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In other words, the notation on the credit report that the debt is disputed by the consumer is largely ignored by potential lenders, employers, landlords, etc.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1", "3"], "text": "Thus, disputing the debt does nothing to prevent harm to the consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debt collector and creditor threaten to report you to the CRAs as a coercive tactic to force you to pay a debt", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "even though you might legitimately not owe the debt or the amount claimed to be owed.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8", "9_10"], "text": "As for my proposal, I do not think this will lead to more litigation. Just the opposite.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a consumer doesn't timely dispute the debt, then the debt can be deemed verified or substantiated.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If, however, the debt is timely disputed, creditors and debt collectors will have to evaluate whether to initiate litigation and weigh the likelihood of prevailing at trial ", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and this may cause creditors and debt collectors to be more judicious about which debts to take to trial.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This proposal would also protect consumers from having their credit standing negatively impacted until after it is conclusively determined that a purported debt that is disputed is in fact owed and the amount of such debt is conclusively determined.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As an alternative to my initial proposal, a rule could be adopted that would impose significant statutory penalties, treble damanages and recovery of attorney's fees against creditors, debt collectors and CRAs in the event the consumer can prove either the disputed debt doesn't exist or the amount of the debt is less than that claimed to be owed.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This approach, however, places the burden of proof on the consumer", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I feel strongly that the burden of proof should be on the creditors and debt collectors to affirmatively prove the existence and amount of any disputed debt before a consumer's credit report is adversely impacted.", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1111, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Once the consumer is located then nearbys, neighbors, relatives, prior used phone numbers may be abused by collectors to harass and embarrass consumers, or even to compel a relative or other third party to pay the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "Violations of the FDCPA should be treated as serious breaches of law.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1112, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Minors are not normally eligible to enter contracts or take on the obligation of credit arrangements,", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "so this would seem necessarily rare.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Regardless, every effort should be made and maintained to protect consumers from mistaken disclosure of personal business.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1113, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "paythefiddler, It's not just innocent family members that debt collectors go after, it's also perfect strangers.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": ["1_4"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have a common last name, no debts, and have been the target of many debt collectors.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All of the deadbeats have had my common last name and first initial.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Once a debt collector has me on their hit list, they don't stop calling until I sent them a cease-communication letter.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They want me to pay the debt to get them to stop.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1114, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2", "3"], "text": "I would like to see strict regulation of the so-called \"skip-trace\" vendors.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These are the companies that debt collectors and others hire to provide them with contact information.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "From my own personal experience (common last name, many debt collectors after me), I can say that I believe that I'm at the mercy of these vendors.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They gather all sorts of information about people without verifying any of it, as far as I can tell.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": ["4_6"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One debt collector told my state's Attorney General that they hired one of these vendors who provided my phone number as a valid contact for someone with my last name and first initial.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This person was a stranger to me,", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but the debt collector wanted me to pay the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "8"], "text": "I think that these vendors should be strictly regulated and use a research tool other then the phone book to gather their information.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They should not be able to provide \"valid\" information unless it really is valid.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1118, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Unless and until debt collection practices have greater transparency for consumers there will be abuses and misunderstandings regarding legal liability.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's too much a pat answer to say consumers should seek legal advice.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1", "3"], "text": "Collectors should be required to say with a certain level of supported certainty whether the debt is valid or not.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Collectors should not be allowed to rely merely on a borrower's \"moral obligation\" to repay the debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Financially disadvantaged, naive, and gullible consumers, and specifically those individuals on fixed, limited incomes, i.e., older Americans, ESL citizens, etc. are especially vulnerable.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1119, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_2"], "text": "In the case of medical debt, the statement should inform the consumer of the date and location of the service provided, including the name of the doctor who was in charge of the case (rather than a consultant or firm that never contacted the consumer) or the commonly used name of the location (such as a hospital or clinic) where the service was performed.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In my experience, cost-conscious consumers who are wary of scams have declined to pay legitimate medical debt ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they did not recognize the debt and could not get an answer to the basic question, \"Why do I owe this money?\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When the debt is unexplained, it is prudent to refuse to send money,", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "yet when the debt is in fact legitimate, the consumer may suffer severe penalties for failure to pay.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A validation notice for medical debt should not simply repeat numerical codes or obscure abbreviations.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "It should state, \"You were billed on (DATE) when you went to (PLACE).\"", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If other debts related to the same visit have been paid, the letter should say so, e.g., \"You already paid for other services during this visit, but you still owe...\" Or, \"Your insurance paid for some of the costs of this visit, but you still owe....\"", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This issue is related to the absurd complexities of medical billing,", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but those complexities should not be used to conceal the origin of a debt from a consumer.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1120, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Information about the source of the debt (such as the date of the service) can be provided without infringing on the patient's privacy.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "No one should be asked to pay a debt without first being told why they owe the money.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "This is esp. true of medical debts, ", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "which are notoriously complex and apparently redundant, with many charges occurring on the same occasion.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1121, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2"], "text": "If this is an area that the CFPB is interested in regulating, I believe it will be necessary to initiate cooperative actions with local State judiciaries.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Because the CFPB is a federal agency,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "it doesn't have authority to tell State governments (including the judicial branch) how to operate or how to interpret its own law.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Since some states are already taking steps in this direction ( like New York),", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "it is likely that the CFPB would find positive reception toward this effort.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But trying to accomplish change through federal rulemaking is not an option in this particular area.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1122, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "This is not an appropriate requirement", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because not all states have licensing or registration for debt collectors.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1123, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "But they also can't send you a signed paper for something you agreed to online, or over the phone.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "So few people actually put a pen to paper these days to sign a formal written agreement.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "So that's an unfair requirement when it doesn't always exist.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1125, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have never applied for credit in any way other by paper application,", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and everyone I have ever owed money to has tons of paperwork.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0", "1"], "text": "I don't know how it works when you apply electronically,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but what's to prevent someone from saying they are owed money?", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "The burden of proof is going to have to be on the creditor,", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and if they aren't getting paper signatures, they'd better have some pretty good proof otherwise.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Meanwhile, if you say they wouldn't lie about it, I would love to sell you my ocean front property in Nebraska.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1126, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "While Alternative 1 seems simplest,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "there are hidden complications.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Who defines what \"principal\" means?", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "With revolving credit accounts, interest accrues (as finance charges) and is rolled into the balance.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "So does \"principal\" mean only the part of the balance that was charged by the cardholder (very difficult, if not impossible, for a collector to calculate) or the total charged off amount?", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I understand that it can be difficult when dealing with different kinds of debts.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But I don't think this option will work for a large portion of consumer debt.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11", "8"], "text": "Alternative 2 doesn't work", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because who defines when a consumer \"defaults\" on an account?", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many of us have missed a payment here or there,", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but we get back on track.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9_10"], "text": "So it's too ambiguous.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6", "7"], "text": "That leaves Alternative 3 as the most feasible,", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but what about accounts that never had a periodic statement or billing statement?", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I propose breaking down the total amount by stating the amount owed on the last statement issued by the original creditor, or, if no statement was ever issued, the original amount of the debt when incurred, and then an itemization of all debits and credits applied since that balance.", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1127, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The case law related to this portion of the FDCPA has made it risky for collectors to include anything other than exactly what the FDCPA says.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2_3"], "text": "However, I don't think the law, as written, is easy to understand.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For example - the first sentence says unless you dispute the debt, it will be considered valid (\"dispute\" and \"valid\" aren't defined), but then goes on to say what the creditor will do if you notify them in writing.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "So if the consumer only disputes verbally, what rights do they have, if any?", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I think the law should be clarified,", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6", "7"], "text": "and then I think the CFPB should create a uniform \"Summary of Consumer Rights\" that can be required to be included with all initial letters from collectors.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That way, debt collectors don't have to worry about overshadowing and trying to fit everything onto one page, or with the tricky area of providing legal advice by interpreting the FDCPA for the consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also, consumers can get a consistent message from all collectors.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If there is a concern about it being separate from the initial letter from the collector, there can be a mandatory one-line disclosure providing a link to a CFPB website with that Summary of Consumer Rights.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1128, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "This proposed rulemaking is not about credit reporting.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I understand that people have significant concerns about their credit reports.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "But that belongs in a reform of the Fair Credit Reporting Act, not the FDCPA.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Inserting credit reporting rules into the FDCPA would make things difficult for debt collectors who don't report to credit reporting agencies at all.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1129, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I think it would.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I work for an attorney at a debt collection law firm", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I think this would make things a lot easier and simpler.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1130, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Credit bureaus are responsible for 95% of identity theft and inaccurate consumer credit files.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's because their revenue comes from businesses who pay for access to their databases including phony ones.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have a letter from a credit bureau that says the only thing they do to investigate/verify accuracy is ask the entity that initially reported the information if it's true.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4", "5"], "text": "New rules have to put tighter restrictions and procedures on credit bureaus", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they are the root of the actual problem.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Secondly, because they are private companies who should not be able to collect or retain any financial information without consumers permission.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Submission of proof of debt or other evidence/documents should be required.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Retention of the identity of the actual [business] persons reporting the account information should be required.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Credit bureaus and debt collectors should not be allowed to sell lists of accounts especially after the accounts are disputed. One creditor, one debt collector.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All debt collectors should be required to register on a national database, including phone numbers, that's publicly available online which they must update within 5 business days regarding any changes.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All lawyers should not be banned from becoming debt collectors.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Here is a a group of people that are trained, licensed in their State, ", "type": "fact", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they lie to circumvent the law and the courts.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "At the heart of the mortgage fiasco were unethical lawyers who acted strictly for greed.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["15"], "text": "None of them were prosecuted or disbarred", "type": "fact", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they hid themselves as representing lenders.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1131, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I meant to say, \"all lawyers should be banned from being debt collectors.\"", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They are unethical and work strictly out of greed to circumvent the laws that are supposed to protect consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Verification of debts should require the creditor to provide written proof of the initial debt instrument with the consumers' signature.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "There should be a notarized statement of authenticity along with it.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This gives a consumer the documents to file a civil suit for fraud, if needed.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1132, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "New rules should allow consumers to resolve, discuss, or negotiate the matter strictly with the creditor.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In other words, consumers should be told that they can refuse to speak to debt collectors about their account(s).", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1134, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "just the phone number should show up on the called ID.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The consumer can google the number and figure out if they want to talk or call back the number.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "More importantly, it gives attorneys the ability to make fdcpa claims against collection agencies", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since we know who is calling.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1135, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["3", "5"], "text": "When creditor or servicing company doesn't \"credit\" a payment after receiving it and then getter further proof but still puts the victim in arrears or foreclosure, there should be fines regardless of whether it is a \"mistake\" or \"criminal act.\"", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A grace period can be allowed", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "but after that slap on the fines. and keep them coming every week they don't correct their problem.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Basically by not crediting payment they are stealing that payment.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "This should apply to any \"mistakes\" or unethical practices such as deliberately or \"mistakenly\" changing around escrow, interest, principal, late fees, insurance and so forth to the profit of the collector.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Heavy fines will take away the profit motive and such \"mistakes\" and unethical practices will greatly decrease.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1136, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "A central system has privacy concerns", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it would be useful only if it included verification of who picked up the document and when.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Instead creditors and debt buyers should be mandated to allow secure document uploading to their own website with official notification that the document has been reviewed.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have a pending case of a company misapplying my payments,", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had to send many registered letters and faxes with proof of payment which cost some money and time.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "With this company anything you send them \"doesn't exist\" unless you have verifiable proof they have been forced to accept it.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It would be a lot easier for the consumers to just upload the documentation and get verification the company reviewed it which can be used for a complaint.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There should be penalties of fines for not marking an uploaded document as \"reviewed\" after a period of time.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1137, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The Consumer Finance Protection Bureau needs to have a large core of undercover agents that get jobs at collection agencies, credit agencies and servicers.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "These agents need full federal law enforcement powers with guns and badges", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so they can perp-walk suspects out of their offices and take them to federal holding facilities for trial when they have proof of criminal activity.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Currently it seems many creditors, servicers and debt collectors consider themselves above the law.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There's only two ways to discourage that thinking and that's jail time and/or fines.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After conviction, victims should receive a framed and signed (first name or nickname of the agent) photograph of the perp-walk.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They usually don't get their money back", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but that's something they will treasure.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1140, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "When a debt collection company (Bayview) took over servicing of my mortgage, I began receiving phone calls at work and on my cell phone about my mortgage payments", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "even thought they were not late.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This included robo-calls.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was told this was 'standard' and to ignore these phone calls,", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I really got angry and filed a BBB complaint in the state of one office.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was never late with one payment,", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and our mortgage was not in debt collection.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Bayview may be a debt collector,", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they need to keep those services separate from their mortgage services.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Calling people at work, robo-calls, and harassing them when they do not have delinquent debts should be against the law.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1141, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I am dealing with a debt collection company who is also a mortgage company.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They are having issues separating the two types of services.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They are also having an incredible amount of IT (web) problems.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": ["3", "4"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Their website is down, or only their staff can see it, or they cannot upload my account information, etc.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Other IT issues include their System, which \"tells them\" it has mailed me documents, but apparently does not really do it.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My point is, I am able to capture a lot of this using ScreenShots and electronic communication, providing a very detailed log.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have sent my screenshots of the errors I saw on my account screen to their IT staff,", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it may have helped resolve their website issues a few weeks later.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I would highly recommend the use of electronic media as a formal way to communicate on both ends.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1142, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The agency I work for is small and follows FDCPA to the letter of the law.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And yet we are still sued constantly by attorneys representing debtors.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These attorneys count on the fact that it's less costly to settle than to go to court to prove that we have not violated the law.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Our retail division is in trouble", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because we've recently lost our two largest clients -- for this reason.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They're now getting slapped with bogus lawsuits as well.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "People don't even have to pay their bills any more;", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they just send a \"cease and desist\" letter, hire an attorney, and wait for a settlement to roll in.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All this will lead to are more stringent rules around extending credit, which is not a good thing for the economy.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If we keep going down this slope, the only people who will be able to get credit will be those who don't need it.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1144, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "This is a fantastic idea.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Right now, debt buyers buy debt for an average price of 4 cents on the dollar.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many debts are bought for 2-4 cents on the dollar", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and many other debts are given away for free.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I were an original creditor, would like to get the most money I could for a debt owed to me.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And so if I could get 10 cents on the dollar directly from the debtor, rather than 4 cents on the dollar from a debt buyer, then I would see no reason not to offer a significantly reduced debt settlement rate to the debtor (or as you call it, letting consumers bid on their own debt).", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Right now, original creditors offer no significant reduced rate to debtor before selling for 4 cents on the dollar.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most creditors barely even offer debtors 10% off the debt as a settlement offer.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sure, a creditor could more quickly offload portfolios to debt buyers by selling them at 4 cents on the dollar.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But creditors could also make way more money offering a onetime chance at 10 cents on the dollar (or something really attractive but still more than 4 cents on the dollar).", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Perhaps the CFPB should make a rule that allows consumers/debtors the chance to receive a onetime offer that is valid for only X amount of days (maybe 45 days) from the date of the letter sent from their creditors of a significantly reduced rate.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The offer would only be valid for a short amount of time and would also inform the consumer that, should the consumer not accept the offer, the creditor would then turn it over to a debt buyer.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["13", "14"], "text": "This letter would only be sent if the creditor\"s intentions are to sell the debt and not just another attempt to collect.", "type": "policy", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So that this way it gives the consumer one final chance to clear the debt owed", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the creditors also have less loss and more profits and would be able to lend to more consumers, give better rates to consumers, and stimulate the economy.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Because more money that is changing hands at higher values (10 cents on the dollar vs. 4 cents on the dollar) instead of sitting in the accounts receivable section waiting to be collected (one day, if ever) stimulates the economy.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This rule would not negatively impact anything (or anyone) and only positively impacts everyone.", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One minor impact might be on the debt collection industry possibly receiving less debt in their portfolios that they buy,", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but this minor impact is offset by the large positive impacts on the economy.", "type": "value", "id": 18, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1145, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, I do think your restrictions on workplace calls per week would be helpful,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I do not see any information requiring details on the content of Robo-Calls. ", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For example, the calls I referred to earlier included robo-calls telling me that I had \"messages\" waiting for me in my Bayview Account, and to access these messages, I needed to call a special phone number.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Well, this was a bunch of baloney", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "it was just a recording wanting to know where I had sent my mortgage payment", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had not set up an electronic deposit yet, like they wanted,", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so they assumed I was skipping a payment).", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8", "9"], "text": "I believe those robo-calls were fraudulent and misleading,", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "particularly since I was never late on any payments, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I never had any \"message\" waiting for me. Just a robotic collection message.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I received three of these messages", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they are still saved in my cell phone voice mail.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1146, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I was flat out lied to by the attorney for a credit card company who brought a small claims suit against me. ", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I disputed the debt (and still do even after they garnished my wages", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they intimidated me into a payment arrangement then lied to me and said there was no court date anymore since I \"settled\".", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was skeptical and called the clerk of court's office only to find out they lied", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I did need to show up.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I showed up for the court date, even as I argued that this court had no jurisdiction over me because I never lived in that county", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but no-one even the clerk's office would listen to me", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I was denied the right to go before a judge.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was only given an opportunity to talk to the attorney for the credit card company and sign papers saying we had a payment arrangement.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Long story short, I made 1 of 2 payments then lost my job.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I called them immediately to tell them I would make the 2nd and final payment 2-3 weeks late because I had to wait for a final check.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They told me okay,", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but unbeknownst to me,they went back to court without me and got a default judgement for $1600 on what would have been a $709 payment.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "iI never got notice of the court hearing ", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "nor did I ever get a copy of the judgement.", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I didn't find out about it until I got a wage garnishment notice from my new employer 2 1/2 years later....VERY humiliating!", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My employer got the wage garnishment notice a week before I did", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["16"], "text": "so I couldn't even dispute it before my employer was involved.", "type": "testimony", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Second, I called the clerk of court's office in that county (3 hours from my home) and argued that you can't go to court without giving me a chance to defend myself and I shouldn't be forced to drive 3 hours each way to a county I never lived in.", "type": "testimony", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was told by the clerk's office that they can file it wherever they want and I have to show up.", "type": "testimony", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I asked \"So if they wanted to file this in California to be jerks you're telling me I'd have to get on a plane and fly to California to defend a $709 lawsuit\"\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "She said \"Yes.\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "THAT HAS TO CHANGE.", "type": "policy", "id": 22, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1147, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2"], "text": "I support these restrictions on robo-calling and any calls during the work hours.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "With respect to robo-calls, any robo-calls that are misleading should be restricted.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is, a robo-call that tells you that you have a message or an account update, and the only way to get it is to call a special number with an extension, but when you call, it is just the same message asking where your payment is, is a waste of the consumer's time and the consumer's cellular resources (two phone calls, one received, one sent).", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1148, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2_3"], "text": "Please consider robo-calls when developing rules for this section.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "See my comments about robo-callers leaving messages on cell phones under robo-calling.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I understand the need to protect privacy,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "but this is not the answer.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The messages left for me on my cell phone could have been returned by anyone with access to the cell phone (family members, snoopy friends) and information on a supposedly late payment would be disclosed by the robo-caller.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Robo-calling does not have the consumer's privacy in mind.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1149, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Yes. I fell onto hard times during a divorce and found out a few years ago that my dad (whom I haven't lived with for 20+ years) receives so many debt collection calls for me every day he quit answering his home phone.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is unacceptable.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "We cannot even figure out how they got his phone number", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I never lived at that address at any point while I had those credit cards and he never co-signed any loans or credit cards with me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The only connection we can come up with is that my stepmom co-signed a short term furniture loan for me 20 years ago when I was just out of college and that maybe somehow her name is tied to my credit report in some way", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "although I've never seen it on my credit reports.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is now 6 years after I went through my divorce ", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and he told me a few months ago he still gets several calls per week for me from debt collectors.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Personally, I don't think they should be allowed to call ANY number for more than 3 months without successful contact with the debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Clearly, they don't have proof they've got the right number ", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and all they're doing by calling the same unverified number for 6 years is harrassing an innocent party.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1150, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I guess I should also have clarified in my previous comment that I have made attempts to deal with creditors directly if I know who they are and who they claim to be representing", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "but my personal perception is they PREFER to continue contacting 3rd parties", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they hope I'll just pay them to avoid the public humiliation.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4", "8"], "text": "And in regards to a comment I read here that creditors can call a 3rd party again if they have a reasonable belief that the person knows how to contact the debtor, I disagree with that entirely.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "First of all, I'm not aware of any law that compels a 3rd party to provide current contact information for a debtor,", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "so even if they do know where that debtor is, they don't deserve to be harassed daily for months or years as punishment for not offering up that information.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many people don't want to be involved", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and no law that I know of says they have to if they aren't a party to the debt.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Secondly, there is no clear and concise way I know of that a creditor can prove what was a reasonable belief.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "My in-laws have no idea how to reach my sister-in-law", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because she wants it that way.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "They haven't spoken in 3 years", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I don't see that changing.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "You can't assume that certain relatives MUST know where a debtor is.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1151, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I also wanted to add that because debt collectors know they can hire robo service companies to false service,", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "they aren't going to negotiate in good faith.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Just as appalling for me was the judge agreeing that the one service I challenged was a false service, but allowing the case to go forward anyways.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sure, people can lie and say they were not served when they were served,", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but the very day I was in court contesting the service, a person who spoke before me made the comment that they found their service document on their door step when they got home.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This means the servicers are lying in court documents,", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": ["4"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and nobody seems to care.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I still want redress on these two cases,", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I want to be able to file an errors and omissions claim with both debt collectors insurance company for lying on court documents.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And if it is not a law, then isn't it time that debt collection companies carry errors and omissions insurance?", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1152, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "This is an awesome suggestion!", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Your suggestion \"I don't think they should be allowed to call ANY number for more than 3 months without successful contact with the debtor\" is spot on!", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "And I can't believe that no one else has ever suggested this before.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4_7"], "text": "3 months (or whatever an appropriate time limit is) would reduce the constant harassment that I and many other innocent parties receive.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This morning I received an illegal phone call from a collector at 6:17 AM with a spoofed phone number for a person that I have never known", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I have told these collectors this several times already.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They have the wrong number.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And I am tired of this.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "The CFPB should absolutely implement a rule that forces unsuccessful contact to 3 months.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1154, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have had several doctor/laboratory debts placed on my credit report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These are debts that I never rec'd a bill for or even a phone call from the hospital or facility.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have very good health insurance that paid over $14k when I had my baby...", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "3 months go by and I start getting notified by my credit monitoring agency that my credit score is going down.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "things such as a (pediatric audiology test $83) when my baby was 1 day old.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "apparently the audiologist doesnt bill through the hospital....", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "subsequently, they also dont bill the patients..", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they outsource their billing to a 3rd party collection agency who immediately reports it to all 3 credit bureaus.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Maybe i missed that forumn on this sight,", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A company can send a $100 bill to Transunion and say I owe it, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and BAM...my credit score takes a 10 point dive.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9_10"], "text": "Agencies should not be able to put something on your credit report without first having not only validated the debt and provided any and all documents that prove you owe the debt, but they must be required to have attempted to collect the debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have had businesses tell em that its cheaper to put the bill directly on your credit report than it is to hire a 3rd party to collect the debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is a horrible injustice to the people who pay their bills, maintain health iunsurance and who will pay their outstanding debts.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The system is set up to force the consumer to prove their innocence (if you will) verus the creditor proving they are owed a debt.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1157, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Currently, CRA's deny responsibility for \"reporting\" inaccurate information given to them.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "CRA's should be liable for both actual and punitive damages caused by \"reporting\" inaccurate information.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1158, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "There's nothing in place for any of them, unless (often several years down the road) a judge decides to throw them out.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is yet another consequence of the litigious society in which we currently live.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't have the answers,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but it seems that someone in government or law should be able to do something about unscrupulous attorneys who create a claim out of thin air just to make a buck.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1159, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Not every debt collection agency is like that.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The one I work for certainly isn't.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1164, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As a college grad since 1979 and a first-time homebuyer, I have found widespread violations of the FDCPA among the creditors and their outsourced private collections agencies.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I've also found and been a victim of deception in the debt collection practice observing poor record keeping on the part of all parties.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We must first examine debt collection from a derivative and forensic viewpoint; corporate finance, federally/state funded institutions and their debt obligations.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "GAAP allows for the write-off of old debts.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yet and still the creditors outsource collection agencies to collect debts the creditor has written off of their balance sheet.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "The debtor is always subject to the debt", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because the collection agency takes a percentage", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Then comes the finance charge (interest) and late payment charges.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "In essence, the original debt remains the same", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because the debtor is only paying commission, interest and late charges.", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I attended a Texas private college (state funded) that lost its accreditation for mismanagement of funds.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My financial aid consisted of the BEOG, NDSL, Stafford Loan and the Merit Scholarship.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The school policy was to clear the balance of my bill before my grades were released.", "type": "fact", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Each grade period, whatever the balance was, my Mom used the funds she had left from our Social Security Income (father deceased 1972) after paying monthly expenses to send to me for my grades to be released.", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After my marriage, the Dept of Ed (Higher Ed) offset two years of joint tax returns, private collection agencies constantly called.", "type": "fact", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I was employed, I voluntarily paid $50/mo. for two years on this debt of which the principle was $4,650.", "type": "testimony", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Even after over 30 yrs., the debt was recorded as a Federal Abstract of Judgement at the county registrar (filed by private attorneys) as if I still owe the debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["16"], "text": "I wasn't properly served.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The process server (whomever it was) left a large manila envelope.", "type": "testimony", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Now the debt has been turned over to the Dept. of Justice in the State of Michigan.", "type": "testimony", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My point is that there is a widespread conflict of interest among the creditor and those outsourced by the creditor for debt collection.", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most, if not all of these organizations are operated by taxpayer funding.", "type": "fact", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The taxpayers are the ultimate creditors.", "type": "value", "id": 22, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1165, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Technology does not allow debtors or alleged debtors to distinguish land lines from cellphones of debt collectors; whether private or federal.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There appears to be a double standard between the debtor and collector.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have received calls after business hours and sometimes even on a Sunday from a mortgage servicer, whom I will not disclose.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This particular servicer has even left an anonymous type of flyer (one that can be hung on a doorknob) with instructions to call the specific servicer's customer service phone number; without disclosing the name of the servicer, although I was already familiar with the phone number.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "I would classify this as mail fraud", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because it bypassed the mail system.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The same scenario with the service of process regarding my old school loan.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The service of process bypassed the mail system", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These are both issues that should be resolved collectively by and among the FCC, FTC and DOJ (not all inclusive).", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A debt collector can call the debtor from a phone number outside of the collector's company", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so it won't be included in the company's phone log.", "type": "fact", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the debtor attempts to return the phone call, the number is either inoperable or not able to receive incoming calls.", "type": "fact", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Collectors may even call a debtor in order to attempt them to give personal information about lowering the interest rate on their credit card (even if the debtor doesn't have a credit card).", "type": "fact", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is obvious or apparent that there may be a credit card floating around in the debtor's name unknowingly.", "type": "fact", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These are all scenarios I have experienced.", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We haven't gotten to the subject of sharing a debtor's information among the debtor's financial institution and the financial institution's correspondent institutions and investment advisor affiliates and other business combinations of the debtor (public utilities companies, mortgage servicers, insurance companies, pension fund mgrs, etc...", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1166, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I had surgery at a hospital in 2006.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have 2 forms of insurance, both excellent.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Therefore I rarely have a medical bill to pay, or it is for a very small amount.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sometime after the surgery (I do not recall how long after the procedure), there were repeated calls to my phone by an actual person who said, \" This is (first name), give me a call at (phone number)\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Since we did not know the person,", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "no one called back.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "We thought we should report it to the DONOTCALL list,", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but we had no company name to report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Finally I happened to answer the phone when that number appeared and the male voice said, \"you know what this is about, right?\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I said, \"no\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He said, \" you have an overdue charge with (hospital name). You haven't paid your bill. I work with a bill collection company\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I said \"I have never received a bill.\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He said \"really?\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I said , \"yes\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He said, \"Call accounting at the hospital\".", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I called the hospital and they said to talk to my insurance company.", "type": "testimony", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I called my 2nd insurance company and they said both the first and the second insurance company had paid the hospital.", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The 2nd insurance company said I did owe money on the bill, something like $1.08.", "type": "testimony", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A bill collection company had been hired to collect $1.08 for which I had never received a bill!", "type": "testimony", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I asked both insurance companies to send me additional copies of the Explanation of Benefits.", "type": "testimony", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I received the copies, I sent them to the billing department of the hospital with a check for the amount that the 2nd insurance company said I owed.", "type": "testimony", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I never did receive a bill.", "type": "testimony", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Nor was i warned it might go to a collection agency.", "type": "testimony", "id": 22, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A collection agency was hired for an amount just slightly over $1.00.", "type": "testimony", "id": 23, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Because of this experience, I do not plan ever to use this hospital again if I can help it.", "type": "value", "id": 24, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My family has had referrals to doctors associated with this hospital,", "type": "testimony", "id": 25, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I always try to get a doctor who is not associated with it.", "type": "value", "id": 26, "evidence": null}]}
