{"commentID": 1169, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Recently I received an \"offer\" from a firm indicating it would approve a new Visa or MasterCard account if I agreed to assume responsibility for a debt allegedly owed to another credit card firm.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The first firm, which apparently was the original creditor, apparently sold the alleged debt to a third party.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It was this third party that was making the \"offer\" to open a new credit account.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Of course, there was a \"hook.\"", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I agreed to assume financial responsibility for the alleged debt and if the third party opened the new account, the credit limit would be for the alleged debt plus a significant \"service charge\" for the transaction.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The finance charge was listed at 29%.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Another questionable aspect of the matter was no guarantee a credit line would remain open as the account was paid down.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "Thus, if the initial \"credit line\" was $500 to cover the outstanding debt and service fee, as the balance were paid down and/or off, the credit limit could be decreased", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so as to prevent it from being used for new purchases.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "Obviously, I shredded the \"offer\" package", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as I did not owe the initial debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I wonder how many people will consider this a relief of some type and agree to the \"offer.\"", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1171, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "One issue I am experiencing is that since I allegedly received an overpayment of wages from a former employer,", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "I have NONE of the consumer protections that I should.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I fall into the gray space of being a consumer", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and my alleged (and incorrectly so) debt is considered \"commercial\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "3"], "text": "and therefore there are absolutely NO regulations on the activities of the debt collector.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The individual assigned to my account has repeatedly revealed to a third party that he is trying to collect a debt from me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The alleged debt has never been substantiated,", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1172, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Some years ago, a debt collector was trying to collect a debt for an emergency room visit that included foot/leg xrays.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The problem was that the only time I had ever been to the hospital in question was a worker's compensation covered workplace injury and it involved only my hand (sliced open, six stitches).", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had contacted the collection agency and informed them that I did not owe anything and the circumstances of the visit.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Although that did not work, once I contacted all three credit bureaus with the same information, the debt collector was unable to verify the debt", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "and they removed it from my credit report - and stopped contacting me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1173, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I'm concerned that the proposed rules are just a back door to allow Director Cordray to find out about my special toy collection.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He has sent me writings demanding my special toy collection,", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "and I'm afraid that now that he's Director of the CFPB, he's using his power to come after my favorite toy, Mr. Longblack.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1178, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "When anyone makes a demand for payment from another party, it is incumbent on that person to produce the evidence to support such demand and not up to the second party to produce evidence that he is not liable for such alleged debt.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Otherwise, anyone can create trouble and misery for any person out of mischief, ill-intent or out to make some fast money for himself or even to defame the second party,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as proper businesses are adverse to bad publicity.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "If the first party claims to represent a third party to collect debt for that third party, then the first party (collector) must produce evidence that he is authorized by the third party to collect a debt for the third party alone", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because anyone can claim to represent any party in an attempt to defraud the innocent second party.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1179, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Validation should be obtained from the Creditor by the Collection Agency prior to any Collection attempt is made by the Collection Agency at the very least.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "It would be even better if the Collection Agency would give notice of validation at least 5 days before any attempt is made to Collect.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This notice would give the Consumer a narrow window to contact the Creditor directly to satisfy a debt that may be outstanding or to inquire about the details of the alleged debt before making a good faith payment to the Collection Agency.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "The rules of Evidence Judicial Procedure should be horned during the validation process.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "With out meeting some measure of the burden of proof all functions of Debt Collection is simply a burden to the Tax Payer,", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "any proceedings with out court worthy documentation would be frivolous.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If Custody of the debt is transfered form a Creditor to and Collection Agency the Contract must be available for the Consumer or Custody of the debt by the Collection Agency should be invalidated.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Privacy should be respected.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When it come to mortgage debt; Upon the issuance of a mortgage form a bank the bottom line banks holding do not decrease.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "In essence The bank has written new currency (guaranteed by the future payment of the Property taxes, and other Taxes placed on the individual Citizens of the United States of America backed by there Social Security numbers and property deeds) in to existence.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "Essentially the Borrower is giving the full amount of the mortgage plus interest to the mortgage lender.", "type": "fact", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "If the FDIC truly backs Lenders, The lender should maintain the documentation of the agreed debt and a Default should be handled by the FDIC.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Outsourcing to a Collection Agency can compromises the custody of the debt and encourages harassment of the consumer by a 3rd party.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "May Fraud be Minimal and Prosperity be Abundant.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1180, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "States Rights versus Federal Rights are the biggest issues with the rule making process.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There is a vast divergence of state law requirements that create areas that confuse consumers, regulators, and those in the industry as to what laws apply in what settings.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A universal rule that would apply in all settings would assist all parties to remove the ambiguity and conflict that currently exists with state multiple levels of regulation at the municipal, state, and two regulators at the federal level", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1181, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2"], "text": "Although I don't think that it is necessary for the CFPB to have undercover agents, I do think that the CFPB should create a new class of examiners.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Currently the CFPB examiners only do examinations of the financial lenders and nonbank lenders.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But since the CFPB is now taking on the collection industry,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "4", "5"], "text": "the CFPB should create a new classification of examiners to do onsite examinations of the debt collection companies.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This would not create any harm to the CFPB ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "nor would it impact the CFPB\"s budget or operations.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The CFPB\"s budget is not allocated through congressional legislation \"", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "it is allocated through monetary transfers from the Federal Reserve.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All the CFPB would need to do is ask for additional transfers from the Federal Reserve to create this new classification of examiners.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These new examiners would help the CFPB monitor the debt collection industry and would help stimulate the economy by adding more jobs.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is a win-win solution.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1182, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "It is the responsibility of the creditor and debt collectors to report accurate information.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Reporting accurate information has nothing to do with \"debt collectors who don't report to credit reporting agencies at all.\"", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a debt collector reported accurately that the debt in question has not been paid, but now is, it is the responsibility of that debt collector to report the newly accurate information.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As I too have noticed, some debt collectors will not accurately report updated information to the credit bureaus once they are paid.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1186, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have a charged off loan which I have been trying to get a repay plan on", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but the debt is listed as one amount on my CBR and the debt collector had the balance increased by $12K more when discussing it over the phone.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is outrageous that they do not have an accurate amount of what is owed to the original lender.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1187, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have a charged off debt I want to pay off.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I cannot afford a lump sum and asked the debt collector and original lender in writing mutiple times to work with me on a settlement.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They refuse to answer my letters", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "and I keep writing every month.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think they should be made to at least respond to a customer requests for repayment.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "They keep asking for my employer name and bank account number", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I know they want to use it to garnish my wages and bank account.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Of course I do not have $32k to settle.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It was a 2nd mtg,", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I lost home due to loss of job,", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "they refused to modify", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they said investor wanted to foreclose instead.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1189, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "There is no need for these so-called examiners", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "but there is definitely a need for courageous and dedicated attorneys determined to enforce the laws that the CFPB should pass, laws that protect the ordinary folk, the innocent, those who're unable to protect themselves, even those who may have actually failed to pay their bills", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because our constitution guarantees the right to our innocence unless proven guilty.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We cannot allow expediency to deny us such fundamental rights.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I believe there is such a thing as the Gideon Decision by the Supreme Court that provides for any accused to an adequate defence,", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "so if any debt-collector or creditor for that matter denies the alleged debtor the right to have his day in court or to a proper defence, then the CFPB attorneys should come down hard on such violators.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The principle behind any rules promulgated by the CFPB must ensure that no alleged debtor get bullied into paying up or blind-sided by the court into doing so.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sometimes, there are reasons why the outstanding bills are not paid ", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the consumer should be allowed to confront the creditor to resolve any complaints by the consumer before the bills are paid.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's a very straight-forward and simple situation actually.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All the CFB needs to do is to enact basic regulations that protects the consumer and stipulates very clearly that the burden of proof must be borne by the creditor before any debt-collector can be engaged to pursue such debts.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debt-collector must only be allowed to follow specific guidelines when doing so", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["13"], "text": "and the matter should be referred to a small claims court to have both sides plead their case before the court issues a ruling, rather than to allow the claim to be reported to a credit reporting agency ", "type": "policy", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "that will destroy the credit score or rating of the consumer without his knowledge, which is absolutely wrong.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Only lawful and valid debts, i.e. when a judgment order has been made, should be allowed to be reported to any credit reporting agency, to avoid creditors and debt-collectors from using such agencies to damage the interests of alleged debtors with unfounded or unproven debts.", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1190, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As medical records become more digitized, ", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "I see no significant cost increase to debt collectors in passing on substantive info to debtors,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "although debt collectors are bound to say otherwise.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My concern is that the cost to consumers of inadequate information is routinely underestimated or dismissed as trivial.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": ["4_8"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I worked with a non-profit in Alabama, I took part in an informational meeting on a program of federal assistance (Farmers Home Admin, IIRC) in securing access to home loans on affordable terms for low-income workers.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One woman who was at the meeting spoke of having been denied access to the program because of a single blot on her credit record, namely an unpaid medical bill.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "She said she had not paid it because she could not determine what the charges were for, was unaware of any medical treatment she had not paid for, and could not get a straight answer from the debt collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "She decided the debt might be illegitimate and refused to pay.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "As a result she was excluded from access to a home loan.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is an example of a consumer on a limited income who was consistently disciplined about her finances and who should have had access to credit.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I find it significant that it was a medical bill that tripped her up, placing her in a category in which even the FHA would not work with her.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "From this point, credit was only available to her at high cost if at all.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I am confident that the rule I am suggesting would have led her to either pay the debt or dispute it formally on the basis of valid information.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What it would not have done is to leave her to conclude that she was being scammed and refuse to pay at all.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This anecdote (and I admit I only have anecdotal evidence) does suggest that legitimate credit agencies also stand to benefit by disclosing information that will persuade skeptical consumers that they do actually owe the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1191, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "My only concern about this excellent comment is that consumers not be subjected to a flood of confusing or potentially intimidating information.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The most useful information is the what, when, who, and why of the original transaction that incurred the unpaid debt.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The original creditor should be identified by a name known to the consumer, e.g. DR. JOHN SMITH, RHEUMATOLOGIST not DYNAMIC HEALTHCARE OF GREATER ANYTOWN d/b/a ASSOCIATED SPECIALISTS P.C.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You get the idea.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1192, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "It could be treated just like any document you fax or snail mail,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "uploading is just an easier way to get it there.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As to fine time, I would say 48 hours.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1193, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I still stand by what I said;", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "CFPB should have a large core of undercover agents with arresting powers.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1194, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I was a reference for an ex-boyfriend on a student loan application.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One of the FDCPA rules is that the reference can only be contacted once by a creditor.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Well, each time the account is sold to a new collection agency, they call me again,", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "even though I tell them I have no idea where he is.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think creditors skirt the FDCPA regulations in a manner that harasses consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For any given account, the reference should only be able to be called a set amount of times--such as the first three collection agencies to purchase the debt from the original creditor.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Here it is, almost 9 years later, and I am still getting calls for a person who is now a stranger to me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Since it is a student loan,", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7", "9"], "text": "it could go on forever.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There is no statute of limitations for government guraranteed debt that I am aware of...", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1196, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Items 1 through 10 should all be provided on the validation notice.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "3", "4", "5"], "text": "Number 10 specifically should include the Date-of-service or DOS for the medical debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many consumers do not realize that medical debt goes to collections just like any other consumer debt.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "They mistakenly believe that their insurance company will resolve the issue.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also with extensive medical bills ( inpatient surgical stay) consumers have professional bills from each physician ( radiology, pathology, etc) in addition to technical component bills for the facility.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many times the consumer never sees these medical providers and either mistakes the bill for another aspect of the service rendered or, again, just assumes the bill/debt will \"be taken care of\".", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "additionally the name of the consumer's insurance Co./plan on the validation notice would be quite helpful.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This may seem to be a great deal of extra information", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but the originating physician and/or facility obtain this information at the time of or prior to service.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1197, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "When calling about a debt, debt collectors MUST verify that they are speaking to the debtor(s) or other adult within the household.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I know that is stated within the FDCPA", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but from experience I know it doesn't always happen.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My situation goes back to the 1970's", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but it was done then ", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it's probably still being done today.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Calling repeatedly, threatening, screaming, cursing at children gets collectors absolutely nowhere.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is a most disgusting form of abuse that should never be tolerated.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "New language in the FDCPA should specifically and clearly state this.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "Additionally, there should be some form of penalty for collectors who engage in this demeaning and useless practice.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1199, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "My husband called a creditor about payments to an old account and wanted to make the account current after missed payments, due to job loss.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The account was reopened under a new account number.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Now I have 2 accounts on my credit report with the same amount.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1201, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "In Michigan a company had its Collection Agency Revoked due to unethical practices 2008.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But this did not stop them.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Now they practice as attorneys and continue the unethical practices.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_2"], "text": "Yes states must figure out how to close this loophole.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1206, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, that just happened to me today,", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "someone called trying to locate a friend saying they were a \"courier service.\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1207, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have not encountered a situation in which the bill collector is hired by a business for many decades now.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Usually the debt collector has bought the debt, usually for pennies on the dollar, from the original creditor.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also disagree that the law provides a way for consumers to steal from businesses.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If anything, I would say we have become in danger of reverting to the tyranny of Dickens' time, where a person and that person's family, including children, would be imprisoned for debt.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Surely we can agree on reasonableness when it comes to how we treat each other, whether debtor or creditor?", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1208, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "It might help to take a look at how debt collectors are compensated.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think, based upon people I know who have held such work, that collectors who receive their pay based on a commission are incentivized to abuse the consumer.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I do not think the CFPB's mission is to provide job security for the debt collection industry.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1209, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Marian makes an excellent point about how Debt Collectors are paid.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They try to get as much money upfront as possible.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Ironically, if they get too much money upfront, the credit card company might snatch the account back from the debt collector.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the amount is \"too low\" that the debt collector receives, they are not interested.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This goes against many sales principles that it is easier to interact at a later date with a paying customer versus trying to make a big score all at once.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1210, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I had an issue where an attorney,acting on my behalf,requested verification of the loan debt and never heard back from the collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "Therefore can not move ahead with settlement until they respond.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1211, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I too have received calls from collectors who are on fishing expeditions, looking for a person who owes money.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "THE PROBLEM IS, EVEN AFTER BEING INFORMED THAT THE PERSON THEY ARE LOOKING FOR CANNOT BE REACHED AT MY PHONE NUMER AND TO PUT ME ON THEIR DO NOT CALL LIST - THEY STILL CALL.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have contacted local law enforcement, state attorney general and federal levels and been informed that if I owed money, I can have the debt collector contact me in writing only, but if I don't owe money, I have no protection because the debt collector has a right to do business.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1"], "text": "Unless the debt collector has more than a last name that matches the person's who owes the debt, they should be allowed to attempt to contact that phone number ONLY until they are told that that person cannot be reached at that phone number.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They should need to have more than a last name for any further phone calls.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They should also have to tell the person they insist on calling why they believe they can find the person who owes the money there.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Additionally, they should also be required to inform the consumer of how to file a complaint if the calls continue.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "There should be a penalty for harassing people who don't owe money.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When you don't owe money, getting phone calls early in the morning or late at night twice a week is harassment", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "the more abusive ones robo call several times a day and hang up when an answering machine picks up).", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Additionally, the means of protecting yourself from harassment should not require any financial burden to the consumer.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was told I could file a lawsuit in the case of one extremely abusive collector", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1212, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "It seems to me that the system must provide a series of 'handshakes': When a dispute is initiated; when the dispue is resolved; or when a dispute is withdrawn.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "In each case the consumer must know with certainty that the collector acknowledges the consumer's position and that the CRA has been properly notified.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The CRA must be party to the handshake,", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is unacceptable that consumer's complaints can laguish for months with the consumer having no way to determine whether the CRA has received updated information from the collector or whether the CRA is taking unduly long to process the update.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1213, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "You are absolutely right.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "But, you'd be surprised at how many times this does happen and how many times the Credit Bureaus Do change correct information to false information supplied by the 'furnisher/debt collector'.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Because I had to send in numerous Certified Letter to the Credit Bureaus, (all of them), in order to stay on top of all the false information and tricks that they did supply.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And I have written proof, that this does and is still happening to other consumers, right now.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1217, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have never been deliquent on my State taxes.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Due to an error made by the company I worked for in 2008, which didn't take out taxes, I am now faced with dealing with the State Collection agency.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have never heard of the State threating the residents to try to collect taxes.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I called and coopertaed,", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "however, the callers are harassing me from morning to night.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have excellent credit and have worked for many years to maintain my credit standing.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have never owed Federal taxes that I have not agreed to pay.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And never in my life owed State taxes", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5", "6", "7"], "text": "and I am shocked that they can hound the residents like private collectors do.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I am retired and and on a fixed income.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For the State to be able to threaten the residents who are making attempts to pay the taxes, (one year) seems like a violation of rights.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1218, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "In 2010 I was sued by a debt collector for a debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "At the time I was in my final year of law school and was surprised at the amount of misinformation used by the plaintiff's attorney (e.g. claiming that no proof of assignment was necessary).", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I informed the attorney that I would need proof that this was my debt as well as proof that his client had proper assignment of the debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He responded by threatening (via e-mail) to interfere with my Bar admission process.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I did not believe that an unsubstantiated debt would affect my ability to sit for the bar", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "and so I stood my ground.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He dropped the case (without prejudice) in Magistrate Court and then re-filed in State Court five months later while I was going through my Certification for Fitness process.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "As a result of his second lawsuit, the State Bar did not allow me to sit for the Bar", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "due to \"a pending lawsuit\" about debt.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "He eventually also dropped the lawsuit in State Court.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "He never shared proof of this purported debt nor did he ever produce proof of assignment", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "presumably because he never had valid proof of either).", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Nonetheless he was effective in \"punishing\" me by interfering with my ability to sit for the Bar after graduating from law school.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "this occurred in Georgia.", "type": "fact", "id": 13, "evidence": ["14_15"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Their rules for Bar Admission are available online at", "type": "fact", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "https://www.gabaradmissions.org/home", "type": "reference", "id": 15, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1219, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I agree that expanding the scope of the validation notice would benefit consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "Especially important is a means for the consumer to contact the original creditor and identify the account in question.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When debts are sold multiple times it becomes impossible for consumers to: (1) determine if the account is theirs; (2) validate proper assignment; and (3) determine if the statute of limitations has expired.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The current requirements facilitate \"zombie debt\" accounts which - although already paid by the consumer - come back to life again and again.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "Absent a means for consumers to identify an account there is no way for them to verify that they have previously paid that debt.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1220, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "From 1999 - 2004 I worked on a number of online identity authentication initiatives.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "At that time the only available solution was to ask \"out of wallet\" questions based on the consumer's credit file.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For example, the credit report might show that the consumer lived on Elm Street 20 years ago.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Since an old address would not be easy to find (e.g. in a lost wallet) ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "the idea is that if the consumer knows that they lived on Elm Street 20 years ago, there is greater confidence that this is indeed the person that they claim to be.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The problem with this approach is that the information in credit reports has a reliability problem.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "Reports indicating low error rates are misleading:", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they only look to \"material errors\" ", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they are often funded by credit industry groups.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If it is commonly accepted that credit reports are filled with errors - then it is incumbent upon collectors to validate and verify the debt prior to pulling a credit report or contacting the consumer.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1226, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "As an \"authorized user\" who has no access to the actual credit card, my credit rating is suffering ", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because the \"account holder\" presently, is only able to make the minimum monthly payments.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't think this is fair and have not been able to get a direct response from anyone to see if card companies can legally do this when they collected no information from me but my name!", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There was NO FULL DISCLOSURE stating that as only being an \"authorized user\" said card company would report on my credit report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1227, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I live in Florida where proof of the debt is getting difficult for debt buyers to prove without them falsifying documents.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I currently have a case where the Debt bill of sale was whited out in three places,", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "sadly these documents were filed by an attorney at law registered with the Florida Bar Association.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debt buyers have no scruples", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1231, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I agree with MER.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have experience as a debtor, pro-bono attorney and debt collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You can't expect collectors to be judge or jury.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The cease communication right is meant to to force the collector to sue or go away.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1234, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Dear CFPB: I hope you will separate the comments about debt buyers from those about debt collection in general.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is another area where you should throw the book at collectors telling deliberate lies or misrepresentations.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "On the other hand, there are too many federal suits brought by consumers who were not misled but who allege that the least sophisticated consumer might have been misled by a letter written in good faith.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The only ones who benefit are attorneys.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The CFPB has power under UDAAP in addition to the FDCPA to punish liars.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They should use it.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Collectors, who are just lay people in most cases should not be held to a strict liability standard.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Punish bad actors but ", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "restore reasonableness to the act.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1235, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Honest, respectful and open communication between consumers and collectors should be the goal.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If there are too many roadblocks to making contact with a debtor, more consumers will find negative information on their credit reports and have more lawsuits filed against them.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Rule number 1 strikes the right balance.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the consumer responds, the consumer will receive the mini-miranda disclosure and information about the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the named person is not at the number, is it really so awful to call the collector and let them know?", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If calls contiue after that point from the same collector, then there should be penalties.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Professional collectors do not want to waste time calling a wrong number.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1236, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I do not think collectors would mind reimbursing consumers who are charged per call or per message.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "Add $5 for the hassle of getting the refund.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Collectors should have a way to make contact with consumers who choose not to have a flat-rate telephone service.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Honest, respectful and open communication by all parties is the key to giving consumers enough information to identify and understand debts and come to workable resolutions for legitimate debts.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is also the key to stopping calls to wrong numbers.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4"], "text": "Collectors who are not honest and respectful should be fined or lose their right to be licensed.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1237, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "My experience has been that people younger than I (a boomer) prefer to communicate electronically (emails, texts & chats).", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I know that when I was deeply in debt, I would have preferred not to have to speak to a real person.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There is a legitimate concern about unencrypted email or the potential for consumers not to consider that others may have access to their email.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, in general, we should encourage communication, however that happens - especially if it is in a form preferred by a particular consumer.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I believe that emails, chats & texts should all be considered writings.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I don't know how you include all disclosures unless you direct someone to a place where they can read them in plain english.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1238, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The Telephone Consumer Protection Act of 1991 (TCPA) was passed by the United States Congress in 1991 and signed into law by President George H. W. Bush as Public Law 102-243.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It amended the Communications Act of 1934.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The TCPA is codified as 47 U.S.C. 227.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The TCPA restricts telephone solicitations (i.e., telemarketing) and the use of automated telephone equipment.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The TCPA limits the use of automatic dialing systems, artificial or prerecorded voice messages, SMS text messages, and fax machines.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It also specifies several technical requirements for fax machines, autodialers, and voice messaging systems\"principally with provisions requiring identification and contact information of the entity using the device to be contained in the message.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1239, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have not heard of anyone in the US being imprisoned for their debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have been in the business for 20 years ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and rest assured, while there are 'debt buyers', the majority of agencies are contingency based collections.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
