{"commentID": 1243, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I believe that some collection agencies attempt to coerce payment in order to reset the clock on debts that would otherwise be time-barred.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "The real issue here however is one of proper record keeping.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "The collection agencies may not be fully sure if the debt is time barred or not ", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "simply because it has passed hands several times.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "A transcript or log should be available to consumers upon request (at a minimum) showing when, where and who held the collection.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1244, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2_3"], "text": "Partial payments should NOT revive the debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The original lender or the agencies working on their behalf have more than reasonable time to collect on an outstanding amount owed.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We have rules in place on both collecting debts and on reporting them", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and partial payment on a debt should not circumvent those rules.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1246, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "I believe Amex handles this the best.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The account holder is liable for all charges made by themselves and any authorized users added to the account.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Authorized Users however are given a unique card number and can be held accountable for any charges they make.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1247, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Email: Yes so long as it is not a \"blind\" email attempt at reaching an individual ", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as it may reach the incorrect party (first.lastname@company.com when it should be first.lastname1@company.com", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The down side to this is the inevitable fishing attacks by scammers.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "Email should therefore be limited to times when the consumer initiates it or formally lists their email with the 3 major reporting agencies as a method of initial contact.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1248, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "Texts: No, text messaging and cell phones should be prohibited ", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as there is not a viable means for the consumer to record the text and bring it into court as documentation if needed.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All the issues raised about collectors calling the wrong individual or family members would be 100x worse with texting.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1249, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Social Media: While the courts have made the rare exception for use of social media as a means of giving notice, ", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": ["2"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "not everyone is on every social media platform.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I am very internet savy yet I am not on foursquare, pinterest and several others.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "On FB, Twitter and others there are several thousand people with my name who may get incorrectly notified.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1250, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Texting should follow all rules regarding phone calls.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Email should follow rules set in place regarding written, mailed, letters.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
