{"commentID": 1267, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I am currently going through a miserable experience with a creditor and debt collector.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In 2004 I completed my college education and consolidated all of my student loans through Nelnet.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In 2005 (or so) I started to get calls from debt collectors stating that I was delinquent on my loan repayment.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I explained the situation, that I had made all of my timely payments through Nelnet and, before I would pay anything else, I would need to see some proof of the debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I never received any proof of the debt ", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and this conversation reoccurred several times for the next five years.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In 2011 I wanted to buy my (wife\"s) dream home.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It was a significant purchase ", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the bankers I talked with indicated I needed to clear up the student loan issue to be approved.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I reached out to the original creditor and the debt collector and begged for some proof of the loan.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They then provided me with a loan application (nothing to indicate that the application was approved or that any funds were ever dispersed to me).", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "While I was not comfortable with the proof, ", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I knew that fighting it out in court would take longer than I was willing to take.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "So, I was very purposeful in my conversations with the original creditor and the debt collector to make sure that the issue would be cleared on my credit report if I paid the full value of the (alleged) loan.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also recorded the conversations I had with the original creditor and the debt collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I paid the original loan amount ", "type": "testimony", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and (if you didn't see this coming) the original creditor refused to update my credit report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And, even after providing the credit reporting agencies with proof that the debt was paid, they also refused to update my credit report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To make matters worse, after the debt was paid, I received a notice from the debt collector that several thousands of dollars had been excused.", "type": "testimony", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I immediately contacted the debt collector and requested documentation that would support their amount due, including documentation where I agreed to a specific interest rate.", "type": "testimony", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "No response from the debt collector.", "type": "testimony", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["19_20"], "text": "So, I am now arguing it out with the IRS regarding any additional taxes that may be due.", "type": "testimony", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And, even though I paid the debt two years ago, my credit report has not yet been updated.", "type": "testimony", "id": 22, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is simply ridiculous than any business would have this much power to have such a negative impact on an individual without any documentation to back it up.", "type": "value", "id": 23, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["23"], "text": "Any creditor should be required to provide certain documentation prior to making a negative credit reporting and there should be significant consequences for any creditor/debt collector that pursues a debt without having the required documentation.", "type": "policy", "id": 24, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1269, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "It apprears that the debt collectors of the debt collection industry are conducting a money laundry and racketing operation by explointing and obtaining monetary from comsumers for products that they don't sell to them or services that they don't provide to consumers with no inital purchase contract with consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It appears that debt collectors are obtaining monetary from consumers where they don't have licenses to sell products to consumers or provide services to consumers.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It appears that debt collectors are costing companies money when companies are trying to recover their loses when they miss payments from their customers for the products that they sell to their customers or the services that they provide to their customers with alegal purchase contracts.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It seems that debt collector are relying on companies' money and on consumers' money for an income when they are not initially involved in the a company sale of products to consumers or in the distributing of a company of services to a consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1272, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "A question that I'd ask surrounds dialects.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are numerous dialects for Spanish, French, etc.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it would be very expensive for agencies to translate every letter into every dialect of a certain language, Spanish being the most common for this type of occurrence.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'd greatly appreciate feedback, commentary and also recommendations on everyone's view on how to address differing language formalities.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1273, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "If a bank is going to sell a consumer's debt, the bank should be required to notify that consumer IN ADVANCE, and allow that consumer a fair chance to bid on and purchase his/her own debt, on terms just as favorable as the terms offered to any other debt buyer (which at present is usually pennies on the dollar).", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debt buyers contribute nothing to society.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Yet, they are allowed to obtain windfall profits by pursuing impoverished consumers for the full face value of such debts.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "This proposal would entail changes more extensive that just \"notice\" ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as it would require a change from bulk loan sales, to requiring an opportunity to purchase individual loan in certain circumstances.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1274, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I would take a hard look at 'credit reporting' from what is being reported by a creditor and then what is reported by a debt collection or debt buying company.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "For example, if a creditor obtains a judgment amount greater than the account balance, that amount is likely not reported ", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because creditors seldom have system capabilities to make adjustments to accounts.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1275, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "One theme we see throughout comments is that debt sold adds confusion as to whom is the creditor, and also triggers a new credit entry, making the debt appear as incremental (additional), when it is simply transferred, and fresh.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The solution to this is simple; ", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "do not allow credit bureaus to ever list more than one entry for the same debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4", "5"], "text": "Put the burden of accurate recordkeeping on the bureaus, ", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they are the only entities who have a responsibility for accurate recordkeeping ", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they are paid to keep accurate records.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Currently the cost of sloppy systems is externalized to both creditors and borrowers, both of whom tend to re-externalize it to other creditors and borrowers in the form of higher costs.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "It is irrelevant whether these dual entries are caused by negligence, incompetence, or malice on the part of the creditor or collector ", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because it is the responsibility of the credit reporting agency to make this practice impossible.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Adding steep fines for double reporting would incentivize CRA's to police their systems so each debt only garners one entry.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Since CRA's are immune from libel suits in most of the country ", "type": "fact", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "regulatory oversight is especially important.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Conversely, clarifying that reporting agencies are not immune from state libel laws -- that regulatory authority is in addition to state defamation law -- would also quickly incentivize more accurate reporting.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1280, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I was harassed for months by a collector who used robo-calls 5 and 6 times a day and blocked its caller ID, for what turned out to be five different debts, none of which were mine.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Robo-calls were not answered;", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "if I picked up, nobody was there, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and no messages were ever left.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The blocked caller ID was \"1 Unavailable,\" which is designed to outfox call-blocking from the recipient's end, and makes it impossible to identify the caller using reverse number lookups and the like.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One day I picked up ", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and finally there was someone on the other end, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "so I was able to figure out who was calling, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "although they were very reluctant to say who they were.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I then looked them up on the internet and got a phone number for them.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I repeatedly stated I was not the person they were looking for, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they refused to stop calling.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I finally got an attorney ", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and after months of the attorney bickering with them, I did get a small money settlement.", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This was occurring when I was getting chemotherapy treatment for cancer and was very ill.", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My life was hell for months because of these practices.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["15"], "text": "Collectors should be prohibited from concealing either their identity or their call-back numbers.", "type": "policy", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["18"], "text": "This happened ", "type": "testimony", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I had moved and was assigned a new number that evidently had belonged to a number of individuals who had outstanding debts.", "type": "testimony", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["20"], "text": "I was afraid to change my number again ", "type": "value", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because it would just usher in a new batch of collectors.", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["23"], "text": "There should also be much, much, much stiffer monetary penalties for violations.", "type": "policy", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The guilty party in the above scenario was a national collection agency with huge annual revenues; ", "type": "fact", "id": 22, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "the piddly amount I was eventually paid was to them a tiny fraction of one cent compared to their annual revenues.", "type": "testimony", "id": 23, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I just happen to be an attorney myself, and ran their name on Pacer--", "type": "testimony", "id": 24, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they had been sued over and over in state and federal court and had actually paid million dollar fines to state attorneys general--also just a small cost of doing business for them compared to their enormous annual revenues.", "type": "testimony", "id": 25, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["23", "25"], "text": "We need much, much stiffer penalties.", "type": "policy", "id": 26, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These people are cyber bullies with absolutely no scruples.", "type": "value", "id": 27, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "At the very least they should be required to identify themselves on caller i.d. with a legitimate callback number, ", "type": "policy", "id": 28, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and robo-calls should be made illegal.", "type": "policy", "id": 29, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1281, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I left a long comment about one particular collector, but recently was harassed by yet another one who was trying to collect from someone else who was not me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Their caller ID was not a phone number;", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "it was just the names of different states, but turned out to be the same company.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These people are bottom-feeders with no scruples.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Accurate caller ID should be required ", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so the victim can at least identify the collector and have a call-back number for them.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And monetary penalties should be much, much stiffer to discourage their outrageous, predatory and harassing practices.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Harrassment is part of their business models.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These people are scum and should be required at the very least to identify themselves accurately.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Robo-calls and ID spoofing should be illegal with stiff fines.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1282, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "They will just continue to call.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Not answering does not stop the constant calls.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "They need to be required to identify themselves accurately ", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so the consumer has at least a fighting chance to speak with them.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "In my case I have no debts of my own but am constantly harassed for other people's debts ", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I have a fairly common last name.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They just start calling everyone with the same last name as their actual debtor.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1283, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "There are currently no \"teeth\" in the enforcement mechanism as well.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Right now filing complaints with the regulators does absolutely nothing except get you into some database ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but nothing is every done about violations.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1_2", "4"], "text": "Requiring accurate identification of the collector with a working call-back number should be the bare minimum.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "At least that way the consumer has a fighting chance of at least talking to them and trying to get erroneous calls stopped.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1_2"], "text": "Right now government enforcement is non-existent and completely worthless.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1284, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "It doesn't just \"occasionally\" happen.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It happens all the time.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Those of us with common names are sitting ducks for these scumbags.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I am constantly harassed by collectors looking for someone else.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Call blocking programs do not work out of area, ", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "so call-blocking is no protection whatever.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1286, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Right now collectors are legally required to stop phone contact when notified by the consumer.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They do not stop.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And the law is not enforced.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Reporting violations to regulators does nothing except get the complainant into some sort of database, ", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the regulators are never heard from again.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There are decent laws on the books.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's the enforcement that is a failure.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
