{"commentID": 1297, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As Director I can clearly in good faith state that as we service our potential losses ", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and my Team make collection calls contact is generally made at work place as well.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Let me also state that many of the call backs are made from Members at work as well.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It all depends on the employer and the work conditions surrounding the consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1298, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Let's keep it as simple as possible. ", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "Based on 3rd party disclosure statue blocking the ID benifits the consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "One never knows who is at the other end of the phone.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1299, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "There should be clear guidelines on what constitutes \"irrelevant and frivolous\".", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In my own experience, the CRA's consistently refused to delete trade lines not belonging to me even when I had provided documentation from the original creditor validating the debt was not mine.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They falsely claimed they received additional information from the original creditor that superseded the documentation I had.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I circled back to the original creditor, I had learned the debt was sold to a junk debt buyer which leads to a separate issue.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the junk debt buyer is reporting to a credit reporting agency, why are they misrepresenting themselves as the original creditor.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Junk Debt buying should be prohibited all together.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The original creditors should know their vendors just as the law mandates they know their customers.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the vendor is violating the law on the original creditor's behalf the original creditor should hold responsibility to some extent.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1300, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I am all for consumers right protection", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but when you see CFPB, FDCPA and other law they are all to make it difficult for collection agencies to do their honest job.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But there is never a talk about consumers responsibilities.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I agree that some collection agencies are aggressive.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I think a good honest collection agencies also need their rights to do honest work.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1301, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Consumers normally are unaware that their debt has been sold to a collection agency.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They, one day, get a call about the debt from someone unbeknownst to them.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The collection agency wants the consumer to remit the payment to them, ", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "when actually, principal on the debt never decreases ", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because the collection agency gets their cut (commission) off the top.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debt is there essentially, forever with added late charges, interest and other penalties.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "I submit to the CFPB to finalize the \"Know Before You Owe\" rule and to outlay the debt validation rules", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "so that consumers can make an informed choice before wasting their money on a debt they may not owe.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1303, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Debt collectors call and cannot verify that the creditor has merged with another company.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debt may have written off the books of the acquired company.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "I propose that the CFPB implement a rule pertaining to debts written off by an acquired company and any additional stipulations on a timeframe to which an old debt can be collected only if the consumer has been validly notified that the debt has been sold to a debt collection agency; excluding the initial call from the DCA", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1307, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "My problem with those debt collection companies employees I have had to deal with is this...", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they either call themselves agent,investigators,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "or they are members of a special department investigating a debt alluding to Law Enforcement or DA's office.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Most recently, as last week, they have indicated, they are going to contact me at my place of employment and are going to initiate civil action if I don't contact them before the close of business.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is out of order and should be stop", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1308, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "One such collection company used the actual phone number of a District Civil Court office in a neighboring county in their phone message for my wife to collect on a debt many years old.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This practice is deplorable and should have sever penalties towards any collection company/employee that uses this type of collection action.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1309, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have experience collection companies who buys the debt from the 1st 2nd or 3rd party add on its fees along with the other companies fees,then submit a new account number to the original account as though it was a new account.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So, a original account for the sake of argument was $500.00 turns out to be listed on your credit report as a $3,000 delinquent account.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "Government laws should not allow this practice to exist.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What ever the original account is that's what should be reported not interest and additional fees a collection company deems it can add to your credit bureau report.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1311, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "In my opinion,collection companies,credit bureaus, and every one in between should be made to have some type of soft ware that could identify time-barred debt.Plus, regulation that will not allow creditors/buyers to reactivate an old debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a given state has its own statue of limitation regarding a legitimate time line to collect a debt, so be it.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The Validation Notice,should identify the true facts of the debt in question.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After complete due process has been exhausted, the record should be completely removed from the consumer file.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1312, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Yes...the CFPB should require debt collectors/debt owners to notify consumers in writing, that a payment plan or partial plan will revive the time-barred debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "However, the debt owner or debt collection company should not be allowed to have a second chance to sue you for the old debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This in itself would be bubble jeopardy in a criminal case of law.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If anything a second seven year listing of the agreed balance you are willing to repay will be listed on ones credit bureau report would be allowed.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Note: A collection company that purchased the account for pennies on the dollar,should \"ONLY\" be allowed to collect the amount of monies they purchased the account for plus any regulated reasonable fee amount.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Because they were not the original lender in the first place.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The original debt owners should \"ONLY\" be allowed to list the agreed pay off amount of the time-barred account,the consumer agreed to pay.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Example: debt owner original time-barred account $1.000.00 dollars.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debt owner accepts $500.00 and consumer agrees to pay back.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The only amount to report is the $500.00 dollars.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1313, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Here's what the federal government laws should mandate how the collection companies and CRAs should investigate disputes", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All collection actions and reporting actions should stop immediately.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The time line should be equal on the consumer,collection company,CRAs reporting period.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The original debt owner or collection company that purchase the account, should produce the original copy of the signed contract, court documents, and any verifiable records relating to the dispute.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Forward those documents to the disputing party within the set aside timeline.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Any and all verification letters would have to state and indicate such findings.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once the dispute could not be verified by,name,social,signed document copy of original agreement, it should be immediately deleted.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The collections companies and original debt owners are responsible for the validity of information they get,buy,receive,send or share.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "So, if they buy good or bad debt they should be held responsible.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The number,types,unclear,clear,collections disputes should all be investigated the same", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1314, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Debt was sold to another company.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "So now debt is listed on my credit twice.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "So debt will last more than 10 years on report.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Plus I've been a victim of identity theft twice.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Both times I reported it to the police and to the credit agencies.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Unfortunately nothing police can do but write a report for proof.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Credit agency was ordered to put a fraud alert on my social but fail to do so.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1316, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have had debt collectors call and tell me that I am not cooperating to get the debt resolved, yell at me, tell me I must be lazy or not understand I owe the money.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They have called me from 7:00 am to 9:00pm at least 10 times during the day using a different company name, different phone number and location including my city and other cities and states all in the same day.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I tell them I am a senior they tell me to borrow the money from a family member or friend.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When I tell them I am not going to do that the harrassment starts all over.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many of them call and act like I am an old friend before they tell me who they are.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They threaten to ruin my credit raiting, confiscate my home and belonging and car,", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The most annoying is when they call and I answer they hang up and call again an hr later and hang up again.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "I know it is them ", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I have caller id.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1318, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I received several Robo calls leaving messages to have me served at my job on a debt I do not owe.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They have Threatened me via voice mail.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They also use Voip numbers we have reversed them different each time.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have reported them several times ", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they continue to call.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1321, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I had to spend quite a bit of time dealing with their repeated calls.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Of course, they weren't looking for me but rather for someone with my very common last name and first initial.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had many calls from them one day.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Apparently, their telephone representatives were trained to hang up if they received any response other than, \"How do I pay?\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They'd hang up on me before I could complete a sentence.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That particular day, either by accident or through malice (I suspect the latter.),", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they had their robo dialer programmed to call back immediately.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The representative would hang up on me ", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and before I could step away from the phone, the robo dialer would call me back ", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I'd be speaking with another representative who would hang up on me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After many such calls and hang-ups, I was finally able to get a representative to stay on the line with me long enough for me to explain that they were calling the wrong person.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After that the calls stopped.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As I think back on this experience, I find it quite comical, ", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I didn't at the time.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I did file complaints with the FTC and my state's Attorney General.", "type": "testimony", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1322, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The original comment was suggesting that anytime a debt collector calls they are automatically agreeing to be recorded if the consumer chooses to do so.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I think that is a FANTASTIC idea.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1323, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Consumers should be able to request calls be limited to one contact per week if they desire.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is a fair and honorable compromise,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1324, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Explaining why the repeat phone call abuse happens does not justify it.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Apparently there are autodialers that call several consumers at the same time, than hang up on all but the first consumer that answers the phone.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "The result is a person can get several collection calls and hang ups through out the day, ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "that is just not right.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1326, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "One communication from the debt collector per week is plenty.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "On top of that, The debt collector's phone rep should have power over the autodialer in the following way.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A consumer's number is on the screen, the report log on that number is on the screen, the most current info at the top of the screen.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the debt collector phone rep sees that the very last communication does is already updated (such as waiting on a job interview with a date that is still in the future), then the debt collector phone rep should have the power to prevent the auto dialer from making the call.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "Not only does this prevent unnecessary hounding of the customer, it also helps prevent abusive reactions from consumers towards the debt collector phone rep", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because the consumer recalls their last communication and that what was discussed could not have reasonably happened yet.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1327, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Just like Cable companies may expect their customers to give them a four hour window for service calls,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "consumers should be allowed to choose a time frame they prefer to be called within.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they never respond within that time frame, then the debt collector could try a different time frame.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1329, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "I am saying that collection agencies cannot be trusted and more often than not go beyond their job scope.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some act as loan sharks and not collection agencies.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also think that their behavior is criminal when it comes to making threats against consumers and harassing people with disabilities and seniors.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1", "2"], "text": "So, yes i think criminal charges should be pursued for their cover ups and harassment. Also other violations of privacy and fairness.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1330, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Collection agencies are not an all loose for the consumer nor they should be.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some collections agencies have gone beyond their job scope and their role in the process of repayment.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1331, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Yes. I think there is a way to get the debt collectors on board.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The CFPB can remind them that debt collection companies may be exposing their own phone reps / employees to unnecessary verbal abuse from customers who have a legitimate justification for being upset because of follow up calls that ignore the updated agreement just reached in the prior call.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "If the previous communication with the debt collector creates a new timeline for possible repayment, then the debt collector should not step on that timeline by making subsequent calls less than a week later. unless the customers says call back in less than a weeks time.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This also gives the debt collection phone rep the ability to say...\"It has been a week or longer since our last communication\"...Which allows the customer a moment to realize they are not being harassed on a daily basis by the same debt collector.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some consumers have situations in which their income grinds to zero ", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "and they may default on more than one account.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Imagine 5 debt collectors each calling twice a day.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Even one call a week can still equal one call a day if a consumer has five simultaneous defaults,", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but that is certainly preferable to 2 calls a day from each collection account, which would equal 10 calls a day, every day.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1332, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I have dealt with the issue of disputes ", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and when you file a dispute and it as been closed it is placed in the comment section that you have filed a dispute.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "By doing this, this has kept me from refinancing my home ", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "just because the word dispute was there.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The mortgage company said I had to have this removed,", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "so I filed another form to ask for this to be removed it never was.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "I believe that once the dispute has been closed there should be no indication that there was a dispute filed.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You again get penalized for trying to correct mistakes on your report.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Another issue that has come up regarding when an account has been charged off or in my case a repossession of a vehicle I had turn over due to not being released by my doctor to go back to work and my disability ran out , I had no other choice but to hand the vehicle over.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "then 6 years later I received a 1099 for over $6000.00.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Plus the 16% interest they charged me for 4 years.", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We keep paying these high interest rates ", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but yet we still have to pay for our credit scores and only receive one free report a year,", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If we are trying to stay on top of credit fraud and inaccurate information that is not of our doing but from reporting agencies , these agencies should be putting more funds in for these things.", "type": "policy", "id": 13, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1337, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2", "3"], "text": "This question is most interesting with respect to student loans.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Unlike most other debts, student loans have the potential to be greater than $75k, ", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "which means a consumer can be sued in Federal Court under supplemental jurisdiction provisions.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Additionally, should the current creditor be able to achieve complete diversity, the consumer can be sued in an entirely different state.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1339, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I think the cost of education needs to be reduced to a more reasonable amount or repayment plans need to be income based.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As far as consumer protection, legal aid needs to be made available, affordable and effective,", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "and consumers need to take time to really know their rights and stop complaining about harassment", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because that's a completely different cause of action than restitution.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1340, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "3"], "text": "Some problems that debt collectors and buyers have with giving consumers this information arises in the field of Electronic Data Interchange.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Here, not all debts, especially with interest are calculated the same way,", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and since there are fees, such as statutory attorneys fees, and court costs, which can be added to the balance, ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2", "4"], "text": "calculating the balance becomes cumbersome when the data is transferred among Trading Partners on a daily basis ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because the data gets lost in translation over day-to-day lags.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Computers don't think the same way people do", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and what we think is a simple calculation is muddled when partial payments are added and the data is transmitted between parties.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1342, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I would like to see some strict regulation on the number of times a creditor can call in a given period of time.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Capital One Bank's dialers will call every single hour if a payment is overdue...", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "sometimes these things are simply overlooked.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If I know I am paying bills on a given day, I just use my caller ID and ignore them.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "I do think that these calls need to be at least limited.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It comes down to simple harrasment.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1344, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, the Massachusetts model sounds very sensible", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "and the Feds should consider adopting it or something similar.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Two contacts in a 7-day period is plenty,", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4", "6"], "text": "but I think wherever the limits are set they will have to be very strictly enforced.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These collectors will find any loopholes, excuses or reasons to get around a regulation like this.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4", "6"], "text": "There has to be zero tolerance, every time, no exceptions.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They have violated our privacy and the right to peaceful enjoyment of our home one too many times.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1345, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1_3"], "text": "Student Loans, Many of the problems that students are facing are with student loans from the private sector.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Take for example Sallie Mae, this company has it on file that i dod not graduate from college ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and i did graduate.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Their collections agencies are like loan sharks going to the extreme of making threats and cussing out students who cannot make payments.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I know for some people it is easy to make payments on student loans ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but for many it is a struggle to get by.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "All students are trying to better themselves ", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and sometimes they simply cannot afford to make payments.", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Companies like Sallie Mae are in the business of making peoples lives miserable.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10_11"], "text": "Their collection practices, customer service and lack of options are usually the reason why students default on their loans.", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Paying for college is a marathon not a sprint ", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and these companies treat the repayment of student loans like a sprint.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "I think they need to offer more options to students.", "type": "policy", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also think private institutions ala the schools that lend money to students need to do a better job at giving students options to prevent default. resolutions and remedy not judgement and default.", "type": "policy", "id": 13, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1347, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "False of misleading are rearranging paper work to suit their claims, false allegations against the lender, personal harassment, humiliation on credit reports, preventing students from seeking consolidation form other companies.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Other false or misleading is the assumption that students dont want to repay their loans.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is not true.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They also mix up the paper work so much it is difficult to get to the bottom of why the loans are in default in the first place.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They need to streamline their services and offer students option in the private loan sector.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "The institutions should do the same", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they treat student loans like mortgage loans.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1349, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Too many collectors call and never report the \"mini-Miranda warning\".", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They call all times of the day and night, and multiple times of the day.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If they don't get you because your have called ID, they will change their ID and try again.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is simply harrassment.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Many will challenge the the consumer, threaten, and even harrass them to the point that I saw someone actually contemplate suicide.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also, when a debt is sold, the information for the orginal details need to go with it.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "many times these collectors will call, ", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and they have no details on debts that are 5 and 6 years old, ", "type": "fact", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and the consumer doesn't rememer it.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1350, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "A certified letter plus a regular letter should be sent.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It proves that a consumer is at least aware of the debt and has X time to respond.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Should cost any more then the postage of the regular letter.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1353, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Having been recently included for free credit checking, after the Target identity theft issue, I checked my credit with Experian and found a $9,924 \"collection\" on my credit report, resulting in a 610 FICO score!", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had never heard of Portfolio Recovery, a company located in Virginia.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I immediately wrote to the Office of Consumer Affairs in Virginia, detailing what this erroneous addition to my credit report had done to my overall score and my ability to maintain good credit.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "ALL of my credit cards lowered my limits,", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I thought that had been in response to the ongoing bank investigations and the banks way of getting back at consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It all made sense when I saw this entry.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What shocked, alarmed and enraged me most is that Experian excepted this \"collection\" entry without documentation.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I can assure you that none exists.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, I have been a victim of lost wallets and identity theft within the last 20 years and may have seemed a legitimate target to Bottom-feeder agencies like Portfolio Recovery ", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "(the Internet is rife with consumer complaints about their tactics and illegal practices attempting to collect \"debts!\"", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I intend to pursue this matter by informing our Attorney General Kamala Harris and am grateful that you are targeting an otherwise unassailable lobby.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Anytime a consumer writes to a credit reporting agency, the letter winds up in Mumbai, is laughed at and never acted upon.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Experian, TransUnion and Equifax should undergo a Congressional investigation, during which their anti-consumer orientation and fraudulent reporting will be noted, as well as the impossibility of restoring a former 810 FICO, once scumbags like Portfolio Recovery have been allowed clear access to ruin the credit score and compromise the professional life and earning potential of millions of consumers.", "type": "policy", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1355, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The debt collector must be required to submit the original application for credit with the consumer's original signature and the original letter of approval for the credit.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "The debt collection company should be required to submit full documentation that the debt actually exists.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Too many debt collectors rely on falsified affidavits.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1356, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "During the past 2 years I have been repeatedly contacted by a variety of collection agencies.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It began innocently enough, when one of them called me, asking \"when can we expect your payment,\" when that statement had not yet arrived and was not due until the 20th of the month and the call occurred on the 11th.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It was a collection agency hired by Capital One.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Coincidentally, I purchased various items at Costco a few days later and received the shock of my little life when my credit card was denied.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I called Capital One from a phone at Costco and was told I had not made my payment...", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "this was even stranger", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because I pay off my balance each month.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What I didn't know is that Costco switched from a very nice bank (HSBC) to Capital One, never notified me ", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and Capital One immediately played hardball, albeit unnecessarily.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To answer their strong-arm tactics, I wrote a letter to Robert Crawford, the incoming CFO of Capital One, in which I had cut up both credit cards and told him to \"shove it,\" for treating a long-time customer like something you scrape off the shoe!", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "When the collection calls began, I was in a great mood", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "after all, I had initiated this mess.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, they were unfaird from the beginning.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They use I.V.R. numbers.", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Without technical jargon, it means that the number we see on caller i.d. is never the number from which they're calling, ", "type": "fact", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["14"], "text": "so you can't block their call", "type": "fact", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "my provider allows me to block 12 numbers ", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["16"], "text": "and I wondered how these collection agencies were constantly squeaking by).", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They robodial, ", "type": "fact", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["18", "20"], "text": "so you can and do get several calls per day and before 8:00 AM and after 9:00 PM,", "type": "fact", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "since they know there is very little you can do about the early or late calls, besides whine", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That said, what followed was even worse....", "type": "value", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "the collection agency (Portfolio Recovery) which was able to place a bogus $9,924 \"collection\" on my Experian credit score, which I saw because Target offered me 1-year free credit monitoring, which, by the way, isn't free if you want to see your complete profile...", "type": "testimony", "id": 22, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "they have no paperwork to substantiate this charge ", "type": "testimony", "id": 23, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it has completely ruined my credit, pulling down my FICO from 795 - 810 to 610!", "type": "testimony", "id": 24, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "To me, having collection agency CEO's boiled in oil seems like an act of mercy!", "type": "value", "id": 25, "evidence": null}]}
