{"commentID": 1368, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I don't believe that debt tolling should be legal.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For instance, I had a medical crisis while living in Illinois for college.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Despite having insurance, I still ended up deeply in debt.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I attempted to work with the debt collectors, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but I just couldn't keep up due to the massive amounts.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I moved back to Wisconsin where I'm from.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The debt has since become time-barred in Wisconsin due to the statute of limitations.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's not on my credit report", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I can't be sued for it here.", "type": "fact", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, should I ever wish to return to Illinois again, it's like I never left and I can be raked over the coals by debt collectors all over again, including being sued.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This doesn't make any sense.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Either I get sued or I don't.", "type": "fact", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's been over 10 years, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it's not like I skipped the country and \"hid\" from them.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I'd like to return to Illinois, ", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but doing so would kill my credit.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They had 10 years to sue me.", "type": "testimony", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Isn't that enough?", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is unfair ", "type": "value", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["18", "20"], "text": "and I believe the issue of debt tolling should be explored.", "type": "policy", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's just not right.", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1369, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "There needs to be a universal Statute of Limitations.", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2_3"], "text": "The current system is an absolute mess.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "17 states maintain a SOL of three to four years, while 19 others have the six years SOL time limit.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The rest all have diverse SOL limits with some extending for even up to 10 years.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Tolling provisions make it even more confusing.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Simplify it.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "Have a single NATIONAL Statute of Limitations.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Make it fair for everyone (debt collectors and debtors", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "5 years seems reasonable.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Having a universal Statute of Limitations will eliminate confusion and ambiguity as to when and where a debtor can be sued.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1371, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1", "2", "3"], "text": "I believe that a universal statute of limitations would be an effective way to end debt tolling.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If there was a universal statute of limitations, there would be no need for debt tolling.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Collectors would be able to file suit no matter where the debtor lived based on a single set of federal laws.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "It also makes things less confusing for debtors ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "(they know that they can be sued within X amount of years no matter where they go, hence they can't \"run\" from debt", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and debt collectors don't have to go from state to state, wading through murky laws.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "Furthermore, debt collectors should not have the privilege of hiding behind tolling laws.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Either they sue or they don't within a federally mandated set of time.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Tolling simply keeps zombie debt going and going.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1373, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I agree 100% with this statement.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Creditors should not simply be able to pull your credit report at their fancy.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had so many soft pulls (this was before I realized I needed to opt out of marketing) that my credit report from Equifax got \"split.\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Basically, this means that my report got chopped in half and trade lines disappeared.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also, a legitimate creditor attempted to pull my credit and was told by Equifax that I didn't exist.", "type": "testimony", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Everything was GONE.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "After numerous fruitless attempts at reaching someone at Equifax, I finally got a real person.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was informed of the split and told that the burden was on me to provide them with the correct information to \"put my report back together.\"", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "I had to fax them my driver's license, social security card, and a utility bill,", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "all because their software cracked due to too many inquiries that I didn't even authorize.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's still not resolved,", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I've filed a report with the CFPB.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1374, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "As a banker in a small bank, I have been on both sides of the collection business.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Bankers have to prove a debt and give consumers a chance of object to the validity.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "5"], "text": "When I have had collection agencys contact us for medical collections, I found these people to be scum.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They don't care if the debt is valid, correct, or anything else.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They just know that they get 50% of everything they collect.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4"], "text": "You can request that they not contact you again, but they will.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "My suggestion is that collection agencies not be allowed to call at all and all correspondence be in writing.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If anyone can tell me what I owe and why I owe it, I will pay it.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They can't and they don't care.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1375, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "While I do not advocate daily robo-calling, I have to wonder why a consumer finds themselves on the receiving end of these calls?", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Receiving the daily call would indicate the consumer is also continually ignoring this debt.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sadly, there is a demographic that thinks this way.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the consumer has found themselves in a tough spot I would think they would choose to take the call or contact the debt collecting entity to try to remedy the situation.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "As far as regulations I do believe that one call a week is sufficient.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The idea of the robo-call is to keep the debt on the consumers mind in an effort that when they get the money they will remember to call and pay the debt.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Any other purpose I think would be considered an attempt to annoy the consumer into paying.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The demographic that allows this is never going to pay anyway ", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "so why play the game.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Even a robo-call costs money ", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "so why continually throw good money after bad.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In 30 years of this business I realize there are two types of people, the one's who want to pay their bill and the ones who never intended to pay in the first place.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1377, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Some of us find ourselves on the receiving end of daily (or more frequent) robo calls ", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because we have common last names.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And I do think that the debt collectors who have called me would very much like me to pay the debt even though it isn't mine.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1378, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The state, county, city make their own laws.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is what I have ran into", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and if a person does not hire a lawyer, are not a big group, there isn't much hope for the consumer.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The law where everyone may hire a lawyer has limits--IE: Will not take a criminal or money cases if a non profit org. or free lawyer takes the case.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I darn sure do not understand the laws etc.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I have tried to read about all this for 2 years.", "type": "testimony", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Of course I'm old and 100% DAV,", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "that could be it.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1380, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "The ACA's (debt collectors) positions on the CFPB's proposed rules is disgusting!!", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is laughable!", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "See for yourself America,", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "here it is: http://www.acainternational.org/files.aspx?p=/images/31323/aca-anpr-comments.pdf", "type": "reference", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1382, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "There are a few states that have the barbaric practice of actually arresting people for their debts by using a legal loophole.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Some of the most egregious examples are in Minnesota, Illinois, and Missouri.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The creditor sues the debtor in court.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the person fails to show, a warrant can be issued for their arrest.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The police can actually arrest and jail the debtor until a court hearing, or until they pay the bond (which is usually the amount of the debt).", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is a downright abuse of the legal system.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These loopholes need to be closed in all states.", "type": "policy", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1383, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I've heard multiple stories of summons being dropped off or served to the wrong individual and summons being mailed to old addresses when the new address was clearly available.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "I don't believe that a summons should ever be served by mail. ", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1"], "text": "If the debt collector wants to sue, they should be required to serve the person directly in the city and state in which they currently reside.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "It's an especially dirty tactic to serve someone by mail.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It's unreliable and puts the debtor at a disadvantage.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1384, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I agree. ", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, I believe that having a universal or national statute of limitations would alleviate this problem.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The current system is too confusing.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1385, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "Notification that a debt is being sold would be ideal ", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as it would afford the debtor the opportunity to negotiate the amount and possibly assist in thwarting any potential negative reporting on one's credit report.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a debtor is afforded the opportunity to negotiate his or her debt for a reasonable amount, perhaps the selling and reselling of debt may be marginalized.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "More and more consumers have emails and other modes of communication", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "and therefore, it would be in the best interest of all parties to amicably resolve issues.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "However, should the dispute not be quelled, reasonable arrangements should be afforded to the debtor.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Debts as assets is an outrageous concept ", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and it behooves both the debtor and the creditor to \"work-it-out\".", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "That is in the best interest of all.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It begins with information, communication and resolution.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1386, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["2"], "text": "i agree. ", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "their comments are outrageous and is just more of the same.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "why should we expect a lobby group of debt collectors to really want enforceable new rules?", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1387, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Yes, if the account is still open the bank must hold onto the agreement for 20 years.", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If the account went delinquent 20 years before litigation then the statute of limitations has long passed and the lawsuit is frivolous;", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "it should be dismissed with sanctions.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1388, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I appreciate Mr. Bartmann's comments", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they appear to be grounded in a collection agency perspective ", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "(there is always business and market share tension between collection agencies and law firms).", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The reality is that (and this was voiced by other participants) many (not all but many) debtors simply won't/can't pay until they have to.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The FDCPA and TCPA have truly made communications with debtor both difficult and hazardous for the collector.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For instance, the fact that you can't safely leave a voice message for a debtor should be very troubling.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Over the years, our firm has stopped initial outbound calling (responding only to inbound calls) and also limited our pre-suit letters to just two.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We send the required disclosure letter and (there being no response and the account reviewed for suit) then send a discounted payment offer that says we are going to file suit but would rather settle.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We offer reasonable terms to the debtors to avoid a costly suit but ", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "the response rate is absolutely miserable, probably in the single digits percentage wise.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Believe me, suits are time consuming and expensive, ", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but they are often simply the only option.", "type": "fact", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Even when the debtors are served, few contact us, and even fewer when the court sends them the judgment.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Worse, a judgment doesn't guarantee payment on the account.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Clarification via Regulations as to what we can say and do in communications would at least promote more communication between the parties.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "With that, perhaps more points of contact could resolve debts before suit.", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["17"], "text": "I strongly disagree that litigation should be \"discouraged\"", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as it is not only a simple reality in much of debt collection but a fundamental right of a creditor.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, I think Regulations making it clear what can and cannot be done in communications that can shield the industry from the wild west of FDCPA and TCPA lawsuits would greatly encourage more communication.", "type": "value", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["21"], "text": "I also think a reasonable, good faith attempt to resolve the case (offering a payment plan and/or lump sum) before suit is filed is still a good idea as well ", "type": "value", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "even though our own response rate has not been great.", "type": "value", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Anything more will infringe on a creditor's rights and interfere with state law.", "type": "value", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Perhaps the CFPB Portal could have a debt resolution aspect to it where a debtor could try to resolve an account in a \"safer\" more disarming manner.", "type": "value", "id": 22, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1389, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "This is the problem.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What account would stay open for 20 years after being delinquent.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It seems to me this is just a way to prolong as long as possible the ability to harass people for very old debt.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "There needs to be time limits.", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This type of thing, re-filing debt, selling the same debt to someone else, and then adding it back AGAIN to the credit report is just an excuse to harass the heck out of people and do it legally.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "These are not good business practices.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is harassment.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once a debt is placed on a credit report -- or even sooner -- once the debt letter is sent, time should start running and this agency needs to set time limits that are reasonable.", "type": "policy", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Creditors have a right to try to collect true, accurate debt.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But what happens is the debt is wildly inflated, then it runs the gamut of various collection agencies until nobody even remembers its genesis.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is all to harass.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1390, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "That might work if each state had reasonable, intelligent and realistic collection rules.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But just the fact that the cost of getting a report varies wildly shows such disparities from state to state.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["1", "3"], "text": "My opinion is that there desperately needs to be some uniformity.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This would help people to know what is expected of them, and what to expect.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1394, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "CG I endorse and want to add again at the risk of sounding like a broken record, it is the wild fluctuation in rules across the country.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is not a \"state's rights\" issue as someone wants to make it, but a way to bring some fairness and intelligence to this process.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1395, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "What Nancy H said exemplifies the problem: no standards across the board.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "What happens to you in this situation depends on the collection agency, the creditor (in the first place) and where you live.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Where you live should not be a factor.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1398, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "This is the PROBLEM over and over", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Why should lawyers get a pass from rules of the Bar Associations or rules of the court because they are now considered \"debt collectors\"", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "even I did not know this, though I have seen advertised quite a bit lawyers in the \"collection\" business.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is wrong.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "I hope if anything, this very thing is addressed.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Using a lawyer to send a letter is often a way to intimidate.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "People become too frightened to even respond.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "The rules are blown off by lawyers who go into this debt collection business ", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they make a fast easy buck, and they know the debtor has very little recourse, and there is so few rules that protect the consumer/debtor.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Being in debt stopped being a crime decades ago,", "type": "fact", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but the lack of rules that protect the debtor are bringing back these draconian practices.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Uniformity, is needed, and making lawyers abide by the rules of the Bar.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is bringing to light why this system has become so fraught with abuse.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1399, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I got hit with a notice from a doctor's office and his collection agency that I owed and -- get this -- never responded to their notices.", "type": "testimony", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "First, I never got any notices ", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and second, I called the doctor's office and validated that I have never been a patient there.", "type": "testimony", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The office manager even wrote a letter to the collection agency.", "type": "testimony", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0_1"], "text": "It was clearly THEIR mistake,", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "The collection agency got all hot and bothered and rude to me", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because then they had to pay to remove the notice of me \"owing\" a debt from the three credit reporting agencies", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "boy I hope you go after these cowboys next -- ", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and yet it was removed.", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But while waiting for the letter, I managed to actually get someone on the phone from Equifax,", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was so angry, ", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and their attitude was, \"we just report this\" blah blah blah.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "I say there ought to be sanctions, monetary sanctions, against these credit reporting agencies for making these mistakes and their cavalier attitude.", "type": "policy", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They have this attitude of, so what?", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This has been more than two years ago and still seethe because of the cavalier and rude attitude when it was clearly their mistake.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I even called MY eye doctor and had him write a letter that I was HIS patient.", "type": "testimony", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You think things don't get out of hand?", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "YOu don't know how this kind of thing hurts people's ratings, scores whatever and then add insult to injury when you deal with rude inept people.", "type": "value", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Hit them in the pocketbook and you will see how fast they will make sure they do not make any mistakes.", "type": "policy", "id": 18, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1400, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "You are not living in the real world if you think it is just so easy, RBell.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "No, most consumers are not lawyers.", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "The people using these debt collection practices are deliberately abusing the law ", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because they know most who are harassed and in debt and working people who probably can't afford a lawyer.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And I'll just bet it is worst in the states with the least amount of consumer protection.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Take care.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "You will sing a different tune when it is you on the meat hook.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1401, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Good idea debt neutrality.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "But the sad thing is, being in debt is NOT considered a crime", "type": "fact", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "however, the way the laws are now, and the abuses these collection agencies engage in, you might as well be considered a criminal.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I agree.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Set up a system where the consumer is on equal footing with the debt collectors.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1403, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Get a copy of the police report ", "type": "policy", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and mail it to all three.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They HAVE to put a freeze on your report, ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and you get a pin, ", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and if you have to lift it you need to have that pin.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "It is quite a pain.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I had a burglary in 2012 -- 14 pages of items stolen, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "I had to call all my credit cards and get issued new ones.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Heartbreaking --not just things like my computer, but items of great value, and great sentimental value.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The least you should have is the peace of mind of having a freeze on your report.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And they HAVE to do it.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "Otherwise, go to a lawyer and let them dangle on the end of the meat hook.", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It is a pain, but worth doing.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1405, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I disagree.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Keeping a paper trail protects everyone, especially the most vulnerable and least able to protect oneself.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1407, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I agree with you that being in debt is not a crime,", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "however, if a debtor defaults on a debt they basically have no rights if they cannot afford an attorney ", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as one will not be provided for them by the state.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Pro Se can easily become a mess ", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["5"], "text": "as no one will actually help with the paperwork, ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "even state funded pro se agencies are simply paid to show where to get the right papers, not to fill them out.", "type": "fact", "id": 5, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1408, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Because credit card contracts are adhesion contracts,", "type": "fact", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["0"], "text": "it is up to educated third party observers to make sure the adhesion contract is fair.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If a person experiences a dramatic event beyond their control that reduces their income, it seems questionable to not allow the debtor the right to suspend the interest rate charges, penalties and fees until they have regained their income.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "They are still promising to pay,", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but since their life has been turned upside down by an event beyond their control, ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "that should have standing in some cases.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["7"], "text": "It just doesn't seem ethical to punish a consumer ", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because their home washes down the river one day, or is burned to the ground by a wild fire, destroyed in an earthquake, and so on.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It especially does not seem ethical that the credit card companies are allowed to hide how they will punish a consumer if the consumer's intent was always to make their payments and it took an act of God to prevent that from happening.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Insurance policies do not cover acts of war, ", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "yet our own government allowed the owner of the twin towers to collect on their insurance policy ", "type": "fact", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "even though 911 was clearly an act of war.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I believe there have been polls that show a majority of americans are upset because the 2008 bailouts did not give them any respite of any kind.", "type": "fact", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The \"Promise to Pay\" says nothing about making that payment every month above and beyond all other situations and scenarios.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I believe judges have misinterpreted Promise to Pay and that lawyers like the way it is set up now ", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["14", "16"], "text": "so they don't want to challenge the obvious holes in credit card adhesion contracts", "type": "value", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because it could quash their own future income stream.", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1409, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "it still bothers me that \"financial literacy\" may be the escape clause that the CFPB uses to avoid the real issue.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "How about rewarding those of us who have tirelessly blogged about exposing the financial traps set up by the credit card companies, especially those of us who did it all on our own dime and time.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Credit Cards are THE BIGGEST PROFIT MAKING scheme in the U.S., much bigger than the mortgage industry.", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And as the CFPB knows, any type of money making machine gets protected through lobbying.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That is exactly why the CFPB was able to fine the credit card companies well over 1/2 billion dollars for aggressively marketing the credit-protector Insurance program.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "When something makes so much money so easily, people just can't help themselves to try and keep expanding the money making venture.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I personally warned about the credit card credit protector programs almost FIVE YEARS BEFORE the CFPB made their over half billion in fines.", "type": "testimony", "id": 6, "evidence": ["7"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.credit-protector.com\">Credit-Protector</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I created my site on my own time and with no funding,", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "and I think my warning almost five years before should matter.", "type": "policy", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also don't understand why someone like myself who created my warning so early on, with no funding, can't be compensated on any level simply as a way to energize future generations that if they take the time and show they care for something that matters, they may someday be publicly rewarded/acknowledged.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also created blogs about Chase Bank and their credit card shenanigans back in 2009.", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once again, the class action lawyers swooped in and took 25 million dollars in legal fees.", "type": "fact", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I didn't see a dime for my blogging", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "even though my 2009 protest blogs probably helped fuel the justified anger by some consumers who then went on a mission to get a class action lawyer involved.", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Once again, I got nothing.", "type": "testimony", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If Government Consumer Organizations are not willing to acknowledge those who care and show it, the system may never truly improve.", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.daily-protest.blogspot.com\">Daily-Protest</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 17, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.bloggersagainstchasebank.blogspot.com\">Bloggers Against Chase Bank</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 18, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.parallelforreclosure.blogspot.com\">Parallel Foreclosure</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 19, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.swarmthebanks.blogspot.com\">Swarm The Banks</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 20, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.wallstreetchange.blogspot.com\">Wall Street Change</a>", "type": "reference", "id": 21, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I have gone out of my way to offer financial literacy through the exposure of unfair credit card and banking policies for several years now.", "type": "value", "id": 22, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The tree fell, people heard it, but no one made a sound.", "type": "value", "id": 23, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1410, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "Even when the right person is hauled into court, everything From_ill_annoy stated is still true.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Defaulters should not be forced to complete the same type of court papers that those accused of crimes are required to fill out and file.", "type": "policy", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Since debt collection is not considered a criminal act, ", "type": "fact", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "filing papers should be much much easier for the defendant, ", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["2"], "text": "and, a defendant should be allowed to plead Involuntary Default and get a better result. such as the freezing of all interest rate charges, penalties and fees in exchange for the promise to pay, even if it takes ten years.", "type": "policy", "id": 4, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1411, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["3"], "text": "The Permissible hours of 9am - 8 pm is good.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I actually would like to see it moved to the other proposed time of 9am - 7pm,", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "but i think 8pm is a fair compromise.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "Because the current 8am - 9pm really is just way to early/late.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I (and many families) are in bed after 8pm ", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["4"], "text": "and phone afer 8pm really is way too late.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "I support the 9am - 8pm hours.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "I further support weekend calling lessened to noon-5pm ", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "because people like to sleep in on the weekends and spend time with family.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "Having a phone call after 5pm really is not necessary ", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "as most people will be out and/or entertaining guests at their homes and will not take calls in the afternoon.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "I further support adherence to blue laws that prohibit consumer contact on Sundays.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Sundays really are when most people are spending whatever little time they have left before the workweek with friends and family.", "type": "value", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["12"], "text": "I do not conduct business on Sundays.", "type": "testimony", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The work week really should be when debt collectors are working on trying to contact consumers.", "type": "policy", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1412, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "This Draft Summary of Discussion fails to address the issues of confusion about the statute of limitations and how they vary among states.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is a big source of confusion in terms of collection of a debt and jurisdiction.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3", "4", "6"], "text": "Creating a more stanadrized set of rules would alleviate these problems.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "In 2010, the FTC released a report, \"Repairing A Broken System,\" which made mention of the need a universal statute of limitations.", "type": "fact", "id": 3, "evidence": ["12"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Additionally, in 2011 ACA's plan, \"The Path Forward: ACA International\"s Blueprint for Modernizing America\"s Consumer Debt Collection System\" also advocated for a national statute of limitations.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": ["14"]}, {"reasons": null, "text": "This is something that both sides of the industry actually agree upon.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "50 different states and 50 different statutes make it too confusing for consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I also reiterate that a compromise in terms of years can be reached.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["9"], "text": "Also, debt tolling needs to be done away with.", "type": "policy", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It only adds to the confusion of when a debt becomes time-barred.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "We live in a transient society.", "type": "value", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A debt should not legally follow a person for the rest of their life:", "type": "policy", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Repairing A Broken System - Federal Trade Commission: http://www.ftc.gov/sites/default/files/documents/public_events/life-debt/debtcollectionreport_0.pdf", "type": "reference", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "InsideArm: Statutes of Limitations Frustrate Debt Collectors and Consumers http://www.insidearm.com/daily/debt-buying-topics/debt-buying/statutes-of-limitations-frustrate-debt-collectors-and-consumers", "type": "reference", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The Path Forward: ACA International\"s Blueprint for Modernizing America\"s Consumer Debt Collection System: http://www.acainternational.org/files.aspx?p=/images/18898/finalblueprint-designedversion.pdf", "type": "reference", "id": 14, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1414, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "I would disagree that there is confusion among consumers about SOL which would, as you suggest, require the need for a national SOL.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The only time I have personally seen SOL straddle a line is when a consumer moves to another state with a different SOL.", "type": "testimony", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["3"], "text": "The clarity needs to be in these such cases.", "type": "policy", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Because once a debtor moves, both parties claim the SOL where it benefits them for their desired outcome.", "type": "value", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A national SOL only benefits the debt collectors and not the consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "The focus should remain on creating, as best as possible, a win-win solution that benefits the debt collectors the consumers.", "type": "policy", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Having a national SOL of 7 years as ACA International wants compromises state laws wherein some states of SOL of 3 years (and otherwise less than 7).", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A SOL is meant to bring resolve.", "type": "value", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "And in reality, if a debt collector/debt owner can not resolve their clients issues within the already established SOL of each state, then extending the SOL or having a national SOL under which to bring suit does nothing but allow debt collectors to continue to harass consumers.", "type": "value", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Three years really is more than enough time to sue.", "type": "value", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Just as criminal defendants are entitled to a quick and speedy trail, so should consumers who may/may not be aware they have an outstanding debt.", "type": "policy", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["8"], "text": "That is to say: having a national SOL is a guise to prolong resolution rather than a more quick a final resolve in when to bring suit.", "type": "value", "id": 11, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1417, "propositions": [{"reasons": ["1"], "text": "I respectfully disagree with your assessment.", "type": "value", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "If anything, I believe that a national statute of limitations would actually stop the process of zombie debt.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "We live in a transient society.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Assume that a national SOL were to be adapted\"", "type": "policy", "id": 3, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Also, you did not address the issue of tolling.", "type": "fact", "id": 4, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["6"], "text": "Again, we live in a transient society.", "type": "value", "id": 5, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "People move from place to place.", "type": "fact", "id": 6, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "For example, I had a medical crisis in Illinois.", "type": "testimony", "id": 7, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I was not able to keep up with the debt. ", "type": "testimony", "id": 8, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "I moved back to my home state of Wisconsin in a town 25 miles away from the Illinois border.", "type": "testimony", "id": 9, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Now, because I live in Wisconsin, ", "type": "testimony", "id": 10, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["10"], "text": "the SOL has passed ", "type": "testimony", "id": 11, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": ["11"], "text": "and I can no longer be sued here.", "type": "testimony", "id": 12, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "However, should I ever choose to move back to Illinois (which I can't unless I want my credit destroyed and want to get sued) it\"s as though the debt never went away due to their tolling laws and longer SOL.", "type": "value", "id": 13, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "It seems that the rationale behind your argument is to solely protect those people who live in states with short SOLs (3-4 years).", "type": "value", "id": 14, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "That\"s not even 50 %.", "type": "fact", "id": 15, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "A reasonable universal statute of limitations would make things more clear.", "type": "value", "id": 16, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "At the very least, tolling provisions should be eliminated should states have their own statute of limitations.", "type": "policy", "id": 17, "evidence": null}]}
{"commentID": 1418, "propositions": [{"reasons": null, "text": "For further reference on debt tolling: http://collectionagencydebt.blogspot.com/2012/08/tolling-debt-and-statute-of-limitations.html", "type": "reference", "id": 0, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "So, again, it seems as though the SOL matters very little in these cases.", "type": "value", "id": 1, "evidence": null}, {"reasons": null, "text": "Perhaps the bigger question is whether or not eliminating debt tolling should be considered as a new rule.", "type": "value", "id": 2, "evidence": null}]}
